name: AADInternals
description: [AADInternals](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0677) is a PowerShell-based framework for administering, enumerating, and exploiting Azure Active Directory. The tool is publicly available on GitHub.(Citation: AADInternals Github)(Citation: AADInternals Documentation)

description: [ABK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0469) is a downloader that has been used by [BRONZE BUTLER](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0060) since at least 2019.(Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019)

name: ADVSTORESHELL
description: [ADVSTORESHELL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0045) is a spying backdoor that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) from at least 2012 to 2016. It is generally used for long-term espionage and is deployed on targets deemed interesting after a reconnaissance phase. (Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy) (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)
relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist Sofacy Feb 2018),(Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy),,(Citation: Bitdefender APT28 Dec 2015),(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2),(Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy)

name: ASPXSpy
description: [ASPXSpy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0073) is a Web shell. It has been modified by [Threat Group-3390](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0027) actors to create the ASPXTool version. (Citation: Dell TG-3390)
relationship citations: (Citation: Dell TG-3390),(Citation: Profero APT27 December 2020),(Citation: Volexity Exchange Marauder March 2021),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT39 Jan 2019),(Citation: McAfee Night Dragon),(Citation: Dell TG-3390)

relationship citations: ,,(Citation: MalwareBytes SideCopy Dec 2021)

name: AdFind

name: Agent Tesla
description: [Agent Tesla](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0331) is a spyware Trojan written for the .NET framework that has been observed since at least 2014.(Citation: Fortinet Agent Tesla April 2018)(Citation: Bitdefender Agent Tesla April 2020)(Citation: Malwarebytes Agent Tesla April 2020)

name: Agent.btz
description: [Agent.btz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0092) is a worm that primarily spreads itself via removable devices such as USB drives. It reportedly infected U.S. military networks in 2008. (Citation: Securelist Agent.btz)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Securelist Agent.btz),(Citation: ThreatExpert Agent.btz)
description_zh: [agent.btz]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0092）是一种蠕虫，主要通过可移动设备（例如USB驱动器）传播自身。据报道，它在2008年感染了美国军事网络。（引文：Securelist Agent.btz）

name: Amadey
description: [Amadey](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1025) is a Trojan bot that has been used since at least October 2018.(Citation: Korean FSI TA505 2020)(Citation: BlackBerry Amadey 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Korean FSI TA505 2020),(Citation: BlackBerry Amadey 2020),,(Citation: Korean FSI TA505 2020),(Citation: BlackBerry Amadey 2020)

name: Anchor
description: [Anchor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0504) is one of a family of backdoor malware that has been used in conjunction with [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) on selected high profile targets since at least 2018.(Citation: Cyberreason Anchor December 2019)(Citation: Medium Anchor DNS July 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cyberreason Anchor December 2019),(Citation: Medium Anchor DNS July 2020)

name: AppleJeus
description: [AppleJeus](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0584) is a family of downloaders initially discovered in 2018 embedded within trojanized cryptocurrency applications. [AppleJeus](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0584) has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032), targeting companies in the energy, finance, government, industry, technology, and telecommunications sectors, and several countries including the United States, United Kingdom, South Korea, Australia, Brazil, New Zealand, and Russia. [AppleJeus](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0584) has been used to distribute the [FALLCHILL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0181) RAT.(Citation: CISA AppleJeus Feb 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: CISA AppleJeus Feb 2021),,(Citation: CISA AppleJeus Feb 2021),(Citation: ObjectiveSee AppleJeus 2019)
description_zh: [Applejeus]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0584）是最初在2018年发现的下载者一家，该家庭嵌入了Trojanized Cryptocurrency应用程序中。 [applejeus]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0584）已被[Lazarus Group]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0032），能源，金融，金融，金融，金融，金融公司的目标公司政府，工业，技术和电信部门以及美国，英国，韩国，澳大利亚，巴西，新西兰和俄罗斯等几个国家。 [Applejeus]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0584）已用于分发[fallchill]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0181）rat。 2021）

name: AppleSeed
description: [AppleSeed](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0622) is a backdoor that has been used by [Kimsuky](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0094) to target South Korean government, academic, and commercial  targets since at least 2021.(Citation: Malwarebytes Kimsuky June 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Malwarebytes Kimsuky June 2021),(Citation: KISA Operation Muzabi),,(Citation: Malwarebytes Kimsuky June 2021),(Citation: KISA Operation Muzabi)
description_zh: [appleseed]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0622）是[Kimsuky]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0094）使用的后门至少自2021年以来的学术和商业目标。（引文：Malwarebytes Kimsuky 2021年6月）

name: Aria-body
description: [Aria-body](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0456) is a custom backdoor that has been used by [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019) since approximately 2017.(Citation: CheckPoint Naikon May 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CheckPoint Naikon May 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021),,(Citation: CheckPoint Naikon May 2020)
description_zh: [ARIA-BODY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0456）是一种自定义后门。

name: Arp
description: [Arp](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0099) displays and modifies information about a system's Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) cache. (Citation: TechNet Arp)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018),(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),,(Citation: Palo Alto ARP),(Citation: TechNet Arp)

name: Astaroth
description: [Astaroth](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0373) is a Trojan and information stealer known to affect companies in Europe, Brazil, and throughout Latin America. It has been known publicly since at least late 2017. (Citation: Cybereason Astaroth Feb 2019)(Citation: Cofense Astaroth Sept 2018)(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cofense Astaroth Sept 2018),(Citation: Cybereason Astaroth Feb 2019),(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
description_zh: [astaroth]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0373）是一家特洛伊木马和信息窃取者，已知会影响欧洲，巴西和整个拉丁美洲的公司。至少从2017年下半年开始就公开闻名。

name: Attor
description: [Attor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0438) is a Windows-based espionage platform that has been seen in use since 2013. [Attor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0438) has a loadable plugin architecture to customize functionality for specific targets.(Citation: ESET Attor Oct 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Attor Oct 2019)
description_zh: [atter]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0438）是一个基于Windows的Espionage平台，自2013年以来一直在使用中。 S0438）具有可加载的插件体系结构，可自定义特定目标的功能。（引用：ESET Attor 2019年10月）

name: AuTo Stealer
description: [AuTo Stealer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1029) is malware written in C++ has been used by [SideCopy](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1008) since at least December 2021 to target government agencies and personnel in India and Afghanistan.(Citation: MalwareBytes SideCopy Dec 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: MalwareBytes SideCopy Dec 2021)
description_zh: [自动窃取器]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1029）是[sidecopy]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g1008）以C ++编写的恶意软件。 2021年针对印度和阿富汗的政府机构和人员。

name: AuditCred
description: [AuditCred](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0347) is a malicious DLL that has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) during their 2018 attacks.(Citation: TrendMicro Lazarus Nov 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro Lazarus Nov 2018),,(Citation: TrendMicro Lazarus Nov 2018)
description_zh: [AuditCred](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0347) is a malicious DLL that has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) during their 2018 attacks 。

name: AutoIt backdoor
description: [AutoIt backdoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0129) is malware that has been used by the actors responsible for the MONSOON campaign. The actors frequently used it in weaponized .pps files exploiting CVE-2014-6352. (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon) This malware makes use of the legitimate scripting language for Windows GUI automation with the same name.
relationship citations: (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),,(Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon)
description_zh: [autoit Backdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0129）是由负责季风活动的参与者使用的恶意软件。演员经常在利用CVE-2014-6352的武器化.PPS文件中使用它。 （引用：Forcepoint季风）此恶意软件利用了具有相同名称的Windows GUI自动化的合法脚本语言。

name: Avaddon
description: [Avaddon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0640) is ransomware written in C++ that has been offered as Ransomware-as-a-Service (RaaS) since at least June 2020.(Citation: Awake Security Avaddon)(Citation: Arxiv Avaddon Feb 2021)
contributors: Matt Brenton, Zurich Global Information Security
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Awake Security Avaddon),(Citation: Arxiv Avaddon Feb 2021),(Citation: Hornet Security Avaddon June 2020)
description_zh: [avaddon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0640）是用C ++编写的勒索软件，该勒索软件至少自2020年6月以来以Ransomware-as-a-Service（RAAS）提供。 ）（引文：Arxiv Avaddon 2021年2月）

name: Avenger
description: [Avenger](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0473) is a downloader that has been used by [BRONZE BUTLER](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0060) since at least 2019.(Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019),,(Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019)
description_zh: [Avenger]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0473）是[Bronze Butler]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0060）以来一直使用的下载器，至少至少在2019年以来。 （引文：趋势微滴答2019年11月）

name: Azorult
description:
[Azorult](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0344) is a commercial Trojan that is used to steal information from compromised hosts. [Azorult](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0344) has been observed in the wild as early as 2016.
In July 2018, [Azorult](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0344) was seen used in a spearphishing campaign against targets in North America. [Azorult](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0344) has been seen used for cryptocurrency theft. (Citation: Unit42 Azorult Nov 2018)(Citation: Proofpoint Azorult July 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCC Group TA505),,(Citation: Unit42 Azorult Nov 2018),(Citation: Proofpoint Azorult July 2018)
description_zh:
[azorult]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0344）是一种商业特洛伊木马，用于从折衷的主机中窃取信息。 [Azorult]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0344）早在2016年就在野外观察到。
2018年7月，[Azorult]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0344）在针对北美目标的一场反对目标运动中使用了。 [azorult]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0344）已用于加密货币盗窃。 （引文：Unit42 Azorult 2018年11月）（引文：2018年7月Azorult Azorult）

name: BACKSPACE
description: [BACKSPACE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0031) is a backdoor used by [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) that dates back to at least 2005. (Citation: FireEye APT30)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT30),,(Citation: FireEye APT30)
description_zh: [backspace]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0031）是[apt30]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0013）使用的后门，至少可追溯到2005年。（引用：FireEye APT30）

name: BADCALL
description: [BADCALL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0245) is a Trojan malware variant used by the group [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032). (Citation: US-CERT BADCALL)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT BADCALL),,(Citation: US-CERT BADCALL)
description_zh: [BADCALL]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0245）是由[Lazarus Group]组使用的Trojan恶意软件变体（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0032）。 （引用：US-CERT BADCALL）

name: BADFLICK
description: [BADFLICK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0642) is a backdoor used by [Leviathan](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0065) in spearphishing campaigns first reported in 2018 that targeted the U.S. engineering and maritime industries.(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)(Citation: Accenture MUDCARP March 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Accenture MUDCARP March 2019),(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),,(Citation: Accenture MUDCARP March 2019)
description_zh: [BADFLICK]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0642）是[leviathan]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0065）使用的后期，在2018年首次报道了针对性的销售活动。美国工程和海事工业。

name: BADNEWS
description: [BADNEWS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0128) is malware that has been used by the actors responsible for the [Patchwork](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0040) campaign. Its name was given due to its use of RSS feeds, forums, and blogs for command and control. (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon) (Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon),(Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017),,(Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon),(Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017),(Citation: PaloAlto Patchwork Mar 2018)
description_zh: [BADNEWS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0128）是恶意软件，已由负责[PatchWork]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0040）的参与者使用。它的名称是由于它使用RSS提要，论坛和博客进行命令和控制。 （引文：力点季风）（引文：TrendMicro Patchwork 2017年12月）

name: BBK

relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019),,(Citation: Trend Micro Tick November 2019)
description_zh: [BBK]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0470）是[Bronze Butler]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0060）以来一直使用的下载器，至少至少从2019年开始使用。 （引文：趋势微滴答2019年11月）

name: BBSRAT
description: [BBSRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0127) is malware with remote access tool functionality that has been used in targeted compromises. (Citation: Palo Alto Networks BBSRAT)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Palo Alto Networks BBSRAT)
description_zh: [bbsrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0127）是恶意软件，具有远程访问工具功能，已在目标妥协中使用。 （引文：帕洛阿尔托网络BBSRAT）

name: BISCUIT

relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1),,(Citation: Mandiant APT1),(Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix)

relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT41 March 2020),(Citation: Kaspersky Lyceum October 2021),(Citation: TrendMicro Tropic Trooper Mar 2018),(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),(Citation: Kaspersky Ferocious Kitten Jun 2021),,(Citation: TrendMicro Tropic Trooper Mar 2018),(Citation: Microsoft BITSAdmin),(Citation: Microsoft About BITS)

name: BLACKCOFFEE
description: [BLACKCOFFEE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0069) is malware that has been used by several Chinese groups since at least 2013. (Citation: FireEye APT17) (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT17),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),,(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT17)

relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT BLINDINGCAN Aug 2020),,(Citation: NHS UK BLINDINGCAN Aug 2020),(Citation: US-CERT BLINDINGCAN Aug 2020)

name: BLUELIGHT

relationship citations: (Citation: Volexity InkySquid BLUELIGHT August 2021),,(Citation: Volexity InkySquid BLUELIGHT August 2021)

name: BONDUPDATER
description: [BONDUPDATER](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0360) is a PowerShell backdoor used by [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049). It was first observed in November 2017 during targeting of a Middle Eastern government organization, and an updated version was observed in August 2018 being used to target a government organization with spearphishing emails.(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017)(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig Sep 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig Sep 2018),,(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig Sep 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017)
description_zh: [bondupdater]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0360）是[oilrig]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0049）使用的PowerShell Backdoor。它于2017年11月在目标中东政府组织中首次观察，并于2018年8月观察到更新版本，用于针对带有矛盾电子邮件的政府组织。 2018年9月）

name: BOOSTWRITE
description: [BOOSTWRITE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0415) is a loader crafted to be launched via abuse of the DLL search order of applications used by [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046).(Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019),,(Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019)
description_zh: [BOOSTWRITE]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0415）是一种装载机，该装载机是通过滥用[FIN7]（https://attack.mitre.orgg/ships of Application of Application of Application of Application启动的装载机组/G0046）。（引文：FireEye Fin7 2019年10月）

name: BOOTRASH
description: [BOOTRASH](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0114) is a [Bootkit](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1542/003) that targets Windows operating systems. It has been used by threat actors that target the financial sector.(Citation: Mandiant M Trends 2016)(Citation: FireEye Bootkits)(Citation: FireEye BOOTRASH SANS)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FireEye BOOTRASH SANS),(Citation: Mandiant M Trends 2016),(Citation: FireEye Bootkits)
description_zh: [bootrash]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0114）是[bootkit]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/techniques/t1542/003），目标是Windows操作系统。它已被针对金融部门的威胁参与者使用。

name: BS2005
description: [BS2005](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0014) is malware that was used by [Ke3chang](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0004) in spearphishing campaigns since at least 2011. (Citation: Mandiant Operation Ke3chang November 2014)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Mandiant Operation Ke3chang November 2014)
description_zh: [BS2005]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0014）是[ke3chang]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0004）在SpearPheshishing活动中至少从2011年开始使用的恶意软件（https://attpps://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org.org/groups/g0004）。 （引用：Mandiant操作KE3chang 2014年11月）

name: BUBBLEWRAP
description: [BUBBLEWRAP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0043) is a full-featured, second-stage backdoor used by the [admin@338](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0018) group. It is set to run when the system boots and includes functionality to check, upload, and register plug-ins that can further enhance its capabilities. (Citation: FireEye admin@338)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye admin@338),,(Citation: FireEye admin@338)
description_zh: [bubbleWrap]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0043）是[admin@338]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0018）使用完整的，第二阶段的后门） 团体。它设置为在系统启动并包含用于检查，上传和注册插件的功能时运行，以进一步增强其功能。 （引文：FireEye Admin@338）

name: Babuk
description: [Babuk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0638) is a Ransomware-as-a-service (RaaS) malware that has been used since at least 2021. The operators of [Babuk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0638) employ a "Big Game Hunting" approach to targeting major enterprises and operate a leak site to post stolen data as part of their extortion scheme.(Citation: Sogeti CERT ESEC Babuk March 2021)(Citation: McAfee Babuk February 2021)(Citation: CyberScoop Babuk February 2021)
contributors: Daniyal Naeem, BT Security; Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: McAfee Babuk February 2021),(Citation: Trend Micro Ransomware February 2021),(Citation: Medium Babuk February 2021),(Citation: Sogeti CERT ESEC Babuk March 2021)
description_zh: [Babuk]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0638）是一种勒索软件-AS-A-Service（RAAS）恶意软件，至少自2021年以来就被使用。[babuk]的运营商（https：/ /Attack.mitre.org/software/S0638）采用“大型游戏狩猎”方法来针对主要企业并操作泄漏站点以将被盗数据作为其勒索计划的一部分发布。引用：McAfee Babuk 2021年2月）（引文：Cyber​​scoop Babuk 2021年2月）

name: BabyShark
description: [BabyShark](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0414) is a Microsoft Visual Basic (VB) script-based malware family that is believed to be associated with several North Korean campaigns. (Citation: Unit42 BabyShark Feb 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Kimsuky November 2020),(Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020),(Citation: CISA AA20-301A Kimsuky),,(Citation: Unit42 BabyShark Apr 2019),(Citation: CISA AA20-301A Kimsuky),(Citation: Unit42 BabyShark Feb 2019),(Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020)
description_zh: [Babyshark]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0414）是Microsoft Visual Basic（VB）基于脚本的恶意软件家族，据信与多个朝鲜竞选活动有关。 （引文：Unit42 Babyshark 2019年2月）

name: BackConfig
description: [BackConfig](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0475) is a custom Trojan with a flexible plugin architecture that has been used by [Patchwork](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0040).(Citation: Unit 42 BackConfig May 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 BackConfig May 2020),,(Citation: Unit 42 BackConfig May 2020)
description_zh: [BackConfig]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0475）是一个自定义的木马，具有灵活的插件架构，该插件已被[PatchWork]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0040）使用。 。（引文：42单元BackConfig 2020年5月）

name: Backdoor.Oldrea
description: [Backdoor.Oldrea](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0093) is a modular backdoor that used by [Dragonfly](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0035) against energy companies since at least 2013. [Backdoor.Oldrea](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0093) was distributed via supply chain compromise, and included specialized modules to enumerate and map ICS-specific systems, processes, and protocols.(Citation: Symantec Dragonfly)(Citation: Gigamon Berserk Bear October 2021)(Citation: Symantec Dragonfly Sept 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Dragonfly),(Citation: Gigamon Berserk Bear October 2021),,(Citation: Symantec Dragonfly),(Citation: Gigamon Berserk Bear October 2021)
description_zh: [backdoor.oldrea]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0093）是一个模块化的后门，由[Dragonfly]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0035）使用，因为自从在能源公司开始至少2013年。[backdoor.oldrea]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0093）是通过供应链妥协分发的，并包括专门的模块以枚举和映射特定于ICS的系统，流程和协议。（引用。（引用。（引用。 ：Symantec Dragonfly）（引文：Gigamon berserk Bear 2021年10月）（引文：Symantec Dragonfly 2017年9月）

name: Bad Rabbit
description: [Bad Rabbit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0606) is a self-propagating ransomware that affected the Ukrainian transportation sector in 2017. [Bad Rabbit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0606) has also targeted organizations and consumers in Russia. (Citation: Secure List Bad Rabbit)(Citation: ESET Bad Rabbit)(Citation: Dragos IT ICS Ransomware)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: Secure List Bad Rabbit),(Citation: ESET Bad Rabbit)
description_zh: [Bad Rabbit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0606）是一种自我传播的勒索软件，在2017年影响了乌克兰运输部门。 /s0606）还针对俄罗斯的组织和消费者。 （引用：安全列表坏兔子）（引文：eset坏兔子）（引文：Dragos IT ICS勒索软件）

name: BadPatch
description: [BadPatch](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0337) is a Windows Trojan that was used in a Gaza Hackers-linked campaign.(Citation: Unit 42 BadPatch Oct 2017)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit 42 BadPatch Oct 2017)
description_zh: [badpatch]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0337）是Windows Trojan，在加沙黑客挂钩的广告系列中使用。

name: Bandook
description: [Bandook](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0234) is a commercially available RAT, written in Delphi and C++, that has been available since at least 2007. It has been used against government, financial, energy, healthcare, education, IT, and legal organizations in the US, South America, Europe, and Southeast Asia. [Bandook](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0234) has been used by [Dark Caracal](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0070), as well as in a separate campaign referred to as "Operation Manul".(Citation: EFF Manul Aug 2016)(Citation: Lookout Dark Caracal Jan 2018)(Citation: CheckPoint Bandook Nov 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CheckPoint Bandook Nov 2020),(Citation: Lookout Dark Caracal Jan 2018),,(Citation: EFF Manul Aug 2016),(Citation: BH Manul Aug 2016),(Citation: CheckPoint Bandook Nov 2020),(Citation: Lookout Dark Caracal Jan 2018)
description_zh: [bandook]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0234）是一只商​​业上可用的老鼠，用Delphi和C ++编写，至少自2007年以来就可以使用。美国，南美，欧洲和东南亚的医疗保健，教育，IT和法律组织。 [bandook]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0234）已被[Dark Caracal]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0070）使用，并在单独的广告系列中使用作为“ Manul行动”。

name: Bankshot
description: [Bankshot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0239) is a remote access tool (RAT) that was first reported by the Department of Homeland Security in December of 2017. In 2018, [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) used the [Bankshot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0239) implant in attacks against the Turkish financial sector. (Citation: McAfee Bankshot)
relationship citations: (Citation: McAfee Bankshot),,(Citation: US-CERT Bankshot Dec 2017),(Citation: McAfee Bankshot)
description_zh: [bankShot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0239）是一种远程访问工具（RAT），由国土安全部首次报告2017年12月。2018年，[Lazarus Group]（https） ：//attack.mitre.org/groups/g0032）使用[bankShot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0239）植入对土耳其金融部门的攻击。 （引文：McAfee Bankshot）

name: Bazar
description: [Bazar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0534) is a downloader and backdoor that has been used since at least April 2020, with infections primarily against professional services, healthcare, manufacturing, IT, logistics and travel companies across the US and Europe. [Bazar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0534) reportedly has ties to [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) campaigns and can be used to deploy additional malware, including ransomware, and to steal sensitive data.(Citation: Cybereason Bazar July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: Google EXOTIC LILY March 2022),(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021),(Citation: NCC Group Team9 June 2020),(Citation: Zscaler Bazar September 2020),(Citation: Cybereason Bazar July 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk's Return October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021)
description_zh: [bazar]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0534）是下载器和后门，至少自2020年4月以来一直使用，主要针对专业服务，制造业，IT，物流，物流和旅行公司和旅行公司，主要是针对专业服务，整个美国和欧洲。据报道，[bazar]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0534）与[trickbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0266）有联系，可以用来部署其他Malwareware，Malwareware，Malware，Malware，，Malware，，Malware，，Malware，Warreware，Warter，包括勒索软件并窃取敏感数据。（引文：Cyber​​eason Bazar 2020年7月）

name: BendyBear
description: [BendyBear](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0574) is an x64 shellcode for a stage-zero implant designed to download malware from a C2 server. First discovered in August 2020, [BendyBear](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0574) shares a variety of features with [Waterbear](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0579), malware previously attributed to the Chinese cyber espionage group [BlackTech](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0098).(Citation: Unit42 BendyBear Feb 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit42 BendyBear Feb 2021)
description_zh: [bendybear]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0574）是X64 shellCode，用于从C2服务器下载恶意软件的Stage-Zero植入物。最初于2020年8月发现，[bendybear]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0574）与[waterbear]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0579）共享多种功能，Malware以前归因于中国网络间谍组[BlackTech]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0098）。（引用：Unit42 Bendybear 2021年2月）

name: Bisonal
description: [Bisonal](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0268) is a remote access tool (RAT) that has been used by [Tonto Team](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0131) against public and private sector organizations in Russia, South Korea, and Japan since at least December 2010.(Citation: Unit 42 Bisonal July 2018)(Citation: Talos Bisonal Mar 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Talos Bisonal Mar 2020),(Citation: Kaspersky CactusPete Aug 2020),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE HUNTLEY ),,(Citation: Unit 42 Bisonal July 2018),(Citation: Talos Bisonal Mar 2020),(Citation: Kaspersky CactusPete Aug 2020)
description_zh: [Bisonal](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0268) is a remote access tool (RAT) that has been used by [Tonto Team](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0131)至少从2010年12月起，针对俄罗斯，韩国和日本的公共和私营部门组织。

name: BitPaymer
description: [BitPaymer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0570) is a ransomware variant first observed in August 2017 targeting hospitals in the U.K. [BitPaymer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0570) uses a unique encryption key, ransom note, and contact information for each operation. [BitPaymer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0570) has several indicators suggesting overlap with the [Dridex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0384) malware and is often delivered via [Dridex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0384).(Citation: Crowdstrike Indrik November 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Crowdstrike Indrik November 2018),(Citation: Crowdstrike EvilCorp March 2021),,(Citation: Crowdstrike Indrik November 2018)
description_zh: [bitpaymer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0570）是2017年8月在英国（BitPaymer]（httpspaymer]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.orgg/software/software/software/s0570））的勒索软件变体。为每个操作使用唯一的加密密钥，赎金注释和联系信息。 [bitpaymer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0570）有几个指标，建议与[dridex]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0384）重叠，并且经常通过[通过[通过[ Dridex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0384）。（引用：CrowdStrike Indrik 2018年11月）

name: BlackEnergy
description: [BlackEnergy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0089) is a malware toolkit that has been used by both criminal and APT actors. It dates back to at least 2007 and was originally designed to create botnets for use in conducting Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks, but its use has evolved to support various plug-ins. It is well known for being used during the confrontation between Georgia and Russia in 2008, as well as in targeting Ukrainian institutions. Variants include BlackEnergy 2 and BlackEnergy 3. (Citation: F-Secure BlackEnergy 2014)
relationship citations: (Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: iSIGHT Sandworm 2014),(Citation: F-Secure BlackEnergy 2014),(Citation: UK NCSC Olympic Attacks October 2020),(Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: Securelist BlackEnergy Feb 2015),(Citation: ESET BlackEnergy Jan 2016),(Citation: ESEST Black Energy Jan 2016),(Citation: F-Secure BlackEnergy 2014),(Citation: Securelist BlackEnergy Nov 2014)
description_zh: [BlackEnergy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0089）是犯罪和APT参与者使用的恶意软件工具包。它的历史可以追溯到至少2007年，最初是为创建用于进行分布式服务（DDOS）攻击的僵尸网络而设计的，但其使用已进化为支持各种插件。它以2008年佐治亚州和俄罗斯之间的对抗以及针对乌克兰机构的对抗而闻名。变体包括Blackenergy 2和Blackenergy 3（引用：F-Secure Blackenergy 2014）

name: BlackMould
description: [BlackMould](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0564) is a web shell based on [China Chopper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0020) for servers running Microsoft IIS. First reported in December 2019, it has been used in malicious campaigns by [GALLIUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0093) against telecommunication providers.(Citation: Microsoft GALLIUM December 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft GALLIUM December 2019),,(Citation: Microsoft GALLIUM December 2019)
description_zh: [BlackMould]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0564）是一个基于[中国斩波器]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0020）的网络外壳，用于运行Microsoft IIS。首次报道2019年12月，它已在恶意运动中使用，该广告系列（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0093）针对电信提供者。（引用：Microsoft Gallium 2019年12月）

name: BloodHound
description: [BloodHound](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0521) is an Active Directory (AD) reconnaissance tool that can reveal hidden relationships and identify attack paths within an AD environment.(Citation: GitHub Bloodhound)(Citation: CrowdStrike BloodHound April 2018)(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCC Group TA505),(Citation: Cycraft Chimera April 2020),(Citation: ESET T3 Threat Report 2021),(Citation: Sophos New Ryuk Attack October 2020),(Citation: FireEye KEGTAP SINGLEMALT October 2020),(Citation: DHS/CISA Ransomware Targeting Healthcare October 2020),(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019),(Citation: CrowdStrike BloodHound April 2018),(Citation: GitHub Bloodhound)
description_zh: [BloodHound]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0521）是一个Active Directory（AD）侦察工具，可以揭示隐藏的关系并识别广告环境中的攻击路径。 Crowdstrike Bloodhound 2018年4月）（引文：Foxit Wocao 2019年12月）

name: Bonadan
description: [Bonadan](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0486) is a malicious version of OpenSSH which acts as a custom backdoor. [Bonadan](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0486) has been active since at least 2018 and combines a new cryptocurrency-mining module with the same credential-stealing module used by the Onderon family of backdoors.(Citation: ESET ForSSHe December 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET ForSSHe December 2018)
description_zh: [bonadan]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0486）是Openssh的恶意版本，可作为自定义后门。 [Bonadan]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0486）至少从2018年起就一直处于活动状态，并将新的加密货币 - 汇总模块与Onderderon家族使用的相同凭证stealing模块结合在一起。 ：Eset Forsshe 2018年12月）

name: BoomBox
description: [BoomBox](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0635) is a downloader responsible for executing next stage components that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2021.(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),,(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)
description_zh: [boombox]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0635）是一个下载器，负责执行[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.orgg/groups/groups/g0016）使用的下一阶段组件至少从2021年开始。

name: BoxCaon
description: [BoxCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0651) is a Windows backdoor that was used by [IndigoZebra](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0136) in a 2021 spearphishing campaign against Afghan government officials. [BoxCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0651)'s name stems from similarities shared with the malware family [xCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0653).(Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021)
contributors: Manikantan Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India; Yoshihiro Kori, NEC Corporation
relationship citations: (Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021),,(Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021)
description_zh: [boxcaon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0651）是一个Windows Backdoor，在2021年在2021年反对的运动中使用了[Indigozebra]（indigozebra]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0136））阿富汗政府官员。 [boxcaon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0651）的名称源于与恶意软件家族共享的相似之处[XCAON]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/software/s0653）。 ：Checkpoint Indigozebra 2021年7月）

name: Brave Prince
description: [Brave Prince](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0252) is a Korean-language implant that was first observed in the wild in December 2017. It contains similar code and behavior to [Gold Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0249), and was seen along with [Gold Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0249) and [RunningRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0253) in operations surrounding the 2018 Pyeongchang Winter Olympics. (Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
relationship citations: (Citation: Talos Kimsuky Nov 2021),,(Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
description_zh: [Brave Prince]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0252）是韩国语言植入物，在2017年12月在野外首次观察到。它包含与[Gold Dragon]（https：https：https：https：https：https：https：https：https：https： //attack.mitre.org/software/s0249），并与[Gold Dragon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0249）一起看到，并[runningrat]（https：//attps:/attack.mitre） Org/Software/S0253）在围绕2018年平昌冬季奥运会的运营中。 （引文：McAfee Gold Dragon）

name: Briba
description: [Briba](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0204) is a trojan used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) to open a backdoor and download files on to compromised hosts. (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012) (Citation: Symantec Briba May 2012)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Briba May 2012)
description_zh: [Briba]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0204）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的特洛伊木马，以打开后门和下载文件。受损的主机。 （引文：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec Briba 2012年5月）

name: Bumblebee
description: [Bumblebee](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1039) is a custom loader written in C++ that has been used by multiple threat actors, including possible initial access brokers, to download and execute additional payloads since at least March 2022. [Bumblebee](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1039) has been linked to ransomware operations including [Conti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0575), Quantum, and Mountlocker and derived its name from the appearance of "bumblebee" in the user-agent.(Citation: Google EXOTIC LILY March 2022)(Citation: Proofpoint Bumblebee April 2022)(Citation: Symantec Bumblebee June 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Google EXOTIC LILY March 2022),,(Citation: Cybereason Bumblebee August 2022),(Citation: Symantec Bumblebee June 2022),(Citation: Proofpoint Bumblebee April 2022),(Citation: Medium Ali Salem Bumblebee April 2022),(Citation: Google EXOTIC LILY March 2022)
description_zh: [bumblebee]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1039）是用C ++编写的自定义加载程序，已由多个威胁参与者使用，包括可能的初始访问经纪人，以自3月以来下载并执行其他有效负载2022. It has been used since at least 2012 and is usually dropped on victims as second-stage malware, though it has been used as first-stage malware in several cases. It has both Windows and Linux variants. (Citation: FireEye APT28) (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2) (Citation: FireEye APT28 January 2017) (Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018) It is tracked separately from the [X-Agent for Android](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0314).

It is intended for espionage, data exfiltration, and providing remote access to infected machines. (Citation: Kaspersky Carbanak) (Citation: FireEye CARBANAK June 2017)

name: Carbon

[Carbon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0335) has been selectively used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) to target government and foreign affairs-related organizations in Central Asia.(Citation: ESET Carbon Mar 2017)(Citation: Securelist Turla Oct 2018)

It was used to target Japanese organizations in 2016. Its lack of persistence methods suggests it may be intended as a first-stage tool. (Citation: Palo Alto menuPass Feb 2017) (Citation: JPCERT ChChes Feb 2017) (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),,(Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: JPCERT ChChes Feb 2017),(Citation: Palo Alto menuPass Feb 2017),(Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017)

[Chaes](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0631) was first observed in 2020, and appears to primarily target victims in Brazil as well as other e-commerce customers in Latin America.(Citation: Cybereason Chaes Nov 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cybereason Chaes Nov 2020)

name: Cobalt Strike
description:
[Cobalt Strike](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0154) is a commercial, full-featured, remote access tool that bills itself as “adversary simulation software designed to execute targeted attacks and emulate the post-exploitation actions of advanced threat actors”. Cobalt Strike’s interactive post-exploit capabilities cover the full range of ATT&CK tactics, all executed within a single, integrated system.(Citation: cobaltstrike manual)

In addition to its own capabilities, [Cobalt Strike](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0154) leverages the capabilities of other well-known tools such as Metasploit and [Mimikatz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0002).(Citation: cobaltstrike manual)

description_zh:
[Cobalt Strike]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0154）是一种商业，完整的远程访问工具，该工具本身就是“旨在执行目标攻击并仿效后启动行动的对手仿真软件，高级威胁行为者”。 Cobalt Strike的互动后口气功能涵盖了整个ATT＆CK策略，所有功能都在单个集成系统中执行。（引用：CobaltStrike手册）

name: Conti
description: [Conti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0575) is a Ransomware-as-a-Service (RaaS) that was first observed in December 2019. [Conti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0575) has been deployed via [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) and used against major corporations and government agencies, particularly those in North America. As with other ransomware families, actors using [Conti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0575) steal sensitive files and information from compromised networks, and threaten to publish this data unless the ransom is paid.(Citation: Cybereason Conti Jan 2021)(Citation: CarbonBlack Conti July 2020)(Citation: Cybleinc Conti January 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021),(Citation: CarbonBlack Conti July 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: Cybereason Conti Jan 2021),(Citation: Cybleinc Conti January 2020),(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021)
description_zh: [conti]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0575）是2019年12月首次观察到的勒索软件-AS-A-Service（RAAS）。 org/software/s0575）已通过[trickbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0266）部署，并针对主要公司和政府机构，尤其是北美的政府机构。与其他勒索软件家族一样，使用[conti]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0575）的参与者从折衷的网络中窃取敏感文件和信息，并威胁要发布此数据，除非已付款。 Cyber​​eason Conti 2021年1月）（引文：Carbonblack Conti 2020年7月）（引文：Cybleinc Conti 2020年1月）

[DRATzarus](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0694) shares similarities with [Bankshot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0239), which was used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) in 2017 to target the Turkish financial sector.(Citation: ClearSky Lazarus Aug 2020)

name: DarkWatchman

Researchers have identified versions written in both Visual C and Delphi. (Citation: Trend Micro Daserf Nov 2017) (Citation: Secureworks BRONZE BUTLER Oct 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Tick Apr 2016),(Citation: Trend Micro Daserf Nov 2017),,(Citation: Symantec Tick Apr 2016),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE BUTLER Oct 2017),(Citation: Trend Micro Daserf Nov 2017)

[Denis](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0354) shares several similarities to the [SOUNDBITE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0157) backdoor and has been used in conjunction with the [Goopy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0477) backdoor.(Citation: Cybereason Oceanlotus May 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Oceanlotus May 2017),(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017),,(Citation: Cybereason Oceanlotus May 2017),(Citation: Securelist Denis April 2017),(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017)

name: Derusbi
description: [Derusbi](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0021) is malware used by multiple Chinese APT groups.(Citation: Novetta-Axiom)(Citation: ThreatConnect Anthem) Both Windows and Linux variants have been observed.(Citation: Fidelis Turbo)
relationship citations: (Citation: ThreatConnect Anthem),(Citation: Cisco Group 72),(Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),(Citation: Novetta-Axiom),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),,(Citation: ThreatGeek Derusbi Converge),(Citation: Fidelis Turbo),(Citation: Novetta-Axiom),(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),(Citation: Airbus Derusbi 2015)

name: Diavol
description: [Diavol](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0659) is a ransomware variant first observed in June 2021 that is capable of prioritizing file types to encrypt based on a pre-configured list of extensions defined by the attacker. [Diavol](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0659) has been deployed by [Bazar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0534) and is thought to have potential ties to [Wizard Spider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0102).(Citation: Fortinet Diavol July 2021)(Citation: FBI Flash Diavol January 2022)(Citation: DFIR Diavol Ransomware December 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Fortinet Diavol July 2021)
description_zh: [diavol]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0659）是2021年6月首次观察到的勒索软件变体，它能够根据攻击者定义的扩展名列表进行对文件类型的优先级加密。 [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0659）已由[bazar]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0534）部署，并被认为与[Wizard有潜在的联系蜘蛛]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0102）。

name: Dipsind
description: [Dipsind](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0200) is a malware family of backdoors that appear to be used exclusively by [PLATINUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0068). (Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016),,(Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016)

name: DnsSystem
description: [DnsSystem](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1021) is a .NET based DNS backdoor, which is a customized version of the open source tool DIG.net, that has been used by [HEXANE](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1001) since at least June 2022.(Citation: Zscaler Lyceum DnsSystem June 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Zscaler Lyceum DnsSystem June 2022),,(Citation: Zscaler Lyceum DnsSystem June 2022)

name: Dok
description: [Dok](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0281) is a Trojan application disguised as a .zip file that is able to collect user credentials and install a malicious proxy server to redirect a user's network traffic (i.e. [Adversary-in-the-Middle](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1557)).(Citation: objsee mac malware 2017)(Citation: hexed osx.dok analysis 2019)(Citation: CheckPoint Dok)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: objsee mac malware 2017),(Citation: hexed osx.dok analysis 2019),(Citation: CheckPoint Dok)

name: Doki
description: [Doki](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0600) is a backdoor that uses a unique Dogecoin-based Domain Generation Algorithm and was first observed in July 2020. [Doki](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0600) was used in conjunction with the [Ngrok](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0508) Mining Botnet in a campaign that targeted Docker servers in cloud platforms. (Citation: Intezer Doki July 20)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Intezer Doki July 20)

name: Donut
description: [Donut](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0695) is an open source framework used to generate position-independent shellcode.(Citation: Donut Github)(Citation: Introducing Donut) [Donut](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0695) generated code has been used by multiple threat actors to inject and load malicious payloads into memory.(Citation: NCC Group WastedLocker June 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCC Group WastedLocker June 2020),,(Citation: Donut Github)
description_zh: [DONUT]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0695）是一个开源框架，用于生成位置独立的shellcode。（引用：Donut github）（引用：引用：介绍Donut）[Donut）[Donut] [https：/ /attack.mitre.org/software/s0695）生成的代码已被多个威胁参与者使用并将恶意有效载荷注入内存。

name: DownPaper
description: [DownPaper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0186) is a backdoor Trojan; its main functionality is to download and run second stage malware. (Citation: ClearSky Charming Kitten Dec 2017)

name: Downdelph
description: [Downdelph](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0134) is a first-stage downloader written in Delphi that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) in rare instances between 2013 and 2015. (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3),(Citation: Secureworks IRON TWILIGHT Active Measures March 2017),,(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3)
description_zh: [downdelph]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0134）是用Delphi编写的第一阶段下载器，该下载器已由[APT28]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0007）使用。在2013年至2015年之间的极少数情况下。（引文：ESET Sednit第3部分）

name: Dridex
description: [Dridex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0384) is a prolific banking Trojan that first appeared in 2014. By December 2019, the US Treasury estimated [Dridex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0384) had infected computers in hundreds of banks and financial institutions in over 40 countries, leading to more than $100 million in theft. [Dridex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0384) was created from the source code of the Bugat banking Trojan (also known as Cridex).(Citation: Dell Dridex Oct 2015)(Citation: Kaspersky Dridex May 2017)(Citation: Treasury EvilCorp Dec 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Sep 2017),(Citation: Crowdstrike Indrik November 2018),(Citation: IBM TA505 April 2020),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 June 2018),(Citation: Treasury EvilCorp Dec 2019),(Citation: Crowdstrike EvilCorp March 2021),,(Citation: Dell Dridex Oct 2015),(Citation: Checkpoint Dridex Jan 2021),(Citation: Kaspersky Dridex May 2017)
description_zh: [dridex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0384）是一款多产的银行木马，首次出现在2014年。到2019年12月，美国财政部估计[dridex]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org /Software/S0384）在40多个国家/地区的数百家银行和金融机构中感染了计算机，导致盗窃超过1亿美元。 [Dridex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0384）是由Bugat Banking Trojan（也称为Cridex）的源代码创建的。 2017年）（引文：2019年12月的国库Evilcorp）

description: [Drovorub](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0502) is a Linux malware toolset comprised of an agent, client, server, and kernel modules, that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007).(Citation: NSA/FBI Drovorub August 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: NSA/FBI Drovorub August 2020),,(Citation: NSA/FBI Drovorub August 2020)

name: Dtrack
description: [Dtrack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0567) is spyware that was discovered in 2019 and has been used against Indian financial institutions, research facilities, and the Kudankulam Nuclear Power Plant. [Dtrack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0567) shares similarities with the DarkSeoul campaign, which was attributed to [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032). (Citation: Kaspersky Dtrack)(Citation: Securelist Dtrack)(Citation: Dragos WASSONITE)(Citation: CyberBit Dtrack)(Citation: ZDNet Dtrack)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Dtrack),,(Citation: Securelist Dtrack),(Citation: CyberBit Dtrack)
description_zh: [DTRACK]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0567）是在2019年发现的间谍软件，已用于印度金融机构，研究设施和Kudankulam核电站。 [dtrack]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0567）与Darkseoul活动共享相似之处，该活动归因于[Lazarus Group]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0032）。 （引用：卡巴斯基DTRACK）（引用：Securelist Dtrack）（引文：Dragos Wassonite）（引用：Cyber​​bit Dtrack）（引用：ZDNET DTRACK）

name: Dyre
description:
[Dyre](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0024) is a banking Trojan that has been used for financial gain. 
 (Citation: Symantec Dyre June 2015)(Citation: Malwarebytes Dyreza November 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider March 2019),(Citation: Malwarebytes TrickBot Sep 2019),(Citation: Forbes Dyre May 2017),,(Citation: Symantec Dyre June 2015),(Citation: Malwarebytes Dyreza November 2015)

[dyre]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0024）是一种用于经济收益的银行特洛伊木马。
 （引文：Symantec Dyre 2015年6月）（引文：Malwarebytes Dyreza 2015年11月）

name: ECCENTRICBANDWAGON
description: [ECCENTRICBANDWAGON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0593) is a remote access Trojan (RAT) used by North Korean cyber actors that was first identified in August 2020. It is a reconnaissance tool--with keylogging and screen capture functionality--used for information gathering on compromised systems.(Citation: CISA EB Aug 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CISA EB Aug 2020),(Citation: CISA AA20-239A BeagleBoyz August 2020),,(Citation: CISA EB Aug 2020)
description_zh: [Eccentricbandwagon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0593）是朝鲜网络参与者使用的远程访问trojan（老鼠），该木马是2020年8月首次确定的。屏幕捕获功能 - 用于妥协系统的信息收集。（引文：CISA EB 2020年8月）

name: EKANS
description: [EKANS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0605) is ransomware variant written in Golang that first appeared in mid-December 2019 and has been used against multiple sectors, including energy, healthcare, and automotive manufacturing, which in some cases resulted in significant operational disruptions. [EKANS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0605) has used a hard-coded kill-list of processes, including some associated with common ICS software platforms (e.g., GE Proficy, Honeywell HMIWeb, etc), similar to those defined in [MegaCortex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0576).(Citation: Dragos EKANS)(Citation: Palo Alto Unit 42 EKANS)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: IBM Ransomware Trends September 2020),(Citation: Dragos EKANS),(Citation: FireEye Ransomware Feb 2020),(Citation: Palo Alto Unit 42 EKANS)
description_zh: [ekans]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0605）是用Golang编写的勒索软件变体，该变体首次出现在2019年12月中旬，并已针对多个领域，包括能源，医疗保健和自动制造业，该部门在某些情况下，导致了严重的操作中断。 [ekans]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0605）使用了硬编码的流程，包括与常见ICS软件平台相关的一些（例如Ge Proficy，Honeywell Hmiweb等），类似于[Megacortex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0576）中定义的。

name: ELMER
description: [ELMER](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0064) is a non-persistent, proxy-aware HTTP backdoor written in Delphi that has been used by [APT16](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0023). (Citation: FireEye EPS Awakens Part 2)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye EPS Awakens Part 2),,(Citation: FireEye EPS Awakens Part 2)
description_zh: [Elmer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0064）是一种非抗抗抑素，代理-AwAw-waw http backdoor用delphi编写，已由[apt16]使用（https：//attack.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.metre.org. /组/G0023）。 （引文：FireEye EPS觉醒第2部分）

name: EVILNUM
description: [EVILNUM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0568) is fully capable backdoor that was first identified in 2018. [EVILNUM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0568) is used by the APT group [Evilnum](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0120) which has the same name.(Citation: ESET EvilNum July 2020)(Citation: Prevailion EvilNum May 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Prevailion EvilNum May 2020),,(Citation: ESET EvilNum July 2020),(Citation: Prevailion EvilNum May 2020)

name: Ebury
description: [Ebury](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0377) is an SSH backdoor targeting Linux operating systems. Attackers require root-level access, which allows them to replace SSH binaries (ssh, sshd, ssh-add, etc) or modify a shared library used by OpenSSH (libkeyutils).(Citation: ESET Ebury Feb 2014)(Citation: BleepingComputer Ebury March 2017)(Citation: ESET Ebury Oct 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Ebury Oct 2017),,(Citation: ESET Ebury Feb 2014),(Citation: ESET Windigo Mar 2014),(Citation: ESET Ebury Oct 2017)
description_zh: [ebury]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0377）是SSH后门目标Linux操作系统。攻击者需要根级访问权限，这使他们可以替换SSH二进制文件（SSH，SSHD，SSH-ADD等）或修改Openssh（libkeyutils）使用的共享库。 2017年3月）（引文：Eset Ebury 2017年10月）

name: Ecipekac
description: [Ecipekac](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0624) is a multi-layer loader that has been used by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045) since at least 2019 including use as a loader for [P8RAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0626), [SodaMaster](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0627), and [FYAnti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0628).(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021),,(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)

name: Egregor
description: [Egregor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0554) is a Ransomware-as-a-Service (RaaS) tool that was first observed in September 2020. Researchers have noted code similarities between [Egregor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0554) and Sekhmet ransomware, as well as [Maze](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0449) ransomware.(Citation: NHS Digital Egregor Nov 2020)(Citation: Cyble Egregor Oct 2020)(Citation: Security Boulevard Egregor Oct 2020)
contributors: Daniyal Naeem, BT Security; Matt Brenton, Zurich Insurance Group
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: JoeSecurity Egregor 2020),(Citation: Intrinsec Egregor Nov 2020),(Citation: NHS Digital Egregor Nov 2020),(Citation: Cybereason Egregor Nov 2020),(Citation: Cyble Egregor Oct 2020)
description_zh: [Egregor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0554）是2020年9月首次观察到的勒索软件-AS-A-Service（RAAS）工具。 ：//attack.mitre.org/software/s0554）和sekhmet lansomware，以及[maze]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0449）兰索软件。引用：隔离埃格雷戈（Cyble Egregor）2020年10月）（引文：安全林荫大道Egregor 2020年10月）

name: Elise
description:
[Elise](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0081) is a custom backdoor Trojan that appears to be used exclusively by [Lotus Blossom](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0030). It is part of a larger group of
tools referred to as LStudio, ST Group, and APT0LSTU. (Citation: Lotus Blossom Jun 2015)(Citation: Accenture Dragonfish Jan 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Accenture Dragonfish Jan 2018),(Citation: Spring Dragon Jun 2015),,(Citation: Accenture Dragonfish Jan 2018),(Citation: Lotus Blossom Jun 2015)
description_zh:
[Elise]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0081）是一种自定义的后门特洛伊木马，似乎由[Lotus Blossom]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org.org/groups/groups/g0030）独家使用。它是较大群体的一部分
工具称为lstudio，st Group和apt0lstu。 （引文：Lotus Blossom 2015年6月）（引文：埃森哲龙鱼2018年1月）

name: Emissary
description: [Emissary](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0082) is a Trojan that has been used by [Lotus Blossom](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0030). It shares code with [Elise](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0081), with both Trojans being part of a malware group referred to as LStudio. (Citation: Lotus Blossom Dec 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: Lotus Blossom Dec 2015),(Citation: Emissary Trojan Feb 2016),,(Citation: Lotus Blossom Dec 2015),(Citation: Emissary Trojan Feb 2016)
description_zh: [Emissary]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0082）是[lotus blossom]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0030）已使用的木马。它与[Elise]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0081）共享代码，两个特洛伊人都是恶意软件组的一部分，称为lstudio。 （引文：Lotus Blossom 2015年12月）

name: Emotet
description: [Emotet](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0367) is a modular malware variant which is primarily used as a downloader for other malware variants such as [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) and [IcedID](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0483). Emotet first emerged in June 2014 and has been primarily used to target the banking sector. (Citation: Trend Micro Banking Malware Jan 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Sophos New Ryuk Attack October 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Grim Spider May 2019),,(Citation: Talos Emotet Jan 2019),(Citation: CIS Emotet Apr 2017),(Citation: Fortinet Emotet May 2017),(Citation: Red Canary Emotet Feb 2019),(Citation: ASEC Emotet 2017),(Citation: Trend Micro Emotet Jan 2019),(Citation: Kaspersky Emotet Jan 2019),(Citation: Picus Emotet Dec 2018),(Citation: Malwarebytes Emotet Dec 2017),(Citation: US-CERT Emotet Jul 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro Banking Malware Jan 2019),(Citation: ESET Emotet Dec 2018),(Citation: CIS Emotet Dec 2018),(Citation: Secureworks Emotet Nov 2018),(Citation: Symantec Emotet Jul 2018),(Citation: IBM IcedID November 2017),(Citation: Carbon Black Emotet Apr 2019)
description_zh: [emotet]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0367）是一个模块化恶意软件变体，主要用作其他恶意软件变体的下载器，例如[trickbot]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.orgg/软件/S0266）和[ICEDID]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0483）。 Emotet于2014年6月首次出现，主要用于针对银行业。 （引文：趋势微银行恶意软件2019年1月）

name: Empire
description: [Empire](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0363) is an open source, cross-platform remote administration and post-exploitation framework that is publicly available on GitHub. While the tool itself is primarily written in Python, the post-exploitation agents are written in pure [PowerShell](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001) for Windows and Python for Linux/macOS. [Empire](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0363) was one of five tools singled out by a joint report on public hacking tools being widely used by adversaries.(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools)(Citation: Github PowerShell Empire)(Citation: GitHub ATTACK Empire)
relationship citations: (Citation: SecureWorks August 2019),(Citation: Crowdstrike Indrik November 2018),(Citation: Group IB Silence Aug 2019),(Citation: DHS/CISA Ransomware Targeting Healthcare October 2020),(Citation: ESET Crutch December 2020),(Citation: Lab52 WIRTE Apr 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017),(Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020),(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),(Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),(Citation: ESET Turla August 2018),(Citation: CrowdStrike Grim Spider May 2019),(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),(Citation: FireEye KEGTAP SINGLEMALT October 2020),(Citation: FireEye FIN10 June 2017),(Citation: Talos Frankenstein June 2019),(Citation: GitHub Inveigh),(Citation: SecureWorks August 2019),(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools),(Citation: Github PowerShell Empire),(Citation: Talos Frankenstein June 2019)
description_zh: [Empire]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0363）是GitHub上公开可用的开源，跨平台远程管理和后口气框架。虽然该工具本身主要用Python编写，但后开发代理以纯[PowerShell]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/techniques/t1059/001）编写，用于Linux/MacOS。 [Empire]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0363）是一份关于对手广泛使用公共黑客工具的联合报告所挑选的五种工具之一（引用：NCSC联合报告公共工具）（引文）（引文）（引文）（引用） ：Github Powershell Empire）（引文：Github Attack Empire）

name: EnvyScout
description: [EnvyScout](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0634) is a dropper that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2021.(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),,(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)

name: Epic
description: [Epic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0091) is a backdoor that has been used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010). (Citation: Kaspersky Turla)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: Secureworks IRON HUNTER Profile),,(Citation: ESET Recon Snake Nest),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla Aug 2014)
description_zh: [epic]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0091）是[turla]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010）使用的后门。 （引文：卡巴斯基·图拉（Kaspersky Turla））

name: EvilBunny
description: [EvilBunny](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0396) is a C++ malware sample observed since 2011 that was designed to be a execution platform for Lua scripts.(Citation: Cyphort EvilBunny Dec 2014)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cyphort EvilBunny Dec 2014)

name: EvilGrab
description: [EvilGrab](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0152) is a malware family with common reconnaissance capabilities. It has been deployed by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045) via malicious Microsoft Office documents as part of spearphishing campaigns. (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),,(Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017)
description_zh: [evilgrab]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0152）是具有常见侦察能力的恶意软件。它是由[Menupass]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0045）通过恶意的Microsoft Office文档作为SpearPheShist活动的一部分而部署的。 （引文：PWC云料斗技术附件2017年4月）

name: Exaramel for Linux
description: [Exaramel for Linux](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0401) is a backdoor written in the Go Programming Language and compiled as a 64-bit ELF binary. The Windows version is tracked separately under [Exaramel for Windows](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0343).(Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: ANSSI Sandworm January 2021),(Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018),,(Citation: ANSSI Sandworm January 2021),(Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018)
description_zh: [exaramel for Linux]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0401）是用GO编程语言编写的后门，并作为64位精灵二进制编译。 Windows版本在[Windows的Exaramel]下单独跟踪（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0343）。（引用：Eset Telebots 2018年10月）

name: Exaramel for Windows
description: [Exaramel for Windows](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0343) is a backdoor used for targeting Windows systems. The Linux version is tracked separately under [Exaramel for Linux](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0401).(Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018),,(Citation: ESET TeleBots Oct 2018)
description_zh: [Windows的Exaramel]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0343）是用于定位Windows系统的后门。 Linux版本分别在[exaramel for Linux]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0401）下进行跟踪。（引用：Eset Telebots 2018年10月）

name: Expand
description: [Expand](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0361) is a Windows utility used to expand one or more compressed CAB files.(Citation: Microsoft Expand Utility) It has been used by [BBSRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0127) to decompress a CAB file into executable content.(Citation: Palo Alto Networks BBSRAT)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Microsoft Expand Utility),(Citation: LOLBAS Expand)
description_zh: [Expand]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0361）是一个Windows实用程序，用于扩展一个或多个压缩的CAB文件。（引用：Microsoft Expand Utility）已由[BBSRAT]（https]（https：https：https： //attack.mitre.org/software/s0127）将CAB文件解压缩到可执行内容中。（引用：Palo Alto Networks bbsrat）

name: Explosive
description: [Explosive](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0569) is a custom-made remote access tool used by the group [Volatile Cedar](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0123). It was first identified in the wild in 2015.(Citation: CheckPoint Volatile Cedar March 2015)(Citation: ClearSky Lebanese Cedar Jan 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: ClearSky Lebanese Cedar Jan 2021),(Citation: CheckPoint Volatile Cedar March 2015),,(Citation: ClearSky Lebanese Cedar Jan 2021),(Citation: CheckPoint Volatile Cedar March 2015)
description_zh: [炸药]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0569）是由[volatile cedar]使用的定制远程访问工具（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0123）。它于2015年在野外首次确定。

name: FALLCHILL
description: [FALLCHILL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0181) is a RAT that has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) since at least 2016 to target the aerospace, telecommunications, and finance industries. It is usually dropped by other [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) malware or delivered when a victim unknowingly visits a compromised website. (Citation: US-CERT FALLCHILL Nov 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT FALLCHILL Nov 2017),,(Citation: US-CERT FALLCHILL Nov 2017),(Citation: CISA AppleJeus Feb 2021)
description_zh: [FallChill]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0181）是[Lazarus Group]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0032）已使用的老鼠针对航空航天，电信和金融行业。通常由其他[Lazarus Group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0032）删除，或者当受害者在不知不觉中访问受害的网站时交付。 （引文：2017年11月11月的美国居民瀑布）

name: FELIXROOT
description: [FELIXROOT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0267) is a backdoor that has been used to target Ukrainian victims. (Citation: FireEye FELIXROOT July 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET GreyEnergy Oct 2018),(Citation: FireEye FELIXROOT July 2018)
description_zh: [felixroot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0267）是用于针对乌克兰受害者的后门。 （引文：Fireeye Felixroot 2018年7月）

name: FIVEHANDS
description: [FIVEHANDS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0618) is a customized version of [DEATHRANSOM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0616) ransomware written in C++. [FIVEHANDS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0618) has been used since at least 2021, including in Ransomware-as-a-Service (RaaS) campaigns, sometimes along with [SombRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0615).(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)(Citation: NCC Group Fivehands June 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: NCC Group Fivehands June 2021),(Citation: CISA AR21-126A FIVEHANDS May 2021),(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)
description_zh: [fixhands]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0618）是[Deatherransom]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0616）的自定义版本。 [五人]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0618）至少从2021年开始使用，包括在Ransomware-as-a-Service（RAAS）广告系列中，有时以及[sombrat]（https：/ /Attack.mitre.org/software/s0615)。（Citation：FireEye 5hands 2021年4月）（引用：NCC Group 5hands 2021年6月）

name: FLASHFLOOD
description: [FLASHFLOOD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0036) is malware developed by [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) that allows propagation and exfiltration of data over removable devices. [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) may use this capability to exfiltrate data across air-gaps. (Citation: FireEye APT30)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT30),,(Citation: FireEye APT30)
description_zh: [flashflood]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0036）是[APT30]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0013）开发的恶意软件。 [apt30]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0013）可以使用此功能在气隙上驱除数据。 （引文：FireEye APT30）

name: FLIPSIDE
description: [FLIPSIDE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0173) is a simple tool similar to Plink that is used by [FIN5](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0053) to maintain access to victims. (Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016),,(Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016)
description_zh: [flipside]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0173）是一个简单的工具给受害者。 （引用：Mandiant Fin5 GRRCON 2016年10月）

name: FYAnti

relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021),,(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)

relationship citations: (Citation: Scarlet Mimic Jan 2016),,(Citation: Scarlet Mimic Jan 2016)

name: FatDuke

relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),,(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)

name: FinFisher
description: [FinFisher](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0182) is a government-grade commercial surveillance spyware reportedly sold exclusively to government agencies for use in targeted and lawful criminal investigations. It is heavily obfuscated and uses multiple anti-analysis techniques. It has other variants including [Wingbird](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0176). (Citation: FinFisher Citation) (Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 21) (Citation: FireEye FinSpy Sept 2017) (Citation: Securelist BlackOasis Oct 2017) (Citation: Microsoft FinFisher March 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Lookout Dark Caracal Jan 2018),,(Citation: Securelist BlackOasis Oct 2017),(Citation: FinFisher Citation),(Citation: FinFisher exposed ),(Citation: Microsoft FinFisher March 2018),(Citation: Elastic Process Injection July 2017)
description_zh: [Finfisher]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0182）是政府级的商业监视间谍软件，据报道专门出售给政府机构，用于有针对性和合法的刑事调查。它被严重混淆，并使用了多种抗分析技术。它还有其他变体，包括[wingbird]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0176）。 （引文：Finfisher引用）（引文：Microsoft Sir Vol 21）（引文：Fireeye Finspy 2017年9月）（引文：Securelist Blackoasis 2017年10月）（引用：Microsoft Finfisher 2018年3月）

relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Nokki Oct 2018),,(Citation: Unit 42 Nokki Oct 2018)

It has primarily been used against defense, media, and communications companies in Japan.(Citation: NTT Security Flagpro new December 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: NTT Security Flagpro new December 2021),,(Citation: NTT Security Flagpro new December 2021)
