The code for [FlawedAmmyy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0381) was based on leaked source code for a version of Ammyy Admin, a remote access software.(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Mar 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Mar 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro TA505 June 2019),(Citation: Visa FIN6 Feb 2019),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019),,(Citation: Korean FSI TA505 2020),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Mar 2018)
description_zh: [flawedammyy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0381）是一种远程访问工具（RAT），首次在2016年初出现。 /software/s0381）基于泄漏的源代码，用于远程访问软件Ammyy Admin的版本。

name: FlawedGrace
description: [FlawedGrace](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0383) is a fully featured remote access tool (RAT) written in C++ that was first observed in late 2017.(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro TA505 June 2019),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019),,(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019)
description_zh: [flawedgrace]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0383）是一款完整的特色远程访问工具（RAT），该工具（RAT）在2017年底首次观察到。

name: FoggyWeb
description: [FoggyWeb](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0661) is a passive and highly-targeted backdoor capable of remotely exfiltrating sensitive information from a compromised Active Directory Federated Services (AD FS) server. It has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least early April 2021.(Citation: MSTIC FoggyWeb September 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC FoggyWeb September 2021),,(Citation: MSTIC FoggyWeb September 2021)
description_zh: [foggyweb]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0661）是一种被动且高度定位的后门，能够从受损的Active Directory FiveDeratory联合服务（AD FS）服务器中远程删除敏感信息。自2021年4月上旬以来，[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）已使用它。

name: Forfiles
description: [Forfiles](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0193) is a Windows utility commonly used in batch jobs to execute commands on one or more selected files or directories (ex: list all directories in a drive, read the first line of all files created yesterday, etc.). Forfiles can be executed from either the command line, Run window, or batch files/scripts. (Citation: Microsoft Forfiles Aug 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Überwachung APT28 Forfiles June 2015),,(Citation: Überwachung APT28 Forfiles June 2015),(Citation: VectorSec ForFiles Aug 2017),(Citation: Evi1cg Forfiles Nov 2017)
description_zh: [forfiles]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0193）是批处理作业中常用的Windows实用程序，用于在一个或多个选择的文件或目录上执行命令（ex：ex：在驱动器中列出所有目录，请阅读昨天创建的所有文件的第一行，等等）。可以从命令行，运行窗口或批处理文件/脚本执行Forfiles。 （引文：Microsoft Forfiles 2016年8月）

name: FrameworkPOS
description: [FrameworkPOS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0503) is a point of sale (POS) malware used by [FIN6](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0037) to steal payment card data from sytems that run physical POS devices.(Citation: SentinelOne FrameworkPOS September 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Crowdstrike Global Threat Report Feb 2018),(Citation: SentinelOne FrameworkPOS September 2019),(Citation: Visa FIN6 Feb 2019),,(Citation: SentinelOne FrameworkPOS September 2019),(Citation: FireEye FIN6 April 2016)
description_zh: [frameworkpos]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0503）是销售点（POS）[FIN6]使用的恶意软件（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0037）来自运行物理POS设备的系统的卡数据。（引文：Sentinelone Frameworkpos 2019年9月）

name: FruitFly
description: FruitFly is designed to spy on mac users  (Citation: objsee mac malware 2017).
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: objsee mac malware 2017)
description_zh: Fruitfly旨在监视Mac用户（引文：OBJSEE MAC恶意软件2017）。

name: FunnyDream
description: [FunnyDream](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1044) is a backdoor with multiple components that was used during the [FunnyDream](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0007) campaign since at least 2019, primarily for execution and exfiltration.(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020),(Citation: Kaspersky APT Trends Q1 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020)
description_zh: [funnydream]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1044）是一个后门至少2019年，主要用于执行和渗透。

name: Fysbis
description: [Fysbis](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0410) is a Linux-based backdoor used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) that dates back to at least 2014.(Citation: Fysbis Palo Alto Analysis)
relationship citations: (Citation: Fysbis Palo Alto Analysis),,(Citation: Fysbis Palo Alto Analysis),(Citation: Fysbis Dr Web Analysis)
description_zh: [FYSBIS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0410）是[apt28]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0007）使用的基于Linux的后端，至少可以追溯到2014年。（引文：Fysbis Palo Alto分析）

name: GLOOXMAIL
description: [GLOOXMAIL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0026) is malware used by [APT1](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0006) that mimics legitimate Jabber/XMPP traffic. (Citation: Mandiant APT1)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1),,(Citation: Mandiant APT1),(Citation: CyberESI GTALK)
description_zh: [GlooxMail]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0026）是[APT1]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0006）使用的恶意软件。 （引用：Mandiant APT1）

name: GRIFFON
description: [GRIFFON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0417) is a JavaScript backdoor used by [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046). (Citation: SecureList Griffon May 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: FBI Flash FIN7 USB),(Citation: CrowdStrike Carbon Spider August 2021),(Citation: SecureList Griffon May 2019),,(Citation: SecureList Griffon May 2019)
description_zh: [griffon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0417）是[Fin7]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0046）使用的JavaScript Backdoor。 （引文：Securelist Griffon 2019年5月）

name: Gazer
description: [Gazer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0168) is a backdoor used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) since at least 2016. (Citation: ESET Gazer Aug 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Gazer Aug 2017),,(Citation: ESET Gazer Aug 2017),(Citation: Securelist WhiteBear Aug 2017)
description_zh: [gazer]（https：//attack.mitre.org/software/s0168）是[turla]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010）使用的后门。 Gazer 2017年8月）

name: Gelsemium
description: [Gelsemium](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0666) is a modular malware comprised of a dropper (Gelsemine), a loader (Gelsenicine), and main (Gelsevirine) plug-ins written using the Microsoft Foundation Class (MFC) framework. [Gelsemium](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0666) has been used by the Gelsemium group since at least 2014.(Citation: ESET Gelsemium June 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Gelsemium June 2021)
description_zh: [gelemium]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0666）是一种模块化恶意软件，由滴管（gelsemine），装载机（gelsenicine）和main（gelsevirine）使用Microsoft Foundation Class编写（MFC）框架。 [gelemium]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0666）至少从2014年开始使用Gelsemium Group。（引用：2021年6月Eset Gelsemium）

name: GeminiDuke
description: [GeminiDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0049) is malware that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) from 2009 to 2012. (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
relationship citations: (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),,(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0049）是[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的恶意软件，2009年至2012年。 F-Secure公爵）

name: Get2
description: [Get2](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0460) is a downloader written in C++ that has been used by [TA505](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0092) to deliver [FlawedGrace](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0383), [FlawedAmmyy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0381), Snatch and [SDBbot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0461).(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019),,(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019)
description_zh: [get2]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0460）是用C ++写的下载器，该下载器已由[TA505]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0092）使用，以交付[ flawedgrace]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0383），[flawedammyy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0381），snatch and Snatch and [sdbbot]（sdbbot] .org/Software/s0461）。

name: Gold Dragon
description: [Gold Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0249) is a Korean-language, data gathering implant that was first observed in the wild in South Korea in July 2017. [Gold Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0249) was used along with [Brave Prince](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0252) and [RunningRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0253) in operations targeting organizations associated with the 2018 Pyeongchang Winter Olympics. (Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
relationship citations: (Citation: Talos Kimsuky Nov 2021),,(Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
description_zh: [Gold Dragon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0249）是韩国语言，数据收集植入物，于2017年7月在韩国的野外最初观察到。[Gold Dragon]（https：//与[Brave Prince]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0252）一起使用/attack.mitre.org/software/S0249）和[brave prince]和[runningrat]（httpspps://attack.mitarak.mitre.orgg/softwareware） /S0253）针对与2018年平昌冬季奥运会相关的组织的运营。 （引文：McAfee Gold Dragon）

name: GoldFinder
description: [GoldFinder](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0597) is a custom HTTP tracer tool written in Go that logs the route a packet takes between a compromised network and a C2 server. It can be used to inform  threat actors of potential points of discovery or logging of their actions, including C2 related to other malware. [GoldFinder](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0597) was discovered in early 2021 during an investigation into the SolarWinds cyber intrusion by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016).(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021),(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),(Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),,(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)
description_zh: [GoldFinder]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0597）是用GO编写的自定义HTTP示踪工具，该工具记录了数据包在受损网络和C2服务器之间使用的路由。它可以用来告知威胁行为者的潜在发现或记录其行为的可能性，包括与其他恶意软件相关的C2。 [Goldfinder]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0597）在2021年初在调查[APTP29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0016）的调查中发现了Solarwinds网络入侵的过程中。 。（引文：Mstic Nobelium 2021年3月）

name: GoldMax
description: [GoldMax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0588) is a second-stage C2 backdoor written in Go with Windows and Linux variants that are nearly identical in functionality. [GoldMax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0588) was discovered in early 2021 during the investigation into the SolarWinds intrusion, and has likely been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least mid-2019. [GoldMax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0588) uses multiple defense evasion techniques, including avoiding virtualization execution and masking malicious traffic.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)(Citation: FireEye SUNSHUTTLE Mar 2021)(Citation: CrowdStrike StellarParticle January 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM May 2021),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021),,(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021),(Citation: FireEye SUNSHUTTLE Mar 2021),(Citation: CrowdStrike StellarParticle January 2022)
description_zh: [Goldmax]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0588）是第二阶段的C2后门，用Windows和Linux变体编写，其功能几乎相同。 [Goldmax]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0588）在2021年初在调查SolarWinds入侵的过程中发现了[apt29]（https://attack.metre.metre.org.mitre.org.org.metre.org.org.metre.org.org.metre.org.org.metre.org.org.org.org.org.org.org-metrre.metre.org.org- /组/G0016）至少从2019年中期开始。 [Goldmax]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0588）使用多种防御逃避技术，包括避免进行虚拟化执行和掩盖恶意交通。引用：众颗恒星粒子2022年1月）

name: GoldenSpy
description: [GoldenSpy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0493) is a backdoor malware which has been packaged with legitimate tax preparation software. [GoldenSpy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0493) was discovered targeting organizations in China, being delivered with the "Intelligent Tax" software suite which is produced by the Golden Tax Department of Aisino Credit Information Co. and required to pay local taxes.(Citation: Trustwave GoldenSpy June 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Trustwave GoldenSpy June 2020),(Citation: Trustwave GoldenSpy2 June 2020)
description_zh: [Goldenspy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0493）是一种后门恶意软件，已包装有合法的税收准备软件。 [Goldenspy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0493）被发现针对中国的针对组织，并使用了由Aisino Credit Information Co.和Golden税务部门生产的“智能税收”软件套件交付要求缴纳当地税。（引文：Trustwave Goldenspy 2020年6月）

name: Goopy
description: [Goopy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0477) is a Windows backdoor and Trojan used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050) and shares several similarities to another backdoor used by the group ([Denis](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0354)). [Goopy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0477) is named for its impersonation of the legitimate Google Updater executable.(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017),,(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017)
description_zh: [goopopy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0477）是Windows Backdoor和[apt32]使用的Trojan（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0050），并与另一个相似之处小组使用的后门（[denis]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0354））。 [goopopy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0477）以其对合法的Google Updater的可执行文件而命名。（引用：Cyber​​eason Cobalt Kitty 2017）

name: Grandoreiro
description: [Grandoreiro](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0531) is a banking trojan written in Delphi that was first observed in 2016 and uses a Malware-as-a-Service (MaaS) business model. [Grandoreiro](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0531) has confirmed victims in Brazil, Mexico, Portugal, and Spain.(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)(Citation: ESET Grandoreiro April 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020),(Citation: IBM Grandoreiro April 2020),(Citation: ESET Grandoreiro April 2020)
description_zh: [Grandoreiro]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0531）是一家用Delphi撰写的银行木马，最初于2016年观察到，并使用了恶意软件-AS-AS-AS-Service（MAAS）商业模型。 [Grandoreiro]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0531）已确认在巴西，墨西哥，葡萄牙和西班牙的受害者。

name: GravityRAT
description: [GravityRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0237) is a remote access tool (RAT) and has been in ongoing development since 2016. The actor behind the tool remains unknown, but two usernames have been recovered that link to the author, which are "TheMartian" and "The Invincible." According to the National Computer Emergency Response Team (CERT) of India, the malware has been identified in attacks against organization and entities in India. (Citation: Talos GravityRAT)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Talos GravityRAT)
description_zh: [GRAVITYRAT]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0237）是一种远程访问工具（RAT），自2016年以来一直在进行中。该工具背后的演员仍然未知，但是已经恢复了两个用户名链接到作者，这是“ themartian”和“无敌”。根据印度国家计算机紧急响应小组（CERT）的数据，该恶意软件已在针对印度的组织和实体的攻击中被发现。 （引文：Talos Gravityrat）

name: Green Lambert
description: [Green Lambert](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0690) is a modular backdoor that security researchers assess has been used by an advanced threat group referred to as Longhorn and The Lamberts. First reported in 2017, the Windows variant of [Green Lambert](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0690) may have been used as early as 2008; a macOS version was uploaded to a multiscanner service in September 2014.(Citation: Kaspersky Lamberts Toolkit April 2017)(Citation: Objective See Green Lambert for OSX Oct 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Objective See Green Lambert for OSX Oct 2021),(Citation: Glitch-Cat Green Lambert ATTCK Oct 2021)
description_zh: [Green Lambert]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0690）是一个模块化的后门，安全研究人员评估已被称为Longhorn和Lamberts的高级威胁组使用。 [Green Lambert]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0690）的Windows变体首次报道，最早可能早在2008年就被使用。 MACOS版本于2014年9月上传到Multiscanner服务。

name: GreyEnergy
description: [GreyEnergy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0342) is a backdoor written in C and compiled in Visual Studio. [GreyEnergy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0342) shares similarities with the [BlackEnergy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0089) malware and is thought to be the successor of it.(Citation: ESET GreyEnergy Oct 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: ESET GreyEnergy Oct 2018)
description_zh: [Greyenergy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0342）是用C编写并在Visual Studio中编译的后门。 [GREYERGY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0342）与[BlackEnergy]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/s0089）共享相似之处，被认为是它的继任者。（引文：Eset Greyenergy 2018年10月）

name: GrimAgent
description: [GrimAgent](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0632) is a backdoor that has been used before the deployment of [Ryuk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0446) ransomware since at least 2020; it is likely used by [FIN6](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0037) and [Wizard Spider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0102).(Citation: Group IB GrimAgent July 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Group IB GrimAgent July 2021),,(Citation: Group IB GrimAgent July 2021)
description_zh: [grimagent]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0632）是一个后门，在部署[ryuk]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0446）至少2020；它可能由[Fin6]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0037）和[Wizard Spider]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0102）使用。 2021年7月）

name: GuLoader
description: [GuLoader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0561) is a file downloader that has been used since at least December 2019 to distribute a variety of remote administration tool (RAT) malware, including [NETWIRE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0198), [Agent Tesla](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0331), [NanoCore](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0336), FormBook, and Parallax RAT.(Citation: Unit 42 NETWIRE April 2020)(Citation: Medium Eli Salem GuLoader April 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit 42 NETWIRE April 2020),(Citation: Medium Eli Salem GuLoader April 2021)
description_zh: [guloader]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0561）是一个文件下载器，至少自2019年12月以来一直在使用各种远程管理工具（Rat）恶意软件，包括[NetWire]（htttps）（htttps） ：//attack.mitre.org/software/s0198），[agent tesla]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0331），[nanocore]（httpspps://attack.mitack.mitre.or.orgg/software/ S0336），FormBook和Alallax Rat。（引文：42 Netwire 2020年4月）（引文：中等ELI SALEM GULOADER 2021年4月）

name: H1N1
description: [H1N1](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0132) is a malware variant that has been distributed via a campaign using VBA macros to infect victims. Although it initially had only loader capabilities, it has evolved to include information-stealing functionality. (Citation: Cisco H1N1 Part 1)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cisco H1N1 Part 1),(Citation: Cisco H1N1 Part 2)
description_zh: [H1N1]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0132）是一种恶意软件变体，已通过使用VBA宏来传播以感染受害者的广告系列。尽管它最初仅具有加载器功能，但它已经演变为包括信息偷窃功能。 （引文：思科H1N1第1部分）

name: HALFBAKED
description: [HALFBAKED](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0151) is a malware family consisting of multiple components intended to establish persistence in victim networks. (Citation: FireEye FIN7 April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN7 April 2017),(Citation: FireEye FIN7 Aug 2018),,(Citation: FireEye FIN7 April 2017)
description_zh: [halfbaked]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0151）是一个恶意软件家族，由多个旨在在受害者网络中建立持久性的组件组成。 （引文：FireEye Fin7 2017年4月）

name: HAMMERTOSS
description: [HAMMERTOSS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0037) is a backdoor that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) in 2015. (Citation: FireEye APT29) (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),,(Citation: FireEye APT29)
description_zh: [Hammertoss]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0037）是[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的后门，2015年。 APT29）（引用：f-Secure the dukes）

name: HAPPYWORK
description: [HAPPYWORK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0214) is a downloader used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067) to target South Korean government and financial victims in November 2016. (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018),,(Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0214）是[APT37]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）使用的下载器2016年11月。（引文：FireEye APT37 2018年2月）

name: HARDRAIN
description: [HARDRAIN](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0246) is a Trojan malware variant reportedly used by the North Korean government. (Citation: US-CERT HARDRAIN March 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT HARDRAIN March 2018),,(Citation: US-CERT HARDRAIN March 2018)
description_zh: [Hardrain]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0246）是据报道，据报道是朝鲜政府使用的木马恶意软件。 （引文：美国 - 塞特·哈德林2018年3月）

name: HAWKBALL
description: [HAWKBALL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0391) is a backdoor that was observed in targeting of the government sector in Central Asia.(Citation: FireEye HAWKBALL Jun 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FireEye HAWKBALL Jun 2019)
description_zh: [Hawkball]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0391）是一个后门，在中亚政府部门的目标中观察到。（引用：Fireeye Hawkball 2019年6月）

name: HDoor
description: [HDoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0061) is malware that has been customized and used by the [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019) group. (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),,(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015)
description_zh: [hdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0061）是恶意软件，已由[Naikon]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0019）组定制和使用。 （引文：Baumgartner Naikon 2015）

name: HELLOKITTY
description: [HELLOKITTY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0617) is a ransomware written in C++  that shares similar code structure and functionality with [DEATHRANSOM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0616) and [FIVEHANDS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0618). [HELLOKITTY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0617) has been used since at least 2020, targets have included a Polish video game developer and a Brazilian electric power company.(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)
description_zh: [hellokitty]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0617）是用C ++编写的勒索软件，与[deatherransom]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/softre.org/software/s0616）共享类似的代码结构和功能和[五人]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0618）。 [Hellokitty]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0617）至少从2020年开始使用，目标包括波兰视频游戏开发人员和一家巴西电力公司。

name: HIDEDRV
description: [HIDEDRV](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0135) is a rootkit used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007). It has been deployed along with [Downdelph](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0134) to execute and hide that malware. (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3) (Citation: Sekoia HideDRV Oct 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3),,(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3)
description_zh: [Hidedrv]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0135）是[apt28]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0007）使用的rootkit。它已与[Downdelph]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0134）一起部署，以执行和隐藏该恶意软件。 （引用：ESET SEDNIT第3部分）（引文：Sekoia Hidedrv 2016年10月）

name: HOMEFRY
description: [HOMEFRY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0232) is a 64-bit Windows password dumper/cracker that has previously been used in conjunction with other [Leviathan](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0065) backdoors. (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),,(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)
description_zh: [homefry]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0232）是一个64-bit Windows密码dumper/cracker，以前与其他[leviathan]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.mitre.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.mitre.org.org /组/G0065）后门。 （引文：2018年3月FireEye Periscope）

name: HOPLIGHT
description: [HOPLIGHT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0376) is a backdoor Trojan that has reportedly been used by the North Korean government.(Citation: US-CERT HOPLIGHT Apr 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT HOPLIGHT Apr 2019),(Citation: CISA AA20-239A BeagleBoyz August 2020),,(Citation: US-CERT HOPLIGHT Apr 2019)
description_zh: [hoplight]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0376）是据报道已被朝鲜政府使用的后门特洛伊木马。

name: HTRAN
description: [HTRAN](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0040) is a tool that proxies connections through intermediate hops and aids users in disguising their true geographical location. It can be used by adversaries to hide their location when interacting with the victim networks. (Citation: Operation Quantum Entanglement)(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro IXESHE 2012),(Citation: Microsoft GALLIUM December 2019),(Citation: Cybereason Soft Cell June 2019),,(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools),(Citation: Operation Quantum Entanglement)
description_zh: [htran]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0040）是一种通过中间啤酒花来代替连接的工具，并帮助用户掩盖其真正的地理位置。对手可以使用它在与受害者网络互动时隐藏其位置。 （引用：量子纠缠操作）（引用：NCSC联合报告公共工具）

name: HTTPBrowser
description: [HTTPBrowser](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0070) is malware that has been used by several threat groups. (Citation: ThreatStream Evasion Analysis) (Citation: Dell TG-3390) It is believed to be of Chinese origin. (Citation: ThreatConnect Anthem)
relationship citations: (Citation: Dell TG-3390),(Citation: SecureWorks BRONZE UNION June 2017),(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),(Citation: Nccgroup Emissary Panda May 2018),(Citation: RSA2017 Detect and Respond Adair),,(Citation: Dell TG-3390),(Citation: ZScaler Hacking Team),(Citation: ThreatStream Evasion Analysis)
description_zh: [httpbrowser]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0070）是多个威胁组使用的恶意软件。 （引用：威胁性逃避分析）（引文：戴尔TG-3390）据信它是中国起源的。 （引文：威胁连接国歌）

name: Hacking Team UEFI Rootkit
description: [Hacking Team UEFI Rootkit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0047) is a rootkit developed by the company Hacking Team as a method of persistence for remote access software. (Citation: TrendMicro Hacking Team UEFI)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: TrendMicro Hacking Team UEFI)
description_zh: [Hacking Team UEFI rootkit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0047）是由公司黑客团队开发的Rootkit，是远程访问软件的持久性方法。 （引文：TrendMicro Hacking Team UEFI）

name: Hancitor
description: [Hancitor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0499) is a downloader that has been used by [Pony](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0453) and other information stealing malware.(Citation: Threatpost Hancitor)(Citation: FireEye Hancitor)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FireEye Hancitor),(Citation: Red Canary Verclsid.exe),(Citation: Threatpost Hancitor)
description_zh: [Hancitor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0499）是[Pony]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0453）和其他信息窃取恶意软件的下载器。 （引文：威胁汤匙汉士师）（引文：FireEye Hancitor）

name: Havij
description: [Havij](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0224) is an automatic SQL Injection tool distributed by the Iranian ITSecTeam security company. Havij has been used by penetration testers and adversaries. (Citation: Check Point Havij Analysis)
relationship citations: (Citation: Check Point Rocket Kitten),,(Citation: Check Point Havij Analysis)
description_zh: [havij]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0224）是由伊朗ITSecteam安全公司分发的自动SQL注入工具。 Havij已被渗透测试人员和对手使用。 （引用：检查点HAVIJ分析）

name: Helminth
description: [Helminth](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0170) is a backdoor that has at least two variants - one written in VBScript and PowerShell that is delivered via a macros in Excel spreadsheets, and one that is a standalone Windows executable. (Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016),(Citation: Crowdstrike Helix Kitten Nov 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Webinar Dec 2017),,(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016),(Citation: ClearSky OilRig Jan 2017),(Citation: Unit 42 Playbook Dec 2017)
description_zh: [helminth]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0170）是一个至少有两个变体的后门 - 一个用vbscript和powershell编写，是通过excel电子表格传递的vbscript和powershell，一个是独立的，它是独立的Windows可执行。 （引文：帕洛阿尔托·奥利里格2016年5月）

name: HermeticWiper
description: [HermeticWiper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0697) is a data wiper that has been used since at least early 2022, primarily against Ukraine with additional activity observed in Latvia and Lithuania. Some sectors targeted include government, financial, defense, aviation, and IT services.(Citation: SentinelOne Hermetic Wiper February 2022)(Citation: Symantec Ukraine Wipers February 2022)(Citation: Crowdstrike DriveSlayer February 2022)(Citation: ESET Hermetic Wiper February 2022)(Citation: Qualys Hermetic Wiper March 2022)
contributors: Harshal Tupsamudre, Qualys; Mayuresh Dani, Qualys
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Hermetic Wizard March 2022),(Citation: ESET Hermetic Wiper February 2022),(Citation: Crowdstrike DriveSlayer February 2022),(Citation: Qualys Hermetic Wiper March 2022),(Citation: Symantec Ukraine Wipers February 2022),(Citation: SentinelOne Hermetic Wiper February 2022)
description_zh: [Hermeticwiper]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0697）是一种数据湿式，至少从2022年初开始使用，主要是针对乌克兰，在拉脱维亚和立陶宛观察到额外的活动。针对政府的一些部门包括政府，财务，国防，航空和IT服务。 ）（引文：Qualmys Hermetic雨刮器2022年3月）

name: HermeticWizard
description: [HermeticWizard](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0698) is a worm that has been used to spread [HermeticWiper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0697) in attacks against organizations in Ukraine since at least 2022.(Citation: ESET Hermetic Wizard March 2022)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Hermetic Wizard March 2022)
description_zh: [HermeticWizard](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0698) is a worm that has been used to spread [HermeticWiper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0697) in attacks against organizations in乌克兰至少至少2022年。

name: Heyoka Backdoor
description: [Heyoka Backdoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1027) is a custom backdoor--based on the Heyoka open source exfiltration tool--that  has been used by [Aoqin Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1007) since at least 2013.(Citation: SentinelOne Aoqin Dragon June 2022)(Citation: Sourceforge Heyoka 2022)
contributors: Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan , NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: (Citation: SentinelOne Aoqin Dragon June 2022),,(Citation: SentinelOne Aoqin Dragon June 2022)
description_zh: [heyoka Backdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1027）是基于Heyoka开源剥离工具的自定义后门 - 该工具 -  [aoqin dragon]（https：//攻击。

name: Hi-Zor
description: [Hi-Zor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0087) is a remote access tool (RAT) that has characteristics similar to [Sakula](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0074). It was used in a campaign named INOCNATION. (Citation: Fidelis Hi-Zor)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Fidelis INOCNATION),(Citation: Fidelis Hi-Zor)
description_zh: [hi-zor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0087）是一种远程访问工具（rat），其特征类似于[sakula]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/software/s00744 ）。它被用于名为Inconation的广告系列中。 （引文：菲德利斯hi-zor）

name: HiddenWasp
description: [HiddenWasp](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0394) is a Linux-based Trojan used to target systems for remote control. It comes in the form of a statically linked ELF binary with stdlibc++.(Citation: Intezer HiddenWasp Map 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Intezer HiddenWasp Map 2019)
description_zh: [hiddenwasp]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0394）是一种基于Linux的特洛伊木马，用于针对远程控制的系统。它以静态链接的精灵二进制形式与stdlibc ++。

name: Hikit
description: [Hikit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0009) is malware that has been used by [Axiom](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0001) for late-stage persistence and exfiltration after the initial compromise.(Citation: Novetta-Axiom)(Citation: FireEye Hikit Rootkit)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cisco Group 72),(Citation: Novetta-Axiom),,(Citation: FireEye HIKIT Rootkit Part 2),(Citation: FireEye Hikit Rootkit),(Citation: Novetta-Axiom)
description_zh: [Hikit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0009）是[axiom]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0001）已使用的恶意软件，用于晚期持久性和剥落最初的妥协之后。

name: Hildegard
description: [Hildegard](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0601) is malware that targets misconfigured kubelets for initial access and runs cryptocurrency miner operations. The malware was first observed in January 2021. The TeamTNT activity group is believed to be behind [Hildegard](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0601). (Citation: Unit 42 Hildegard Malware)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Hildegard Malware),,(Citation: Unit 42 Hildegard Malware)
description_zh: [hildegard]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0601）是恶意软件，它针对错误配置的kubelets用于初始访问并运行加密货币矿工操作。恶意软件首先在2021年1月观察到。据信Teamtnt活动组落后于[hildegard]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0601）。 （引文：42单元希尔德加尔恶意软件）

name: HotCroissant
description: [HotCroissant](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0431) is a remote access trojan (RAT) attributed by U.S. government entities to malicious North Korean government cyber activity, tracked collectively as HIDDEN COBRA.(Citation: US-CERT HOTCROISSANT February 2020) [HotCroissant](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0431) shares numerous code similarities with [Rifdoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0433).(Citation: Carbon Black HotCroissant April 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT HOTCROISSANT February 2020),,(Citation: Carbon Black HotCroissant April 2020),(Citation: US-CERT HOTCROISSANT February 2020)
description_zh: [Hotcroissant]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0431）是美国政府实体归因于恶意的朝鲜政府网络活动的远程访问特洛伊木马（RAT），统称为隐藏的Cobra（引文：US-- us-us--- CERT HOTCROISSANT 2020年2月）[Hotcroissant]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0431）与[rifdoor]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/software/s0433）共享许多代码相似之处。碳黑色热剂2020年4月）

name: Hydraq
description: [Hydraq](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0203) is a data-theft trojan first used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) in the 2009 Google intrusion known as Operation Aurora, though variations of this trojan have been used in more recent campaigns by other Chinese actors, possibly including [APT17](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0025).(Citation: MicroFocus 9002 Aug 2016)(Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012)(Citation: Symantec Trojan.Hydraq Jan 2010)(Citation: ASERT Seven Pointed Dagger Aug 2015)(Citation: FireEye DeputyDog 9002 November 2013)(Citation: ProofPoint GoT 9002 Aug 2017)(Citation: FireEye Sunshop Campaign May 2013)(Citation: PaloAlto 3102 Sept 2015)
aliases: 9002 RAT, Aurora, HidraQ, HomeUnix, Homux, HydraQ, McRat, MdmBot, Roarur
relationship citations: (Citation: Cisco Group 72),(Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),(Citation: Novetta-Axiom),,(Citation: Symantec Hydraq Persistence Jan 2010),(Citation: Symantec Trojan.Hydraq Jan 2010),(Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),(Citation: Symantec Hydraq Jan 2010)
description_zh: [Hydraq]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0203）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）首次使用的Data-theft Trojan known as Operation Aurora, though variations of this trojan have been used in more recent campaigns by other Chinese actors, possibly including [APT17](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0025).(Citation: MicroFocus 9002 Aug 2016 （引用：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引用：Symantec Trojan.Hydraq 2010年1月）（引用：ASERT SENWEN SEVENDEND DIMPSED DIGENDED DAGGED 2015年8月8日）（引用：Fireeye代理人9002，2013年11月9002年）（引文：ProofPoint：2017年8月9002日获得了9002）（引文：引文：引文： FireEye Sunshop活动2013年5月）（引文：Paloalto 3102 2015年9月）

name: HyperBro
description: [HyperBro](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0398) is a custom in-memory backdoor used by [Threat Group-3390](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0027).(Citation: Unit42 Emissary Panda May 2019)(Citation: Securelist LuckyMouse June 2018)(Citation: Hacker News LuckyMouse June 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: Securelist LuckyMouse June 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),(Citation: Hacker News LuckyMouse June 2018),(Citation: Unit42 Emissary Panda May 2019),,(Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),(Citation: Unit42 Emissary Panda May 2019)
description_zh: [Hyphybro]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0398）是[threat group-3390]使用的自定义内部后门（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.troups/groups/g0027）。（（引用：Unit42使者熊猫2019年5月）（引文：Securelist Luckymouse 2018年6月）（引文：Hacker News Luckymouse 2018年6月）

name: HyperStack
description: [HyperStack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0537) is a RPC-based backdoor used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) since at least 2018. [HyperStack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0537) has similarities to other backdoors used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) including [Carbon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0335).(Citation: Accenture HyperStack October 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Accenture HyperStack October 2020),,(Citation: Accenture HyperStack October 2020)
description_zh: [Hyperstack]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0537）是[turla]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010）以来使用的RPC的后门，至少至少2018年。 Hyperstack]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0537）与[turla]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010）使用的其他后门具有相似之处，包括[Carbon]（https：/https：/https：/https：/ /Attack.mitre.org/software/S0335)。（Citate：Accenture Hyperstack 2020年10月）

name: ISMInjector
description: [ISMInjector](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0189) is a Trojan used to install another [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049) backdoor, ISMAgent. (Citation: OilRig New Delivery Oct 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: OilRig New Delivery Oct 2017),,(Citation: OilRig New Delivery Oct 2017)
description_zh: [isminjector]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0189）是一个用于安装另一个[oilrig]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0049）的特洛伊木马，Ismagent。 （引文：油脂新交付2017年10月）

name: IceApple
description: [IceApple](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1022) is a modular Internet Information Services (IIS) post-exploitation framework, that has been used since at least 2021 against the technology, academic, and government sectors.(Citation: CrowdStrike IceApple May 2022)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: CrowdStrike IceApple May 2022)
description_zh: [ICEAPPLE]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1022）是一个模块化的互联网信息服务（IIS）后 - 开发框架，至少自2021年以来就使用了技术，学术和政府部门。 （引文：CrowdStrike iCeapple 2022年5月）

name: IcedID
description: [IcedID](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0483) is a modular banking malware designed to steal financial information that has been observed in the wild since at least 2017.  [IcedID](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0483)  has been downloaded by [Emotet](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0367) in multiple campaigns.(Citation: IBM IcedID November 2017)(Citation: Juniper IcedID June 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Valak May 2020),(Citation: Secureworks GOLD CABIN),(Citation: Unit 42 Valak July 2020),(Citation: Unit 42 TA551 Jan 2021),,(Citation: Juniper IcedID June 2020),(Citation: IBM IcedID November 2017)
description_zh: [ICEDID]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0483）是一种模块化银行恶意软件，旨在窃取至少自2017年以来在野外观察到的财务信息。 mitre.org/software/s0483）在多个广告系列中已下载（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0367）。（引用：IBM ICEDID 2017年11月11日）

name: Imminent Monitor
description: [Imminent Monitor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0434) was a commodity remote access tool (RAT) offered for sale from 2012 until 2019, when an operation was conducted to take down the Imminent Monitor infrastructure. Various cracked versions and variations of this RAT are still in circulation.(Citation: Imminent Unit42 Dec2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: QiAnXin APT-C-36 Feb2019),,(Citation: QiAnXin APT-C-36 Feb2019),(Citation: Imminent Unit42 Dec2019)
description_zh: [迫在眉睫的监视器]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0434）是一种商品远程访问工具（RAT），从2012年到2019年，进行了销售，届时进行了一项操作，以降低即将降低迫在眉睫的监视器基础架构。该大鼠的各种破裂版本和变化仍在循环中。

name: Impacket
description: [Impacket](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0357) is an open source collection of modules written in Python for programmatically constructing and manipulating network protocols. [Impacket](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0357) contains several tools for remote service execution, Kerberos manipulation, Windows credential dumping, packet sniffing, and relay attacks.(Citation: Impacket Tools)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: US-CERT TA18-074A),(Citation: Core Security Impacket),(Citation: Tarrask scheduled task),(Citation: Bitdefender FIN8 July 2021),(Citation: Unit42 Emissary Panda May 2019),(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019),(Citation: Impacket Tools)
description_zh: [Impacket]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0357）是用Python编写的模块的开源量，用于编程构建和操纵网络协议。 [Impacket]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0357）包含几种用于远程服务执行的工具，Kerberos操纵，Windows凭据转储，数据包嗅探和中继攻击。（引用：Impacket工具）

name: Industroyer
description: [Industroyer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0604) is a sophisticated malware framework designed to cause an impact to the working processes of Industrial Control Systems (ICS), specifically components used in electrical substations.(Citation: ESET Industroyer) [Industroyer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0604) was used in the attacks on the Ukrainian power grid in December 2016.(Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2017) This is the first publicly known malware specifically designed to target and impact operations in the electric grid.(Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2018)
contributors: Dragos  Threat  Intelligence; Joe Slowik -  Dragos
relationship citations: (Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2017),(Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING),(Citation: ESET Industroyer),(Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2018),,(Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2017),(Citation: ESET Industroyer)
description_zh: [Industroyer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0604）是一个复杂的恶意软件框架，旨在对工业控制系统（ICS）的工作过程产生影响，特别是用于电气取代的组件。（引文：引文：： Eset Industroyer）[Industroyer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0604）在2016年12月对乌克兰电力网格的攻击中使用。（引用：Dragos Crashoverride 2017）这是第一个专门的公共知名恶意软件旨在针对电网中的目标和影响操作。（引文：Dragos Crashoverride 2018）

name: InnaputRAT
description: [InnaputRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0259) is a remote access tool that can exfiltrate files from a victim’s machine. [InnaputRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0259) has been seen out in the wild since 2016. (Citation: ASERT InnaputRAT April 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ASERT InnaputRAT April 2018)
description_zh: [Innaputrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0259）是一种远程访问工具，可以从受害者的计算机中删除文件。 [Innaputrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0259）自2016年以来在野外看到。（引用：Asert Innaputrat 2018年4月）

name: InvisiMole
description: [InvisiMole](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0260) is a modular spyware program that has been used by the InvisiMole Group since at least 2013. [InvisiMole](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0260) has two backdoor modules called RC2FM and RC2CL that are used to perform post-exploitation activities. It has been discovered on compromised victims in the Ukraine and Russia. [Gamaredon Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0047) infrastructure has been used to download and execute [InvisiMole](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0260) against a small number of victims.(Citation: ESET InvisiMole June 2018)(Citation: ESET InvisiMole June 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET InvisiMole June 2018),(Citation: ESET InvisiMole June 2020)
description_zh: [Invisimole]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0260）是一个模块化的间谍程序，至少从2013年开始就已被Invisimole Group使用。 Software/S0260）有两个称为RC2FM和RC2CL的后门模块，用于执行后探索活动。它是在乌克兰和俄罗斯受害的受害者中发现的。 [Gamaredon Group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0047）基础结构已用于下载和执行[Invisimole]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0260）受害者（引文：Invisimole 2018年6月）（引文：Invisimole 2020年6月）

name: Invoke-PSImage
description: [Invoke-PSImage](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0231) takes a PowerShell script and embeds the bytes of the script into the pixels of a PNG image. It generates a one liner for executing either from a file of from the web. Example of usage is embedding the PowerShell code from the Invoke-Mimikatz module and embed it into an image file. By calling the image file from a macro for example, the macro will download the picture and execute the PowerShell code, which in this case will dump the passwords. (Citation: GitHub Invoke-PSImage)
relationship citations: (Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),,(Citation: GitHub Invoke-PSImage),(Citation: GitHub PSImage)
description_zh: [Invoke-psimage]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0231）获取PowerShell脚本，并将脚本的字节嵌入到PNG映像的像素中。它生成一个衬里，用于从网络文件中执行。用法的示例是从Invoke-Mimikatz模块中嵌入PowerShell代码，并将其嵌入到图像文件中。例如，通过从宏调用图像文件，宏将下载图片并执行PowerShell代码，在这种情况下，该代码将转储密码。 （引文：github invoke-psimage）

description: [IronNetInjector](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0581) is a [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) toolchain that utilizes scripts from the open-source IronPython implementation of Python with a .NET injector to drop one or more payloads including [ComRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0126).(Citation: Unit 42 IronNetInjector February 2021 )
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 IronNetInjector February 2021 ),,(Citation: Unit 42 IronNetInjector February 2021 )
description_zh: [ironneTinjector]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0581）是[turla]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.t，groups/g0010一下）工具链，它利用了来自开放式Ironpython实现的脚本带有.net注射器的Python丢弃一个或多个有效载荷，包括[comrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0126）。

name: Ixeshe
description: [Ixeshe](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0015) is a malware family that has been used since at least 2009 against targets in East Asia. (Citation: Moran 2013)
relationship citations: (Citation: Moran 2013),(Citation: Moran 2014),,(Citation: Trend Micro IXESHE 2012),(Citation: Moran 2013)

name: JCry

relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Carbon Black JCry May 2019)
description_zh: [jcry]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0389）是在GO中写的勒索软件。它被确定为#opjerusalem 2019活动的范围。

It is based on Carberp source code and serves as reconnaissance malware. (Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy) (Citation: F-Secure Sofacy 2015) (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 1) (Citation: FireEye APT28 January 2017)

name: JPIN
description: [JPIN](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0201) is a custom-built backdoor family used by [PLATINUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0068). Evidence suggests developers of [JPIN](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0201) and [Dipsind](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0200) code bases were related in some way. (Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016),,(Citation: Microsoft PLATINUM April 2016)

name: JSS Loader
description: [JSS Loader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0648) is Remote Access Trojan (RAT) with .NET and C++ variants that has been used by [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046) since at least 2020.(Citation: eSentire FIN7 July 2021)(Citation: CrowdStrike Carbon Spider August 2021)

name: Janicab
description: [Janicab](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0163) is an OS X trojan that relied on a valid developer ID and oblivious users to install it. (Citation: Janicab)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: f-secure janicab),(Citation: Janicab)
description_zh: [janicab]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0163）是OS X Trojan，它依靠有效的开发人员ID和遗忘用户来安装它。 （引文：Janicab）

name: Javali
description: [Javali](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0528) is a banking trojan that has targeted Portuguese and Spanish-speaking countries since 2017, primarily focusing on customers of financial institutions in Brazil and Mexico.(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
description_zh: [Javali](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0528) is a banking trojan that has targeted Portuguese and Spanish-speaking countries since 2017, primarily focusing on customers of financial institutions in Brazil and Mexico.(Citation: Securelist巴西银行恶意软件2020年7月）

name: KGH_SPY
description: [KGH_SPY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0526) is a modular suite of tools used by [Kimsuky](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0094) for reconnaissance, information stealing, and backdoor capabilities. [KGH_SPY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0526) derived its name from PDB paths and internal names found in samples containing "KGH".(Citation: Cybereason Kimsuky November 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Kimsuky November 2020),,(Citation: Cybereason Kimsuky November 2020)
description_zh: [KGH_SPY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0526) is a modular suite of tools used by [Kimsuky](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0094) for reconnaissance, information stealing,和后门功能。 [kgh_spy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0526）从pdb路径和包含“ kgh”的样本中找到的内部名称衍生出其名称。

description: [KOCTOPUS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0669)'s batch variant is loader used by [LazyScripter](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0140) since 2018 to launch [Octopus](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0340) and [Koadic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0250) and, in some cases, [QuasarRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0262). [KOCTOPUS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0669) also has a VBA variant that has the same functionality as the batch version.(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),,(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021)

name: KOMPROGO
description: [KOMPROGO](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0156) is a signature backdoor used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050) that is capable of process, file, and registry management. (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
description_zh: [komprogo]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0156）是[APT32]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0050）使用的签名后门和注册表管理。 （引文：FireEye APT32 2017年5月）

name: KONNI
description: [KONNI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0356) is a remote access tool that security researchers assess has been used by North Korean cyber actors since at least 2014. [KONNI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0356) has significant code overlap with the [NOKKI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0353) malware family, and has been linked to several suspected North Korean campaigns targeting political organizations in Russia, East Asia, Europe and the Middle East; there is some evidence potentially linking [KONNI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0356) to [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067).(Citation: Talos Konni May 2017)(Citation: Unit 42 NOKKI Sept 2018)(Citation: Unit 42 Nokki Oct 2018)(Citation: Medium KONNI Jan 2020)(Citation: Malwarebytes Konni Aug 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Talos Konni May 2017),(Citation: Medium KONNI Jan 2020),(Citation: Malwarebytes Konni Aug 2021),(Citation: Malwarebytes KONNI Evolves Jan 2022)
description_zh: [KONNI]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0356）是一种远程访问工具，至少自2014年以来，朝鲜网络参与者已经使用了安全研究人员评估。 mitre.org/software/s0356）与[nokki]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0353）恶意软件家族具有重要的代码重叠，并已与几个可疑的朝鲜竞选活动链接，东亚，欧洲和中东；有一些证据可能将[konni]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0356）连接到[apt37]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）。（引用：Talos Konni May May 2017年）（引文：42 Unit Nokki 2018年9月）（引文：42 Unit Nokki 2018年10月）（引文：中型Konni 2020年1月）（引文：Malwarebytes Konni 2021年8月）

relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Zscaler Kasidet),(Citation: Microsoft Kasidet)
description_zh: [kasidet]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0088）是通过使用恶意VBA宏来删除的后门。 （引文：Zscaler kasidet）

name: Kazuar
description: [Kazuar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0265) is a fully featured, multi-platform backdoor Trojan written using the Microsoft .NET framework. (Citation: Unit 42 Kazuar May 2017)

name: Kerrdown
description: [Kerrdown](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0585) is a custom downloader that has been used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050) since at least 2018 to install spyware from a server on the victim's network.(Citation: Amnesty Intl. Ocean Lotus February 2021)(Citation: Unit 42 KerrDown February 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 KerrDown February 2019),(Citation: Amnesty Intl. Ocean Lotus February 2021),,(Citation: Unit 42 KerrDown February 2019),(Citation: Amnesty Intl. Ocean Lotus February 2021)
description_zh: [Kerrdown]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0585）是一个自定义下载器，自从至少2018年以来，[apt32]（https://attpps：//attpps://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0050）从受害者网络上的服务器安装间谍软件。

name: Kessel
description: [Kessel](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0487) is an advanced version of OpenSSH which acts as a custom backdoor, mainly acting to steal credentials and function as a bot. [Kessel](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0487) has been active since its C2 domain began resolving in August 2018.(Citation: ESET ForSSHe December 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET ForSSHe December 2018)
description_zh: [kessel]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0487）是OpenSSH的高级版本，它充当自定义后门，主要是在窃取凭据和功能作为机器人。 [Kessel]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0487）自2018年8月开始解决其C2域以来一直活跃。（引用：Eset Forsshe 2018年12月）

name: Kevin
description: [Kevin](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1020) is a backdoor implant written in C++ that has been used by [HEXANE](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1001) since at least June 2020, including in operations against organizations in Tunisia.(Citation: Kaspersky Lyceum October 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Lyceum October 2021),,(Citation: Kaspersky Lyceum October 2021)

name: KeyBoy

description: This piece of malware steals the content of the user's keychain while maintaining a permanent backdoor  (Citation: OSX Keydnap malware).

name: KillDisk
description: [KillDisk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0607) is a disk-wiping tool designed to overwrite files with random data to render the OS unbootable. It was first observed as a component of [BlackEnergy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0089) malware during cyber attacks against Ukraine in 2015. [KillDisk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0607) has since evolved into stand-alone malware used by a variety of threat actors against additional targets in Europe and Latin America; in 2016 a ransomware component was also incorporated into some [KillDisk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0607) variants.(Citation: KillDisk Ransomware)(Citation: ESEST Black Energy Jan 2016)(Citation: Trend Micro KillDisk 1)(Citation: Trend Micro KillDisk 2)
relationship citations: (Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: ESET Lazarus KillDisk April 2018),(Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: Trend Micro KillDisk 2),(Citation: ESEST Black Energy Jan 2016),(Citation: ESET Telebots Dec 2016),(Citation: KillDisk Ransomware),(Citation: Trend Micro KillDisk 1)
description_zh: [killdisk]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0607）是一种磁盘播放工具，旨在覆盖具有随机数据的文件，以使OS无法引导。首先被视为[BlackEnergy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0089）在2015年对乌克兰进行网络攻击期间的恶意软件的组成部分。 /s0607）从那以后，各种威胁行为者对欧洲和拉丁美洲的其他目标进行了独立的恶意软件； 2016年，还将勒索软件组件合并到一些[killdisk]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0607）中。 KILLDISK 1）（引用：趋势微型Killdisk 2）

name: Kinsing
description: [Kinsing](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0599) is Golang-based malware that runs a cryptocurrency miner and attempts to spread itself to other hosts in the victim environment. (Citation: Aqua Kinsing April 2020)(Citation: Sysdig Kinsing November 2020)(Citation: Aqua Security Cloud Native Threat Report June 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Aqua Kinsing April 2020),(Citation: Sysdig Kinsing November 2020)
description_zh: [Kinsing]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0599）是基于Golang的恶意软件，它运行了加密货币矿工，并试图在受害者环境中传播到其他主机。 （引文：2020年4月的水上亲属）（引文：Sysdig Kinsing 2020年11月）（引文：Aqua Security Cloud Native Threst报告2021年6月）

name: Kivars
description: [Kivars](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0437) is a modular remote access tool (RAT), derived from the Bifrost RAT, that was used by [BlackTech](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0098) in a 2010 campaign.(Citation: TrendMicro BlackTech June 2017)

name: Koadic
description: [Koadic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0250) is a Windows post-exploitation framework and penetration testing tool that is publicly available on GitHub. [Koadic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0250) has several options for staging payloads and creating implants, and performs most of its operations using Windows Script Host.(Citation: Github Koadic)(Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018)(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018),(Citation: ATT Sidewinder January 2021),(Citation: Reaqta MuddyWater November 2017),(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),,(Citation: Github Koadic),(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021)

name: Kobalos
description: [Kobalos](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0641) is a multi-platform backdoor that can be used against Linux, FreeBSD, and Solaris. [Kobalos](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0641) has been deployed against high profile targets, including high-performance computers, academic servers, an endpoint security vendor, and a large internet service provider; it has been found in Europe, North America, and Asia. [Kobalos](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0641) was first identified in late 2019.(Citation: ESET Kobalos Feb 2021)(Citation: ESET Kobalos Jan 2021)
contributors: Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Kobalos Feb 2021),(Citation: ESET Kobalos Jan 2021)
description_zh: [Kobalos]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0641）是一个多平台的后门，可用于Linux，FreeBSD和Solaris。 [kobalos]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0641）已针对高调目标部署，包括高性能计算机，学术服务器，端点安全供应商和大型互联网服务提供商；它已在欧洲，北美和亚洲发现。 [Kobalos]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0641）于2019年底首次确定。

name: Komplex
description: [Komplex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0162) is a backdoor that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) on OS X and appears to be developed in a similar manner to [XAgentOSX](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0161) (Citation: XAgentOSX 2017) (Citation: Sofacy Komplex Trojan).
relationship citations: (Citation: Sofacy Komplex Trojan),(Citation: Secureworks IRON TWILIGHT Active Measures March 2017),(Citation: XAgentOSX 2017),,(Citation: Sofacy Komplex Trojan)
