name: Kwampirs
description: [Kwampirs](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0236) is a backdoor Trojan used by [Orangeworm](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0071). It has been found on machines which had software installed for the use and control of high-tech imaging devices such as X-Ray and MRI machines. (Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018)
contributors: Elger Vinicius S. Rodrigues, @elgervinicius, CYBINT Centre
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018),,(Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018),(Citation: Symantec Security Center Trojan.Kwampirs)
description_zh: [kwampirs]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0236）是[Orangeworm]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0071）使用的后门木马。它已经在安装软件的机器上找到，用于使用和控制高科技成像设备，例如X射线和MRI机器。 （引文：赛门铁克橙虫2018年4月）

name: LOWBALL
description: [LOWBALL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0042) is malware used by [admin@338](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0018). It was used in August 2015 in email messages targeting Hong Kong-based media organizations. (Citation: FireEye admin@338)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye admin@338),,(Citation: FireEye admin@338)
description_zh: [lowball]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0042）是[admin@338]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0018）使用的恶意软件。它于2015年8月在针对基于香港的媒体组织的电子邮件中使用。 （引文：FireEye Admin@338）

name: LaZagne
description: [LaZagne](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0349) is a post-exploitation, open-source tool used to recover stored passwords on a system. It has modules for Windows, Linux, and OSX, but is mainly focused on Windows systems. [LaZagne](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0349) is publicly available on GitHub.(Citation: GitHub LaZagne Dec 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT35 2018),(Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019),(Citation: ATT TeamTNT Chimaera September 2020),(Citation: Symantec Leafminer July 2018),(Citation: TrendMicro Tonto Team October 2020),(Citation: Symantec Buckeye),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),(Citation: ESET EvilNum July 2020),(Citation: Symantec MuddyWater Dec 2018),,(Citation: GitHub LaZagne Dec 2018)
description_zh: [lazagne]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0349）是一种后爆炸，开放式工具，用于在系统上恢复存储的密码。它具有用于Windows，Linux和OSX的模块，但主要集中在Windows系统上。 [Lazagne]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0349）在GitHub上公开可用。（引用：Github Lazagne 2018年12月）

name: LightNeuron
description: [LightNeuron](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0395) is a sophisticated backdoor that has targeted Microsoft Exchange servers since at least 2014. [LightNeuron](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0395) has been used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) to target diplomatic and foreign affairs-related organizations. The presence of certain strings in the malware suggests a Linux variant of [LightNeuron](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0395) exists.(Citation: ESET LightNeuron May 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET LightNeuron May 2019),(Citation: Secureworks IRON HUNTER Profile),,(Citation: ESET LightNeuron May 2019)
description_zh: [LightNeuron]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0395）是一个复杂的后门，至少从2014年开始就针对Microsoft Exchange服务器。 ）已被[Turla]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010）使用，以针对与外交和外交事务相关的组织。恶意软件中某些字符串的存在表明存在[LightNeuron]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0395）的Linux变体。（引用：Eset Lightneuron 2019年5月）

name: Linfo
description: [Linfo](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0211) is a rootkit trojan used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) to open a backdoor on compromised hosts. (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012) (Citation: Symantec Linfo May 2012)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Linfo May 2012)
description_zh: [linfo]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0211）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的rootkit trojan，可在妥协的主机上打开后门。 （引文：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec Linfo 2012年5月）

name: Linux Rabbit
description: [Linux Rabbit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0362) is malware that targeted Linux servers and IoT devices in a campaign lasting from August to October 2018. It shares code with another strain of malware known as Rabbot. The goal of the campaign was to install cryptocurrency miners onto the targeted servers and devices.(Citation: Anomali Linux Rabbit 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Anomali Linux Rabbit 2018)
description_zh: [Linux Rabbit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0362）是恶意软件，该恶意软件针对的是Linux服务器和IoT设备，该广告系列持续时间为2018年8月至10月。它与另一种称为Rabbot的恶意软件菌株共享代码。该活动的目的是将加密货币矿工安装到目标服务器和设备上。（引用：Anomali Linux Rabbit 2018）

name: LiteDuke
description: [LiteDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0513) is a third stage backdoor that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016), primarily in 2014-2015. [LiteDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0513) used the same dropper as [PolyglotDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0518), and was found on machines also compromised by [MiniDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0051).(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),,(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
description_zh: [liteduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0513）是[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的第三阶段后门2015。 [liteduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0513）使用与[polyglotduke]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0518）相同的滴管，并在机器上也被发现[Miniduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0051）。（引用：Eset Dukes 2019年10月）

name: LitePower
description: [LitePower](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0680) is a downloader and second stage malware that has been used by [WIRTE](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0090) since at least 2021.(Citation: Kaspersky WIRTE November 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky WIRTE November 2021),,(Citation: Kaspersky WIRTE November 2021)
description_zh: [litepower]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0680）是下载器和第二阶段恶意软件，自从[wirte]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0090）使用以来至少2021。

name: Lizar
description: [Lizar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0681) is a modular remote access tool written using the .NET Framework that shares structural similarities to [Carbanak](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0030). It has likely been used by [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046) since at least February 2021.(Citation: BiZone Lizar May 2021)(Citation: Threatpost Lizar May 2021)(Citation: Gemini FIN7 Oct 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Threatpost Lizar May 2021),(Citation: Gemini FIN7 Oct 2021),,(Citation: Threatpost Lizar May 2021),(Citation: BiZone Lizar May 2021)
description_zh: [lizar]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0681）是使用.NET框架编写的模块化远程访问工具，该框架与[Carbanak]共享结构性相似性（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software /s0030）。自2021年2月以来，[Fin7]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0046）可能已经使用它。 FIN7 2021年10月）

name: LoJax
description: [LoJax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0397) is a UEFI rootkit used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) to persist remote access software on targeted systems.(Citation: ESET LoJax Sept 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET LoJax Sept 2018),,(Citation: ESET LoJax Sept 2018)
description_zh: [lojax]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0397）是[apt28]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0007）使用的UEFI rootkit，可在目标远程访问系统上使用目标远程访问软件。（引文：Eset Lojax 2018年9月）

name: LockerGoga
description: [LockerGoga](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0372) is ransomware that was first reported in January 2019, and has been tied to various attacks on European companies, including industrial and manufacturing firms.(Citation: Unit42 LockerGoga 2019)(Citation: CarbonBlack LockerGoga 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN6 Apr 2019),,(Citation: Unit42 LockerGoga 2019),(Citation: CarbonBlack LockerGoga 2019),(Citation: Wired Lockergoga 2019)
description_zh: [lockergoga]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0372）是勒索软件，于2019年1月首次报道，并与包括工业和制造公司在内的欧洲公司的各种攻击有关。 2019）（引文：Carbonblack Lockergoa 2019）

name: Lokibot
description: [Lokibot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0447) is a widely distributed information stealer that was first reported in 2015. It is designed to steal sensitive information such as usernames, passwords, cryptocurrency wallets, and other credentials. [Lokibot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0447) can also create a backdoor into infected systems to allow an attacker to install additional payloads.(Citation: Infoblox Lokibot January 2019)(Citation: Morphisec Lokibot April 2020)(Citation: CISA Lokibot September 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit42 SilverTerrier 2018),,(Citation: TrendMicro Msiexec Feb 2018),(Citation: Talos Lokibot Jan 2021),(Citation: FSecure Lokibot November 2019),(Citation: Infoblox Lokibot January 2019)
description_zh: [lokibot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0447）是一个广泛分布的信息窃取器，于2015年首次报道。它旨在窃取敏感信息，例如用户名，密码，加密货币钱包和其他凭据。 [lokibot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0447）还可以在受感染的系统中创建后门，以允许攻击者安装其他有效负载。（引用：infoblox lokibot 2019年1月） ）（引文：CISA Lokibot 2020年9月）

name: LookBack
description: [LookBack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0582) is a remote access trojan written in C++ that was used against at least three US utility companies in July 2019. The TALONITE activity group has been observed using [LookBack](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0582).(Citation: Proofpoint LookBack Malware Aug 2019)(Citation: Dragos TALONITE)(Citation: Dragos Threat Report 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Proofpoint LookBack Malware Aug 2019)
description_zh: [BeackBack]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0582）是一款远程访问C ++编写的远程访问Trojan，在2019年7月在至少三家美国公用事业公司中使用。 ]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0582）。

name: LoudMiner
description: [LoudMiner](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0451) is a cryptocurrency miner which uses virtualization software to siphon system resources. The miner has been bundled with pirated copies of Virtual Studio Technology (VST) for Windows and macOS.(Citation: ESET LoudMiner June 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET LoudMiner June 2019)
description_zh: [LoudMiner]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0451）是一款加密货币矿工，它使用虚拟化软件来滴答系统资源。该矿工已与Windows和Macos的虚拟工作室技术（VST）的盗版副本捆绑在一起。

name: Lslsass
description: [Lslsass](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0121) is a publicly-available tool that can dump active logon session password hashes from the lsass process. (Citation: Mandiant APT1)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1),,(Citation: Mandiant APT1)
description_zh: [LSLSASS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0121）是一种公开的工具，可以从LSASS进程中转移活动登录会话密码哈希。 （引用：Mandiant APT1）

name: Lucifer
description: [Lucifer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0532) is a crypto miner and DDoS hybrid malware that leverages well-known exploits to spread laterally on Windows platforms.(Citation: Unit 42 Lucifer June 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit 42 Lucifer June 2020)
description_zh: [Lucifer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0532）是一款加密矿工和DDOS混合恶意软件，利用众所周知的利用来横向散布在Windows平台上（引用：42 Unit 42 Lucifer 2020年6月6月6月））

name: Lurid
description: [Lurid](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0010) is a malware family that has been used by several groups, including [PittyTiger](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0011), in targeted attacks as far back as 2006. (Citation: Villeneuve 2014) (Citation: Villeneuve 2011)
relationship citations: (Citation: Villeneuve 2014),,(Citation: Villeneuve 2011)
description_zh: [lurid]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0010）是一个恶意软件家族，已被几个组使用，包括[pittytiger]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0011），，在2006年的有针对性攻击中。（引文：Villeneuve 2014）（引文：Villeneuve 2011）

name: MCMD
description: [MCMD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0500) is a remote access tool that provides remote command shell capability used by [Dragonfly 2.0](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0074).(Citation: Secureworks MCMD July 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks MCMD July 2019),,(Citation: Secureworks MCMD July 2019)
description_zh: [MCMD]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0500）是一种远程访问工具，可提供[Dragonfly 2.0]使用的远程命令Shell功能（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0074）） 。（引用：SecureWorks MCMD 2019年7月）

name: MESSAGETAP
description: [MESSAGETAP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0443) is a data mining malware family deployed by [APT41](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0096) into telecommunications networks to monitor and save SMS traffic from specific phone numbers, IMSI numbers, or that contain specific keywords. (Citation: FireEye MESSAGETAP October 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020),(Citation: FireEye MESSAGETAP October 2019),,(Citation: FireEye MESSAGETAP October 2019)
description_zh: [MESSAGETAP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0443) is a data mining malware family deployed by [APT41](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0096) into telecommunications networks to monitor and从特定的电话号码，IMSI号或包含特定关键字的特定电话号码中保存SMS流量。 （引文：FireEye Messagetap 2019年10月）

name: MURKYTOP
description: [MURKYTOP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0233) is a reconnaissance tool used by [Leviathan](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0065). (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018),(Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),,(Citation: FireEye Periscope March 2018)
description_zh: [murkytop]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0233）是[leviathan]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0065）使用的侦察工具。 （引文：2018年3月FireEye Periscope）

name: MacMa
description: [MacMa](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1016) is a macOS-based backdoor with a large set of functionalities to control and exfiltrate files from a compromised computer. [MacMa](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1016) has been observed in the wild since November 2021.(Citation: ESET DazzleSpy Jan 2022)
contributors: Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan , NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET DazzleSpy Jan 2022),(Citation: SentinelOne MacMa Nov 2021),(Citation: Objective-See MacMa Nov 2021)
description_zh: [MACMA]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1016）是一种基于MacOS的后门，具有大量功能，可以从折衷的计算机中控制和删除文件。 [MACMA]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1016）自2021年11月以来一直在野外观察到。（引用：Eset Dazzlespy 2022年1月）

name: MacSpy
description: [MacSpy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0282) is a malware-as-a-service offered on the darkweb  (Citation: objsee mac malware 2017).
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: alientvault macspy),(Citation: objsee mac malware 2017)
description_zh: [MACSPY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0282）是DarkWeb上提供的恶意软件-AS-A-Service（引用：OBJSEE MAC MAC MALWARE 2017）。

name: Machete
description: [Machete](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0409) is a cyber espionage toolset used by [Machete](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0095). It is a Python-based backdoor targeting Windows machines that was first observed in 2010.(Citation: ESET Machete July 2019)(Citation: Securelist Machete Aug 2014)(Citation: 360 Machete Sep 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist Machete Aug 2014),(Citation: ESET Machete July 2019),,(Citation: Securelist Machete Aug 2014),(Citation: ESET Machete July 2019),(Citation: 360 Machete Sep 2020),(Citation: Cylance Machete Mar 2017)
description_zh: [Machete]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0409）是[Machete]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0095）使用的网络间谍工具集。这是一款位于Python的后门瞄准机器，于2010年首次观察到。

name: MailSniper
description: MailSniper is a penetration testing tool for searching through email in a Microsoft Exchange environment for specific terms (passwords, insider intel, network architecture information, etc.). It can be used by a non-administrative user to search their own email, or by an Exchange administrator to search the mailboxes of every user in a domain.(Citation: GitHub MailSniper)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Leafminer July 2018),,(Citation: GitHub MailSniper),(Citation: Black Hills Attacking Exchange MailSniper, 2016)
description_zh: Mailsniper是一种渗透测试工具，用于通过Microsoft Exchange环境中的电子邮件搜索特定术语（密码，内部Intel，网络体系结构信息等）。非管理用户可以使用它来搜索自己的电子邮件，也可以由Exchange管理员搜索域中每个用户的邮箱。（引用：GitHub Mailsniper）

name: MarkiRAT
description: [MarkiRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0652) is a remote access Trojan (RAT) compiled with Visual Studio that has been used by [Ferocious Kitten](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0137) since at least 2015.(Citation: Kaspersky Ferocious Kitten Jun 2021)
contributors: Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Ferocious Kitten Jun 2021),,(Citation: Kaspersky Ferocious Kitten Jun 2021)
description_zh: [Markirat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0652）是一种与Visual Studio一起编译的远程访问Trojan（Rat），已由[凶猛的小猫]（https://attack.mitre.orgg/-组/G0137）至少从2015年开始。（引文：卡巴斯基凶猛小猫2021年6月）

name: Matryoshka
description: [Matryoshka](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0167) is a malware framework used by [CopyKittens](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0052) that consists of a dropper, loader, and RAT. It has multiple versions; v1 was seen in the wild from July 2016 until January 2017. v2 has fewer commands and other minor differences. (Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017) (Citation: CopyKittens Nov 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017),,(Citation: CopyKittens Nov 2015),(Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017)
description_zh: [matryoshka]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0167）是[CopyKittens]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0052）使用的恶意软件框架，由滴管，加载器，载荷，和老鼠。它有多个版本；从2016年7月到2017年1月，在野外看到V1。V2的命令和其他较小的差异更少。 （引文：Clearsky Wilted Tulip 2017年7月）（引文：2015年11月的CopyKittens）

name: Maze
description: [Maze](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0449) ransomware, previously known as "ChaCha", was discovered in May 2019. In addition to encrypting files on victim machines for impact, [Maze](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0449) operators conduct information stealing campaigns prior to encryption and post the information online to extort affected companies.(Citation: FireEye Maze May 2020)(Citation: McAfee Maze March 2020)(Citation: Sophos Maze VM September 2020)
contributors: Center for Threat-Informed Defense (CTID); SarathKumar Rajendran, Trimble Inc
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Maze May 2020),,(Citation: FireEye Maze May 2020),(Citation: Sophos Maze VM September 2020),(Citation: McAfee Maze March 2020)
description_zh: [Maze]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0449）勒索软件（以前称为“ chacha”）于2019年5月被发现。 //attack.mitre.org/software/s0449）操作员在加密之前进行信息窃取活动，并在线发布信息给勒索受影响的公司（引用：Fireeye Maze 2020年5月）（引用：McAfee Maze Maze 2020年3月）迷宫VM 2020年9月）

name: MechaFlounder
description: [MechaFlounder](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0459) is a python-based remote access tool (RAT) that has been used by [APT39](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0087). The payload uses a combination of actor developed code and code snippets freely available online in development communities.(Citation: Unit 42 MechaFlounder March 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 MechaFlounder March 2019),,(Citation: Unit 42 MechaFlounder March 2019)
description_zh: [Mechaflounder]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0459）是一种基于Python的远程访问工具（RAT），已由[APT39]（https://attack.metarce.mitre.org.org/groups/）使用过G0087）。有效载荷结合了演员开发的代码和代码片段，可在开发社区中在线免费提供。

name: MegaCortex
description: [MegaCortex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0576) is ransomware that first appeared in May 2019. (Citation: IBM MegaCortex) [MegaCortex](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0576) has mainly targeted industrial organizations. (Citation: FireEye Ransomware Disrupt Industrial Production)(Citation: FireEye Financial Actors Moving into OT)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: IBM MegaCortex),(Citation: mbed-crypto)
description_zh: [megacortex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0576）是勒索软件，首次出现在2019年5月。 ）主要针对的是工业组织。 （引文：FireEye勒索软件破坏工业生产）（引文：FireEye金融参与者进入OT）

name: Melcoz
description: [Melcoz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0530) is a banking trojan family built from the open source tool Remote Access PC. [Melcoz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0530) was first observed in attacks in Brazil and since 2018 has spread to Chile, Mexico, Spain, and Portugal.(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Securelist Brazilian Banking Malware July 2020)
description_zh: [Melcoz]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0530）是由开源工具远程访问PC构建的银行Trojan家族。 [Melcoz]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0530）在巴西的攻击中首次观察到，自2018年以来已蔓延到智利，墨西哥，西班牙和葡萄牙。

name: Metamorfo
description: [Metamorfo](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0455) is a Latin-American banking trojan operated by a Brazilian cybercrime group that has been active since at least April 2018. The group focuses on targeting banks and cryptocurrency services in Brazil and Mexico.(Citation: Medium Metamorfo Apr 2020)(Citation: ESET Casbaneiro Oct 2019)
contributors: Chen Erlich, @chen_erlich, enSilo; Jose Luis Sánchez Martinez
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Medium Metamorfo Apr 2020),(Citation: FireEye Metamorfo Apr 2018),(Citation: Fortinet Metamorfo Feb 2020),(Citation: ESET Casbaneiro Oct 2019)
description_zh: [metamorfo]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0455）是由巴西网络犯罪集团运营的拉丁美洲银行木马，至少从2018年4月开始就一直活跃。在巴西和墨西哥。

name: Meteor
description: [Meteor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0688) is a wiper that was used against Iranian government organizations, including Iranian Railways, the Ministry of Roads, and Urban Development systems, in July 2021. [Meteor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0688) is likely a newer version of similar wipers called Stardust and Comet that were reportedly used by a group called "Indra" since at least 2019 against private companies in Syria.(Citation: Check Point Meteor Aug 2021)

description_zh: [Meteor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0688）是一家雨刮器，在2021年7月在包括伊朗铁路，道路和城市发展系统在内的伊朗政府组织使用。 （https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0688）可能是一个较新的类似惠普的版本，称为Stardust and Comet，据报道，该小组至少从2019年开始对叙利亚的私人公司进行了一个名为“ Indra”的小组。 ：检查点流星2021年8月）

name: Miner-C
description: [Miner-C](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0133) is malware that mines victims for the Monero cryptocurrency. It has targeted FTP servers and Network Attached Storage (NAS) devices to spread. (Citation: Softpedia MinerC)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Softpedia MinerC)
description_zh: [Miner-C]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0133）是恶意软件，可为Monero加密货币挖掘受害者。它具有针对的FTP服务器和网络附加存储（NAS）设备来传播。 （引文：软皮）

name: MiniDuke
description: [MiniDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0051) is malware that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) from 2010 to 2015. The [MiniDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0051) toolset consists of multiple downloader and backdoor components. The loader has been used with other [MiniDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0051) components as well as in conjunction with [CosmicDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0050) and [PinchDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0048). (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),,(Citation: Securelist MiniDuke Feb 2013),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
description_zh: [Miniduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0051）是[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的恶意软件。 ]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0051）工具集由多个下载器和后门组件组成。加载程序已与其他[Miniduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0051）组件以及与[cosmicduke]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0050）一起使用。和[pinchduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0048）。 （引用：f-secure the dukes）

name: MirageFox
description: [MirageFox](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0280) is a remote access tool used against Windows systems. It appears to be an upgraded version of a tool known as Mirage, which is a RAT believed to originate in 2012. (Citation: APT15 Intezer June 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: APT15 Intezer June 2018),,(Citation: APT15 Intezer June 2018)
description_zh: [MirageFox]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0280）是针对Windows系统使用的远程访问工具。它似乎是一种称为Mirage的工具的升级版本，该工具被认为始于2012年。（引用：APT15 Intezer 2018年6月）

name: Mis-Type

Its name was given based on the variable "More_eggs" being present in its code. There are at least two different versions of the backdoor being used, version 2.0 and version 4.4. (Citation: Talos Cobalt Group July 2018)(Citation: Security Intelligence More Eggs Aug 2019)

name: Mosquito
description: [Mosquito](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0256) is a Win32 backdoor that has been used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010). [Mosquito](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0256) is made up of three parts: the installer, the launcher, and the backdoor. The main backdoor is called CommanderDLL and is launched by the loader program. (Citation: ESET Turla Mosquito Jan 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Turla Mosquito Jan 2018),(Citation: ESET Turla Mosquito May 2018),(Citation: Secureworks IRON HUNTER Profile),,(Citation: ESET Turla Mosquito Jan 2018)

name: Mythic
description: [Mythic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0699) is an open source, cross-platform post-exploitation/command and control platform. [Mythic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0699) is designed to "plug-n-play" with various agents and communication channels.(Citation: Mythic Github)(Citation: Mythic SpecterOps)(Citation: Mythc Documentation) Deployed [Mythic](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0699) C2 servers have been observed as part of potentially malicious infrastructure.(Citation: RecordedFuture 2021 Ad Infra)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Mythc Documentation)
description_zh: [Mythic]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0699）是开源的，跨平台后post-exploitation/命令和控制平台。 [Mythic]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0699）旨在使用各种代理和通信渠道“插入n-play”。 MyTHC文档）部署[神话]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0699）C2服务器已被视为潜在恶意基础架构的一部分。

description: [NBTscan](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0590) is an open source tool that has been used by state groups to conduct internal reconnaissance within a compromised network.(Citation: Debian nbtscan Nov 2019)(Citation: SecTools nbtscan June 2003)(Citation: Symantec Waterbug Jun 2019)(Citation: FireEye APT39 Jan 2019)

name: NDiskMonitor
description: [NDiskMonitor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0272) is a custom backdoor written in .NET that appears to be unique to [Patchwork](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0040). (Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017)

name: NETEAGLE
description: [NETEAGLE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0034) is a backdoor developed by [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) with compile dates as early as 2008. It has two main variants known as “Scout” and “Norton.” (Citation: FireEye APT30)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT30),,(Citation: FireEye APT30)

name: NETWIRE
description: [NETWIRE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0198) is a publicly available, multiplatform remote administration tool (RAT) that has been used by criminal and APT groups since at least 2012.(Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017)(Citation: McAfee Netwire Mar 2015)(Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017),(Citation: Unit42 SilverTerrier 2018),(Citation: Cylance Shaheen Nov 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017),,(Citation: Proofpoint NETWIRE December 2020),(Citation: Red Canary NETWIRE January 2020),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017),(Citation: FireEye NETWIRE March 2019),(Citation: McAfee Netwire Mar 2015),(Citation: Unit 42 NETWIRE April 2020)

name: NOKKI
description: [NOKKI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0353) is a modular remote access tool. The earliest observed attack using [NOKKI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0353) was in January 2018. [NOKKI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0353) has significant code overlap with the [KONNI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0356) malware family. There is some evidence potentially linking [NOKKI](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0353) to [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067).(Citation: Unit 42 NOKKI Sept 2018)(Citation: Unit 42 Nokki Oct 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020),,(Citation: Unit 42 NOKKI Sept 2018)
description_zh: [nokki]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0353）是一个模块化的远程访问工具。最早使用[Nokki]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0353）的攻击是2018年1月。使用[konni]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0356）恶意软件家族。有一些证据可能将[nokki]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0353）连接到[apt37]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）。 2018年9月）（引文：42单元Nokki 2018年10月）

relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Naid June 2012)
description_zh: [NAID]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0205）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的特洛伊木马，可在受损的主机上打开后门。 （引文：赛门铁克Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec NAID 2012年6月）

name: NanHaiShu
description: [NanHaiShu](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0228) is a remote access tool and JScript backdoor used by [Leviathan](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0065). [NanHaiShu](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0228) has been used to target government and private-sector organizations that have relations to the South China Sea dispute. (Citation: Proofpoint Leviathan Oct 2017) (Citation: fsecure NanHaiShu July 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint Leviathan Oct 2017),(Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),,(Citation: fsecure NanHaiShu July 2016),(Citation: Proofpoint Leviathan Oct 2017)

name: NanoCore
description: [NanoCore](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0336) is a modular remote access tool developed in .NET that can be used to spy on victims and steal information. It has been used by threat actors since 2013.(Citation: DigiTrust NanoCore Jan 2017)(Citation: Cofense NanoCore Mar 2018)(Citation: PaloAlto NanoCore Feb 2016)(Citation: Unit 42 Gorgon Group Aug 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Gorgon Group Aug 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017),(Citation: Unit42 SilverTerrier 2018),(Citation: Citizen Lab Group5),,(Citation: Cofense NanoCore Mar 2018),(Citation: PaloAlto NanoCore Feb 2016),(Citation: DigiTrust NanoCore Jan 2017)

name: Net
description: The [Net](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0039) utility is a component of the Windows operating system. It is used in command-line operations for control of users, groups, services, and network connections. (Citation: Microsoft Net Utility) [Net](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0039) has a great deal of functionality, (Citation: Savill 1999) much of which is useful for an adversary, such as gathering system and network information for Discovery, moving laterally through [SMB/Windows Admin Shares](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1021/002) using net use commands, and interacting with services. The net1.exe utility is executed for certain functionality when net.exe is run and can be used directly in commands such as net1 user.
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike Ryuk January 2019),(Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016),(Citation: Alperovitch 2014),(Citation: Mandiant APT1),(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory GRU Brute Force Campaign July 2021),(Citation: Sophos New Ryuk Attack October 2020),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),(Citation: Mandiant Operation Ke3chang November 2014),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk's Return October 2020),(Citation: SecureWorks BRONZE UNION June 2017),(Citation: FireEye APT40 March 2019),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE BUTLER Oct 2017),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016),(Citation: Dell TG-1314),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),(Citation: FireEye KEGTAP SINGLEMALT October 2020),(Citation: Cybereason Soft Cell June 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT38 Oct 2018),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk in 5 Hours October 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021),(Citation: Red Canary Hospital Thwarted Ryuk October 2020),(Citation: Dragos Crashoverride 2018),(Citation: NCC Group Chimera January 2021),(Citation: NCC Group APT15 Alive and Strong),(Citation: Cybereason Cobalt Kitty 2017),(Citation: US-CERT TA18-074A),(Citation: FireEye Know Your Enemy FIN8 Aug 2016),(Citation: FireEye admin@338),(Citation: DFIR Report APT35 ProxyShell March 2022),(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro TA505 June 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk 2 Hour Speed Run November 2020),,(Citation: TechNet Net Time),(Citation: Technet Net Use),(Citation: Savill 1999),(Citation: Microsoft Net)
description_zh: [net]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0039）实用程序是Windows操作系统的组件。它用于控制用户，组，服务和网络连接的命令行操作。 （引文：Microsoft Net Utility） [net]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0039）具有很大的功能，（引用：Savill 1999），其中许多功能对于对手很有用，例如收集系统和网络信息，以发现发现的信息，使用 Net> Net use 命令横向通过[SMB/Windows Admin Share]（https://attps://attps.mitre.org/techniques/t1021/002）移动。 net.exe运行时，将执行net1.exe实用程序，以执行某些功能，并且可以直接在命令中使用，例如 net1 user 。

name: Net Crawler
description: [Net Crawler](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0056) is an intranet worm capable of extracting credentials using credential dumpers and spreading to systems on a network over SMB by brute forcing accounts with recovered passwords and using [PsExec](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0029) to execute a copy of [Net Crawler](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0056). (Citation: Cylance Cleaver)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cylance Cleaver),,(Citation: Cylance Cleaver)
description_zh: [net crawler]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0056）是一种Intranet蠕虫，能够使用凭据倾销器提取凭据，并通过用恢复密码和[PSEXECECECECECECEXEMSTINGS的凭证在网络上传播到网络上，并使用[PSEXECEC ]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0029）执行[Net Crawler]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0056）的副本。 （引文：鳄鱼刀）

name: NetTraveler
description: [NetTraveler](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0033) is malware that has been used in multiple cyber espionage campaigns for basic surveillance of victims. The earliest known samples have timestamps back to 2005, and the largest number of observed samples were created between 2010 and 2013. (Citation: Kaspersky NetTraveler)
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint TA459 April 2017),,(Citation: Kaspersky NetTraveler)
description_zh: [nettraveler]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0033）是恶意软件，已用于多个网络间谍活动，以基本监视受害者。最早的已知样品的时间戳可以追溯到2005年，并且在2010年至2013年之间创建了最多的观测样品。（引用：Kaspersky Nettraveler）

name: Netwalker
description: [Netwalker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0457) is fileless ransomware written in PowerShell and executed directly in memory.(Citation: TrendMicro Netwalker May 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: TrendMicro Netwalker May 2020),(Citation: Sophos Netwalker May 2020)
description_zh: [NetWalker]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0457）是用PowerShell编写的无赎金软件，直接在内存中执行。

name: Ngrok
description: [Ngrok](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0508) is a legitimate reverse proxy tool that can create a secure tunnel to servers located behind firewalls or on local machines that do not have a public IP. [Ngrok](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0508) has been leveraged by threat actors in several campaigns including use for lateral movement and data exfiltration.(Citation: Zdnet Ngrok September 2018)(Citation: FireEye Maze May 2020)(Citation: Cyware Ngrok May 2019)(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),(Citation: CrowdStrike PIONEER KITTEN August 2020),,(Citation: FireEye Maze May 2020),(Citation: MalwareBytes Ngrok February 2020),(Citation: Trend Micro Ngrok September 2020),(Citation: Cyware Ngrok May 2019),(Citation: Zdnet Ngrok September 2018)
description_zh: [ngrok]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0508）是合法的反向代理工具，可以为位于防火墙后面的服务器或没有公共IP的本地机器上创建安全的隧道。 [ngrok]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0508）在几项运动中，威胁参与者在包括侧向移动和数据删除的几项活动中利用了。（引用：ZDNET NGROK 2018年9月） 2020年）（引文：Cyware Ngrok 2019年5月）（引文：Malwarebytes Lazyscripter 2021年2月）

relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Suckfly May 2016),(Citation: Symantec Suckfly March 2016),,(Citation: Microsoft SAM),(Citation: Symantec Backdoor.Nidiran)

name: Nltest
description: [Nltest](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0359) is a Windows command-line utility used to list domain controllers and enumerate domain trusts.(Citation: Nltest Manual)

name: NotPetya
description: [NotPetya](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0368) is malware that was used by [Sandworm Team](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0034) in a worldwide attack starting on June 27, 2017. While [NotPetya](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0368) appears as a form of ransomware, its main purpose was to destroy data and disk structures on compromised systems; the attackers never intended to make the encrypted data recoverable. As such, [NotPetya](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0368) may be more appropriately thought of as a form of wiper malware. [NotPetya](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0368) contains worm-like features to spread itself across a computer network using the SMBv1 exploits EternalBlue and EternalRomance.(Citation: Talos Nyetya June 2017)(Citation: US-CERT NotPetya 2017)(Citation: ESET Telebots June 2017)(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Cyclops Blink March 2022),(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: NCSC Sandworm Feb 2020),(Citation: UK NCSC Olympic Attacks October 2020),(Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: US-CERT NotPetya 2017),(Citation: NCSC Joint Report Public Tools),(Citation: PsExec Russinovich),(Citation: Talos Nyetya June 2017)
description_zh: [nontpetya]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0368）是[Sandworm Team]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0034）使用的恶意软件27，2017。尽管[notpetya]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0368）以勒索软件的一种形式出现，但其主要目的是销毁有关损害系统的数据和磁盘结构；攻击者从不打算使加密数据可回收。因此，[notpetya]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0368）可以更恰当地将其视为雨刷恶意软件的一种形式。 [nontpetya]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0368）包含蠕虫般的功能，可以使用SMBV1 Exploits Eternalblue和Eternalromance在计算机网络中传播自身。 -cert notpetya 2017）（引文：ESET Telebots 2017年6月）（引文：美国地方法院起诉GRU单位74455 2020年10月）

name: OceanSalt
description: [OceanSalt](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0346) is a Trojan that was used in a campaign targeting victims in South Korea, United States, and Canada. [OceanSalt](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0346) shares code similarity with [SpyNote RAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0305), which has been linked to [APT1](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0006).(Citation: McAfee Oceansalt Oct 2018)

name: Olympic Destroyer
description: [Olympic Destroyer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0365) is malware that was used by [Sandworm Team](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0034) against the 2018 Winter Olympics, held in Pyeongchang, South Korea. The main purpose of the malware was to render infected computer systems inoperable. The malware leverages various native Windows utilities and API calls to carry out its destructive tasks. [Olympic Destroyer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0365) has worm-like features to spread itself across a computer network in order to maximize its destructive impact.(Citation: Talos Olympic Destroyer 2018)(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Cyclops Blink March 2022),(Citation: CrowdStrike GTR 2019),(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: UK NCSC Olympic Attacks October 2020),(Citation: Secureworks IRON VIKING ),,(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Unit 74455 October 2020),(Citation: PsExec Russinovich),(Citation: Talos Olympic Destroyer 2018)
description_zh: [奥运会驱逐舰]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0365）是[Sandworm Team]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0034）使用的恶意软件，以针对2018年冬季奥林匹克运动会，在韩国平昌举行。恶意软件的主要目的是使受感染的计算机系统无法操作。该恶意软件利用各种本地Windows实用程序和API调用来执行其破坏性任务。 [奥林匹克驱逐舰]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0365）具有蠕虫状功能，可以在计算机网络上传播自身，以最大程度地发挥其破坏性影响。美国地方法院起诉GRU 74455 2020年10月）

description_zh: [OUTSTEEL]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1017）是一个文件上传器，并且使用[Ember Bear]使用的脚本语言自动开发了Document Quether（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org of /groups/g1003）至少从2021年3月开始。

name: OwaAuth
description: [OwaAuth](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0072) is a Web shell and credential stealer deployed to Microsoft Exchange servers that appears to be exclusively used by [Threat Group-3390](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0027). (Citation: Dell TG-3390)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Dell TG-3390)
description_zh: [Owaauth]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0072）是部署到Microsoft Exchange服务器的Web壳和凭证窃取器，似乎由[thrant Group-3390]（https-3390）（https：//攻击）独家使用。 mitre.org/groups/g0027）。 （引文：戴尔TG-3390）

name: P.A.S. Webshell
description: [P.A.S. Webshell](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0598) is a publicly available multifunctional PHP webshell in use since at least 2016 that provides remote access and execution on target web servers.(Citation: ANSSI Sandworm January 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: ANSSI Sandworm January 2021),,(Citation: ANSSI Sandworm January 2021)
description_zh: [P.A.S. webshel​​l]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0598）是一种公开可用的多功能PHP webshel​​l，至少自2016年以来使用，可在目标网络服务器上提供远程访问和执行。

name: P2P ZeuS
description: [P2P ZeuS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0016) is a closed-source fork of the leaked version of the ZeuS botnet. It presents improvements over the leaked version, including a peer-to-peer architecture. (Citation: Dell P2P ZeuS)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Dell P2P ZeuS)
description_zh: [P2P ZEUS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0016）是泄漏版本的Zeus botnet版本的封闭消息。它对泄漏版本进行了改进，包括对等体系结构。 （引文：戴尔P2P宙斯）

name: P8RAT
description: [P8RAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0626) is a fileless malware used by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045) to download and execute payloads since at least 2020.(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021),,(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)
description_zh: [p8rat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0626）是[menupass]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0045）使用的无申请恶意软件，至少从2020.（引文：Securelist APT10 2021年3月10日）

name: PHOREAL
description: [PHOREAL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0158) is a signature backdoor used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050). (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
description_zh: [phoreal]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0158）是[apt32]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0050）使用的签名后门。 （引文：FireEye APT32 2017年5月）

name: PLAINTEE
description: [PLAINTEE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0254) is a malware sample that has been used by [Rancor](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0075) in targeted attacks in Singapore and Cambodia. (Citation: Rancor Unit42 June 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Rancor Unit42 June 2018),,(Citation: Rancor Unit42 June 2018)
description_zh: [PRAINTEE]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0254）是[Rancor]（rancor]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0075）已使用的恶意软件样本和柬埔寨。 （引文：Rancor Unit42 2018年6月42日）

name: PLEAD
description: [PLEAD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0435) is a remote access tool (RAT) and downloader used by [BlackTech](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0098) in targeted attacks in East Asia including Taiwan, Japan, and Hong Kong.(Citation: TrendMicro BlackTech June 2017)(Citation: JPCert PLEAD Downloader June 2018) [PLEAD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0435) has also been referred to as [TSCookie](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0436), though more recent reporting indicates likely separation between the two. [PLEAD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0435) was observed in use as early as March 2017.(Citation: JPCert TSCookie March 2018)(Citation: JPCert PLEAD Downloader June 2018)
contributors: Hannah Simes, BT Security; Tatsuya Daitoku, Cyber Defense Institute, Inc.
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Palmerworm Sep 2020),(Citation: JPCert PLEAD Downloader June 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro Waterbear December 2019),(Citation: TrendMicro BlackTech June 2017),,(Citation: JPCert PLEAD Downloader June 2018),(Citation: TrendMicro BlackTech June 2017),(Citation: ESET PLEAD Malware July 2018)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0435）是一个远程访问工具（rat）和[BlackTech]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0098）使用的下载器在包括台湾，日本和香港在内的东亚的袭击。被称为[tscookie]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0436），尽管最新的报告表明两者之间可能分离。在2017年3月时，使用[https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0435）。

name: POORAIM
description: [POORAIM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0216) is a backdoor used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067) in campaigns since at least 2014. (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018),,(Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
description_zh: [apt37]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0216）是[apt37]（https：//attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）在广告系列中使用的后门：FireEye APT37 2018年2月）

name: POSHSPY
description: [POSHSPY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0150) is a backdoor that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2015. It appears to be used as a secondary backdoor used if the actors lost access to their primary backdoors. (Citation: FireEye POSHSPY April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye POSHSPY April 2017),,(Citation: FireEye POSHSPY April 2017)
description_zh: [Poshspy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0150）是一个后门，自2015年以来一直在[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用。如果演员失去了对主要的后门的访问权，则似乎用作使用的次要后门。 （引文：FireEye Poshspy 2017年4月）

name: POWERSOURCE
description: [POWERSOURCE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0145) is a PowerShell backdoor that is a heavily obfuscated and modified version of the publicly available tool DNS_TXT_Pwnage. It was observed in February 2017 in spearphishing campaigns against personnel involved with United States Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) filings at various organizations. The malware was delivered when macros were enabled by the victim and a VBS script was dropped. (Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017) (Citation: Cisco DNSMessenger March 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017),,(Citation: Cisco DNSMessenger March 2017),(Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017)
description_zh: [PowerSource]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0145）是PowerShell后门，是公开可用的工具DNS_TXT_PWNAGE的大量混淆和修改的版本。在2017年2月在各种组织的美国证券交易委员会（SEC）档案中，针对与美国证券交易委员会（SEC）文件有关的人事活动中观察到了这一点。当受害者启用宏并删除了VBS脚本时，该恶意软件是交付的。 （引文：Fireeye Fin7 2017年3月7日）（引文：Cisco DNSMESSENGENGENGENS 2017年3月）

name: POWERSTATS
description: [POWERSTATS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0223) is a PowerShell-based first stage backdoor used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069). (Citation: Unit 42 MuddyWater Nov 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: ClearSky MuddyWater Nov 2018),(Citation: ClearSky MuddyWater June 2019),(Citation: Symantec MuddyWater Dec 2018),(Citation: Unit 42 MuddyWater Nov 2017),(Citation: FireEye MuddyWater Mar 2018),,(Citation: ClearSky MuddyWater Nov 2018),(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022),(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),(Citation: Unit 42 MuddyWater Nov 2017),(Citation: FireEye MuddyWater Mar 2018)
description_zh: [POWERSTATS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0223) is a PowerShell-based first stage backdoor used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069). （引文：42 Unit Muddywater 2017年11月）

name: POWERTON
description: [POWERTON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0371) is a custom PowerShell backdoor first observed in 2018. It has typically been deployed as a late-stage backdoor by [APT33](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0064). At least two variants of the backdoor have been identified, with the later version containing improved functionality.(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: Microsoft Holmium June 2020),,(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail)
description_zh: [powerton]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0371）是2018年首次观察到的自定义PowerShell后门。[APT33]（httpps：// thtps：//攻击）通常已将其作为后期后门部署为后期后门。 mitre.org/groups/g0064）。已经确定了后门的至少两个变体，后来的版本包含改进的功能。（引用：FireEye APT33 Guardrail）

name: POWRUNER
description: [POWRUNER](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0184) is a PowerShell script that sends and receives commands to and from the C2 server. (Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Webinar Dec 2017)
description_zh: [powruner]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0184）是一个PowerShell脚本，可发送和从C2服务器发送和接收命令。 （引文：FireEye APT34 2017年12月34日）

name: PS1
description: [PS1](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0613) is a loader that was used to deploy 64-bit backdoors in the [CostaRicto](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0132) campaign.(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020),(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020)
description_zh: [ps1]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0613）是一种加载程序，用于在[costaricto]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0132）中部署64-BIT后门竞选。

name: PUNCHBUGGY
description: [PUNCHBUGGY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0196) is a backdoor malware used by [FIN8](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0061) that has been observed targeting POS networks in the hospitality industry. (Citation: Morphisec ShellTea June 2019)(Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016) (Citation: FireEye Know Your Enemy FIN8 Aug 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016),,(Citation: Morphisec ShellTea June 2019),(Citation: FireEye Know Your Enemy FIN8 Aug 2016),(Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016)
description_zh: [punchbuggy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0196）是[Fin8]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0061）使用的后路恶意软件，已被观察到针对POS网络酒店业。 （引文：2019年6月Morphisec Shelltea）（引文：Fireeye Fin8 2016年5月8日）

name: PUNCHTRACK
description: [PUNCHTRACK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0197) is non-persistent point of sale (POS) system malware utilized by [FIN8](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0061) to scrape payment card data. (Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016) (Citation: FireEye Know Your Enemy FIN8 Aug 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016),,(Citation: FireEye Know Your Enemy FIN8 Aug 2016),(Citation: FireEye Fin8 May 2016)
description_zh: [PUNCHTRACK]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0197）是非销售点（POS）[FIN8]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0061）使用的系统恶意软件刮擦支付卡数据。 （引文：Fireeye Fin8 2016年5月8日）（引文：FireEye知道您的敌人Fin8 2016年8月8日）

name: Pandora
description: [Pandora](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0664) is a multistage kernel rootkit with backdoor functionality that has been in use by [Threat Group-3390](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0027) since at least 2020.(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),,(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021)
description_zh: [pandora]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0664）是一个多阶段内核rootkit，带有后门功能，该功能已被[thrant Group-3390]（https-3390）（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.orgg/groupss）使用。 /g0027）至少从2020年开始。（引用：趋势微铁虎2021年4月）

name: Pasam
description: [Pasam](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0208) is a trojan used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) to open a backdoor on compromised hosts. (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012) (Citation: Symantec Pasam May 2012)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Pasam May 2012)
description_zh: [PASAM]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0208）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的特洛伊木马，可在受损的主机上打开后门。 （引文：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec Pasam 2012年5月）

name: Pass-The-Hash Toolkit
description: [Pass-The-Hash Toolkit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0122) is a toolkit that allows an adversary to "pass" a password hash (without knowing the original password) to log in to systems. (Citation: Mandiant APT1)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1),,(Citation: Mandiant APT1)
description_zh: [Pass-The-Hash Toolkit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0122）是一个工具包，允许对手“传递”密码哈希（不知道原始密码）登录到系统。 （引用：Mandiant APT1）

name: Pay2Key
description: [Pay2Key](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0556) is a ransomware written in C++ that has been used by [Fox Kitten](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0117) since at least July 2020 including campaigns against Israeli companies. [Pay2Key](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0556) has been incorporated with a leak site to display stolen sensitive information to further pressure victims into payment.(Citation: ClearkSky Fox Kitten February 2020)(Citation: Check Point Pay2Key November 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: ClearkSky Fox Kitten February 2020),(Citation: Check Point Pay2Key November 2020),,(Citation: ClearkSky Fox Kitten February 2020),(Citation: Check Point Pay2Key November 2020)
description_zh: [pay2key]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0556）是用C ++编写的勒索软件，该软件已由[Fox Kitten]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0117），因为至少2020年7月，包括针对以色列公司的竞选活动。 [PAY2KEY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0556）已与泄漏网站合并，以显示被盗的敏感信息，以进一步付款，以付款。点工资2Key 2020年11月）

name: PcShare
description: [PcShare](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1050) is an open source remote access tool that has been modified and used by Chinese threat actors, most notably during the FunnyDream campaign since late 2018.(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020)(Citation: GitHub PcShare 2014)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020)
description_zh: [pcshare]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1050）是一种开源远程访问工具，已被中国威胁参与者修改和使用，最著名的是自2018年底以来的FounsulyDream活动中。（引用：BitDefender：BitDefender Funnydream活动2020年11月）（引文：GitHub PCShare 2014）

name: Peirates
description: [Peirates](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0683) is a post-exploitation Kubernetes exploitation framework with a focus on gathering service account tokens for lateral movement and privilege escalation. The tool is written in GoLang and publicly available on GitHub.(Citation: Peirates GitHub)
relationship citations: (Citation: TeamTNT Cloud Enumeration),,(Citation: Peirates GitHub)
description_zh: [peirates]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0683）是一个后 -  exexploitation kubernetes剥削框架，重点是收集服务帐户令牌，以进行横向移动和特权升级。该工具用Golang编写，并在GitHub上公开可用。（引用：Peirates github）

name: Penquin
description: [Penquin](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0587) is a remote access trojan (RAT) with multiple versions used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) to target Linux systems since at least 2014.(Citation: Kaspersky Turla Penquin December 2014)(Citation: Leonardo Turla Penquin May 2020)
contributors: Antonio Villani, @LDO_CyberSec, Leonardo's Cyber Security Division; Nino Verde, @LDO_CyberSec, Leonardo's Cyber Security Division; Silvio La Porta, @LDO_CyberSec, Leonardo's Cyber Security Division
relationship citations: (Citation: Leonardo Turla Penquin May 2020),,(Citation: Leonardo Turla Penquin May 2020),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla Penquin December 2014)
description_zh: [penquin]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0587）是一个远程访问trojan（rat），其多个版本由[turla]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.orgroups/g0010）到目标Linux系统至少至少2014年。

name: Peppy
description: [Peppy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0643) is a Python-based remote access Trojan, active since at least 2012, with similarities to [Crimson](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0115).(Citation: Proofpoint Operation Transparent Tribe March 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 ProjectM March 2016),,(Citation: Proofpoint Operation Transparent Tribe March 2016)
description_zh: [PEPPY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0643）是一个基于Python的远程访问Trojan，至少从2012年起就活跃，与[Crimson]相似（https：//attack.mitre.org.org/软件/S0115）。

name: Pillowmint
description: [Pillowmint](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0517) is a point-of-sale malware used by [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046) designed to capture credit card information.(Citation: Trustwave Pillowmint June 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trustwave Pillowmint June 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Carbon Spider August 2021),,(Citation: Trustwave Pillowmint June 2020)
description_zh: [PillowMint]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0517）是[Fin7]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0046）使用的Point-of-sale恶意软件卡信息。

name: PinchDuke
description: [PinchDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0048) is malware that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) from 2008 to 2010. (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
relationship citations: (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),,(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
description_zh: [pinchduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0048）是[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的恶意软件，2008年至2010年。 F-Secure公爵）

name: Ping
description: [Ping](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0097) is an operating system utility commonly used to troubleshoot and verify network connections. (Citation: TechNet Ping)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: NCC Group APT15 Alive and Strong),(Citation: Alperovitch 2014),(Citation: Group IB APT 41 June 2021),(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk in 5 Hours October 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),(Citation: ClearSky Siamesekitten August 2021),(Citation: DHS/CISA Ransomware Targeting Healthcare October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk's Return October 2020),(Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017),(Citation: Cybereason Soft Cell June 2019),(Citation: Symantec Shuckworm January 2022),,(Citation: TechNet Ping)
description_zh: [ping]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0097）是一种操作系统实用程序，通常用于故障排除和验证网络连接。 （引用：Technet Ping）

name: PingPull
description: [PingPull](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1031) is a remote access Trojan (RAT) written in Visual C++ that has been used by [GALLIUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0093) since at least June 2022. [PingPull](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1031) has been used to target telecommunications companies, financial institutions, and government entities in Afghanistan, Australia, Belgium, Cambodia, Malaysia, Mozambique, the Philippines, Russia, and Vietnam.(Citation: Unit 42 PingPull Jun 2022)
contributors: Manikanran Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India; Yoshihiro Kori, NEC Corporation
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 PingPull Jun 2022),,(Citation: Unit 42 PingPull Jun 2022)
description_zh: [pingpull]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1031）是远程访问trojan（rat）在Visual C ++中编写的，已由[gallium]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.orgg/groups）使用。 /g0093）至少从2022年6月开始。[pingpull]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1031）用于针对电信公司，金融机构和政府机构，阿富汗，澳大利亚，澳大利亚，比尔木，贝尔利吉亚，坎博迪亚，，坎博迪亚，，坎博迪亚，，剑桥，，剑桥大学，马来西亚，莫桑比克，菲律宾，俄罗斯和越南。

name: PipeMon
description: [PipeMon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0501) is a multi-stage modular backdoor used by [Winnti Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0044).(Citation: ESET PipeMon May 2020)
contributors: Martin Smolár, ESET; Mathieu Tartare, ESET
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET PipeMon May 2020),,(Citation: ESET PipeMon May 2020)
description_zh: [pipemon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0501）是[winnti group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0044）使用的多stage模块化后门。 Eset Pipemon 2020年5月）

name: Pisloader
description: [Pisloader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0124) is a malware family that is notable due to its use of DNS as a C2 protocol as well as its use of anti-analysis tactics. It has been used by [APT18](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0026) and is similar to another malware family, [HTTPBrowser](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0070), that has been used by the group. (Citation: Palo Alto DNS Requests)
relationship citations: (Citation: Palo Alto DNS Requests),,(Citation: Palo Alto DNS Requests)
description_zh: [pisloader]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0124）是一个恶意软件家族，由于其将DNS用作C2协议以及使用抗分析策略而值得注意。它已通过[APT18]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0026）使用，与另一个恶意软件家族[httpbrowser]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0070），相似该小组已经使用了。 （引文：帕洛阿尔托DNS请求）

name: PlugX
description: [PlugX](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0013) is a remote access tool (RAT) with modular plugins that has been used by multiple threat groups.(Citation: Lastline PlugX Analysis)(Citation: FireEye Clandestine Fox Part 2)(Citation: New DragonOK)(Citation: Dell TG-3390)
aliases: DestroyRAT, Kaba, Korplug, Sogu, TVT, Thoper

name: PoetRAT
description: [PoetRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0428) is a remote access trojan (RAT) that was first identified in April 2020. [PoetRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0428) has been used in multiple campaigns against the private and public sectors in Azerbaijan, including ICS and SCADA systems in the energy sector. The STIBNITE activity group has been observed using the malware. [PoetRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0428) derived its name from references in the code to poet William Shakespeare. (Citation: Talos PoetRAT April 2020)(Citation: Talos PoetRAT October 2020)(Citation: Dragos Threat Report 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Dragos Threat Report 2020),(Citation: Talos PoetRAT October 2020),(Citation: Talos PoetRAT April 2020)
description_zh: [poetrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0428）是一个远程访问特洛伊（Rat），于2020年4月首次确定。 S0428）已用于针对阿塞拜疆的私营部门和公共部门的多项运动，包括能源领域的ICS和SCADA系统。使用恶意软件观察到了Stibnite活动组。 [poetrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0428）从代码中的参考文献引入诗人威廉·莎士比亚（William Shakespeare）。 （引文：2020年4月的Talos Poetrat）（引文：Talos Poetrat 2020年10月）（引文：Dragos威胁报告2020）

name: PoisonIvy
description: [PoisonIvy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0012) is a popular remote access tool (RAT) that has been used by many groups.(Citation: FireEye Poison Ivy)(Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012)(Citation: Symantec Darkmoon Aug 2005)

description_zh: [毒理]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0012）是一个流行的远程访问工具（大鼠），已被许多组使用。 （引文：Symantec Darkmoon 2005年8月）

name: PolyglotDuke
description: [PolyglotDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0518) is a downloader that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2013. [PolyglotDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0518) has been used to drop [MiniDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0051).(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),,(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
description_zh: [polyglotduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0518）是[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0016）以来至少从2013年开始使用的下载器。 PolyGlotDuke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0518）已用于删除[Miniduke]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0051）。

name: Pony
description: [Pony](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0453) is a credential stealing malware, though has also been used among adversaries for its downloader capabilities. The source code for Pony Loader 1.0 and 2.0 were leaked online, leading to their use by various threat actors.(Citation: Malwarebytes Pony April 2016)
contributors: Arie Olshtein, Check Point; Kobi Eisenkraft, Check Point
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Malwarebytes Pony April 2016)
description_zh: [PONY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0453）是凭证窃取恶意软件，尽管也已在对手中用于其下载器功能。小马加载程序1.0和2.0的源代码在线泄漏，导致各种威胁参与者使用。（引用：Malwarebytes Pony 2016年4月）

name: PoshC2
description: [PoshC2](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0378) is an open source remote administration and post-exploitation framework that is publicly available on GitHub. The server-side components of the tool are primarily written in Python, while the implants are written in [PowerShell](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001). Although [PoshC2](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0378) is primarily focused on Windows implantation, it does contain a basic Python dropper for Linux/macOS.(Citation: GitHub PoshC2)
relationship citations: (Citation: SecureWorks August 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),,(Citation: SecureWorks August 2019),(Citation: GitHub PoshC2)
description_zh: [poshc2]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0378）是一个开源远程管理和后解放框架，在GitHub上公开可用。该工具的服务器端组件主要用Python编写，而植入物则以[PowerShell]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/techniques/t1059/001）编写。虽然[POSHC2]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0378）主要集中在Windows植入上，但它确实包含一个用于Linux/MacOS的基本Python Dropper。（引用：Github Poshc2）

name: PowGoop
description: [PowGoop](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1046) is a loader that consists of a DLL loader and a PowerShell-based downloader; it has been used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069) as their main loader.(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)(Citation: CYBERCOM Iranian Intel Cyber January 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022),,(Citation: CYBERCOM Iranian Intel Cyber January 2022),(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)
description_zh: [POWGOOP]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1046）是由DLL加载程序和基于PowerShell的下载器组成的加载程序；它已被[Muddywater]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0069）用作其主要装载机。（引用：DHS CISA AA22-0555A MUDDYWATE

name: Power Loader
description: [Power Loader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0177) is modular code sold in the cybercrime market used as a downloader in malware families such as Carberp, Redyms and Gapz. (Citation: MalwareTech Power Loader Aug 2013) (Citation: WeLiveSecurity Gapz and Redyms Mar 2013)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: MalwareTech Power Loader Aug 2013),(Citation: WeLiveSecurity Gapz and Redyms Mar 2013)
description_zh: [Power Loader]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0177）是在Carberp，Redyms和Gapz等恶意软件家族中的下载器中出售的模块化代码。 （引文：Malwaretech Power Loader 2013年8月）（引文：WeliveSecurity Gapz和Redyms 2013年3月）

name: PowerDuke
description: [PowerDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0139) is a backdoor that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) in 2016. It has primarily been delivered through Microsoft Word or Excel attachments containing malicious macros. (Citation: Volexity PowerDuke November 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Volexity PowerDuke November 2016),,(Citation: Volexity PowerDuke November 2016)
description_zh: [PowerDuke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0139）是[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的后门。通过Microsoft Word或包含恶意宏的Excel附件传递。 （引文：Volexity Powerduke 2016年11月）

name: PowerLess
description: [PowerLess](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1012) is a PowerShell-based modular backdoor that has been used by [Magic Hound](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0059) since at least 2022.(Citation: Cybereason PowerLess February 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason PowerLess February 2022),,(Citation: Cybereason PowerLess February 2022)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1012）是一个基于PowerShell的模块化后门，自从[Magic Hound]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0059））至少2022年。

name: PowerPunch
description: [PowerPunch](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0685) is a lightweight downloader that has been used by [Gamaredon Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0047) since at least 2021.(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022),,(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022)
description_zh: [PowerPunch]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0685）是一个轻量级下载器，已被[Gamaredon Group]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0047）起使用，至少至少从2021年开始使用。

name: PowerShower
description: [PowerShower](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0441) is a PowerShell backdoor used by [Inception](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0100) for initial reconnaissance and to download and execute second stage payloads.(Citation: Unit 42 Inception November 2018)(Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Inception November 2018),,(Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019),(Citation: Unit 42 Inception November 2018)
description_zh: [PowerShower]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0441）是[Inception]使用的PowerShell Backdoor（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0100）用于初始侦察，并下载和执行并执行并执行并执行第二阶段有效载荷。

name: PowerSploit
description: [PowerSploit](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0194) is an open source, offensive security framework comprised of [PowerShell](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001) modules and scripts that perform a wide range of tasks related to penetration testing such as code execution, persistence, bypassing anti-virus, recon, and exfiltration. (Citation: GitHub PowerSploit May 2012) (Citation: PowerShellMagazine PowerSploit July 2014) (Citation: PowerSploit Documentation)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: NCC Group TA505),(Citation: TrendMicro EarthLusca 2022),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),(Citation: Cymmetria Patchwork),(Citation: CrowdStrike Carbon Spider August 2021),(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020),(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019),(Citation: Pentestlab Stored Credentials),(Citation: PowerSploit Documentation),(Citation: GitHub PowerSploit May 2012),(Citation: Harmj0y Kerberoast Nov 2016),(Citation: PowerSploit Invoke Kerberoast)
description_zh: [powersploit]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0194）是由[PowerShell]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.techniques/techniques/t1059/001）组成的开源，进攻安全框架。执行与渗透测试相关的广泛任务的脚本，例如代码执行，持久性，绕过反病毒，侦察和渗透。 （引文：Github Powersploit 2012年5月）（引文：Powershellmagazine Powersploit 2014年7月）（引文：PowerSploit文档）

name: PowerStallion
description: [PowerStallion](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0393) is a lightweight [PowerShell](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001) backdoor used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010), possibly as a recovery access tool to install other backdoors.(Citation: ESET Turla PowerShell May 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Turla PowerShell May 2019),,(Citation: ESET Turla PowerShell May 2019)
description_zh: [powerstallion]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0393）是轻量级[powershell]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/techniques/techniques/t1059/001）backdoor使用了[turla]（htttps]（htttps：httpps：：htttps：htttps：htttps：htttpse） //attack.mitre.org/groups/g0010），可能是安装其他后门的恢复访问工具（引用：Eset Turla Powershell 2019年5月）

name: Prikormka
description: [Prikormka](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0113) is a malware family used in a campaign known as Operation Groundbait. It has predominantly been observed in Ukraine and was used as early as 2008. (Citation: ESET Operation Groundbait)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: ESET Operation Groundbait)
description_zh: [prikormka]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0113）是一种恶意软件系列，用于广告系列，称为“操作grountbait”。它主要是在乌克兰观察到的，早在2008年就被使用。

name: ProLock
description: [ProLock](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0654) is a ransomware strain that has been used in Big Game Hunting (BGH) operations since at least 2020, often obtaining initial access with [QakBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0650). [ProLock](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0654) is the successor to PwndLocker ransomware which was found to contain a bug allowing decryption without ransom payment in 2019.(Citation: Group IB Ransomware September 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Group IB Ransomware September 2020)
description_zh: [prolock]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0654）是一种勒索软件菌株，至少自2020年以来一直在大型游戏狩猎（BGH）操作中使用，通常与[qakbot]（https：https：https：https：https：https：https：https： //attack.mitre.org/software/s0650）。 [prolock]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0654）是Pwndlocker lansomware的继任者，该勒索软件被发现包含一个错误，允许在2019年不用勒索付款而进行解密。

name: Proton
description: [Proton](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0279) is a macOS backdoor focusing on data theft and credential access  (Citation: objsee mac malware 2017).
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: objsee mac malware 2017)
description_zh: [Proton]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0279）是MacOS后门，重点是数据盗窃和凭据访问（引用：OBJSEE MAC MAC MALWARE 2017）。

name: Proxysvc
description: [Proxysvc](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0238) is a malicious DLL used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) in a campaign known as Operation GhostSecret. It has appeared to be operating undetected since 2017 and was mostly observed in higher education organizations. The goal of [Proxysvc](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0238) is to deliver additional payloads to the target and to maintain control for the attacker. It is in the form of a DLL that can also be executed as a standalone process. (Citation: McAfee GhostSecret)
relationship citations: (Citation: McAfee GhostSecret),,(Citation: McAfee GhostSecret)
description_zh: [proxysvc]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0238）是[lazarus group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0032）使用的恶意DLL 。自2017年以来，它似乎一直没有被发现，并且主要在高等教育组织中观察到。 [ProxySVC]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0238）的目标是向目标传递额外的有效负载并维持攻击者的控制。以DLL的形式，也可以作为独立过程执行。 （引用：McAfee Ghostsecret）

name: PsExec
description: [PsExec](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0029) is a free Microsoft tool that can be used to execute a program on another computer. It is used by IT administrators and attackers. (Citation: Russinovich Sysinternals) (Citation: SANS PsExec)
