name: Psylo
description: [Psylo](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0078) is a shellcode-based Trojan that has been used by [Scarlet Mimic](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0029). It has similar characteristics as [FakeM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0076). (Citation: Scarlet Mimic Jan 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Scarlet Mimic Jan 2016),,(Citation: Scarlet Mimic Jan 2016)
description_zh: [psylo]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0078）是基于shellcode的木马，已由[Scarlet Mimic]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0029）使用。它具有与[fakem]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0076）相似的特征。 （引文：猩红色模仿2016年1月）

name: Pteranodon
description: [Pteranodon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0147) is a custom backdoor used by [Gamaredon Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0047). (Citation: Palo Alto Gamaredon Feb 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Gamaredon February 2022),(Citation: Secureworks IRON TILDEN Profile),(Citation: Palo Alto Gamaredon Feb 2017),(Citation: Symantec Shuckworm January 2022),(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022),,(Citation: Palo Alto Gamaredon Feb 2017),(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022),(Citation: Unit 42 Gamaredon February 2022),(Citation: Symantec Shuckworm January 2022)
description_zh: [pteranodon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0147）是[gamaredon group]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0047）使用的自定义后门。 （引文：帕洛阿尔托·甘帕登（Palo Alto Gamaredon）2017年2月）

name: Pupy
description: [Pupy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0192) is an open source, cross-platform (Windows, Linux, OSX, Android) remote administration and post-exploitation tool. (Citation: GitHub Pupy) It is written in Python and can be generated as a payload in several different ways (Windows exe, Python file, PowerShell oneliner/file, Linux elf, APK, Rubber Ducky, etc.). (Citation: GitHub Pupy) [Pupy](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0192) is publicly available on GitHub. (Citation: GitHub Pupy)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT35 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: Unit 42 Magic Hound Feb 2017),(Citation: Secureworks Cobalt Gypsy Feb 2017),,(Citation: GitHub Pupy)
description_zh: [pupy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0192）是开源，cross-platform（Windows，linux，osx，Android）远程管理和后示例工具。 （引用：github pupy）它用python编写，可以以几种不同的方式生成有效载荷（Windows Exe，Python文件，PowerShell Oneliner/File/File，Linux Elf，APK，APK，Rubber Ducky等）。 （引用：github pupy）[pupy]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0192）在GitHub上公开可用。 （引文：github pupy）

name: PyDCrypt
description: [PyDCrypt](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1032) is malware written in Python designed to deliver [DCSrv](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1033). It has been used by [Moses Staff](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1009) since at least September 2021, with each sample tailored for its intended victim organization.(Citation: Checkpoint MosesStaff Nov 2021)
contributors: Hiroki Nagahama, NEC Corporation; Manikantan Srinivasan , NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India
relationship citations: (Citation: Checkpoint MosesStaff Nov 2021),,(Citation: Checkpoint MosesStaff Nov 2021)
description_zh: [pydcrypt]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1032）是用python编写的恶意软件，旨在交付[dcsrv]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/s1033）。至少自2021年9月以来，[摩西工作人员]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g1009）已使用它，每个样本都针对其预期的受害者组织量身定制。

name: Pysa
description: [Pysa](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0583) is a ransomware that was first used in October 2018 and has been seen to target particularly high-value finance, government and healthcare organizations.(Citation: CERT-FR PYSA April 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: CERT-FR PYSA April 2020)
description_zh: [pysa]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0583）是一种勒索软件，最初于2018年10月使用，已被视为针对高价值金融，政府和医疗保健组织。 Pysa fr 2020年4月）

name: QUADAGENT
description: [QUADAGENT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0269) is a PowerShell backdoor used by [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049). (Citation: Unit 42 QUADAGENT July 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 QUADAGENT July 2018),,(Citation: GitHub Invoke-Obfuscation),(Citation: Unit 42 QUADAGENT July 2018)
description_zh: [quadagent]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0269）是[oilrig]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0049）使用的PowerShell Backdoor。 （引文：2018年7月42日第42单元）

name: QakBot
description: [QakBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0650) is a modular banking trojan that has been used primarily by financially-motivated actors since at least 2007. [QakBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0650) is continuously maintained and developed and has evolved from an information stealer into a delivery agent for ransomware, most notably [ProLock](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0654) and [Egregor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0554).(Citation: Trend Micro Qakbot December 2020)(Citation: Red Canary Qbot)(Citation: Kaspersky QakBot September 2021)(Citation: ATT QakBot April 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: ATT QakBot April 2021),,(Citation: Group IB Ransomware September 2020),(Citation: Red Canary Qbot),(Citation: Trend Micro Qakbot December 2020),(Citation: Crowdstrike Qakbot October 2020),(Citation: Cyberint Qakbot May 2021),(Citation: Kaspersky QakBot September 2021),(Citation: Trend Micro Qakbot May 2020),(Citation: Kroll Qakbot June 2020),(Citation: ATT QakBot April 2021)
description_zh: [qakbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0650）是一个模块化的银行木马，至少从2007年开始就主要由财务上的参与者使用。 org/software/s0650）是不断维护和开发的，并已从信息窃取器演变为勒索软件的送货代理，最著名的是[prolock]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0654）和[egregor]（egregor]（egregor]（Egregor）（ https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0554)。（Citation：趋势Micro Qakbot 2020年12月）（引用：红色金丝雀QBOT）（引用：Kaspersky Qakbot 2021年9月）（引文：ATT QAKBOT

name: QuasarRAT
description: [QuasarRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0262) is an open-source, remote access tool that has been publicly available on GitHub since at least 2014. [QuasarRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0262) is developed in the C# language.(Citation: GitHub QuasarRAT)(Citation: Volexity Patchwork June 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Gorgon Group Aug 2018),(Citation: Volexity Patchwork June 2018),(Citation: Symantec Cicada November 2020),(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),(Citation: ESET BackdoorDiplomacy Jun 2021),(Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017),(Citation: DOJ APT10 Dec 2018),(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021),,(Citation: CISA AR18-352A Quasar RAT December 2018),(Citation: GitHub QuasarRAT),(Citation: Volexity Patchwork June 2018)
description_zh: [quasarrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0262）是一种开放式，远程访问工具，至少从2014年开始就在GitHub上公开可用。 .org/Software/s0262）在C＃语言中开发。

name: QuietSieve
description: [QuietSieve](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0686) is an information stealer that has been used by [Gamaredon Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0047) since at least 2021.(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022),,(Citation: Microsoft Actinium February 2022)
description_zh: [quietsieve]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0686）是一个信息窃取器，自从至少2021年以来，[gamaredon group]（https://attpps：//attpps://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0047） 。

name: RARSTONE
description: [RARSTONE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0055) is malware used by the [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019) group that has some characteristics similar to [PlugX](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0013). (Citation: Aquino RARSTONE)
relationship citations: (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: CameraShy),,(Citation: Camba RARSTONE),(Citation: Aquino RARSTONE)
description_zh: [rarstone]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0055）是[Naikon]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0019）组使用的恶意软件，该组具有类似于[Plugx的特征]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0013）。 （引文：阿基诺rarstone）

name: RATANKBA
description: [RATANKBA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0241) is a remote controller tool used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032). [RATANKBA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0241) has been used in attacks targeting financial institutions in Poland, Mexico, Uruguay, the United Kingdom, and Chile. It was also seen used against organizations related to telecommunications, management consulting, information technology, insurance, aviation, and education. [RATANKBA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0241) has a graphical user interface to allow the attacker to issue jobs to perform on the infected machines. (Citation: Lazarus RATANKBA) (Citation: RATANKBA)
relationship citations: (Citation: Lazarus RATANKBA),,(Citation: RATANKBA),(Citation: Lazarus RATANKBA)
description_zh: [ratankba]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0241）是[lazarus group]使用的远程控制器工具（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0032）。 [ratankba]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0241）已用于针对波兰，墨西哥，乌拉圭，英国和智利的金融机构的攻击。还可以看出，它针对与电信，管理咨询，信息技术，保险，航空和教育有关的组织。 [ratankba]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0241）具有图形用户界面，可让攻击者发布作业以在受感染的机器上执行。 （引文：拉撒路·兰克巴巴（Lazarus Ratankba）（引文：ratankba）

name: RCSession
description: [RCSession](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0662) is a backdoor written in C++ that has been in use since at least 2018 by [Mustang Panda](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0129) and by [Threat Group-3390](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0027) (Type II Backdoor).(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE PRESIDENT December 2019)(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021)(Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE PRESIDENT December 2019),(Citation: Profero APT27 December 2020),(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),,(Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE PRESIDENT December 2019),(Citation: Profero APT27 December 2020)
description_zh: [rcsession]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0662）是用C ++编写的后门，至少从[野马熊猫]（https：//attack.mitark.mitre.org.org/groups）开始使用。 /g0129）和[theat teht group-3390]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0027）（II型后门）。 ）（引文：趋势微型DRBControl 2020年2月）

name: RDAT
description: [RDAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0495) is a backdoor used by the suspected Iranian threat group [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049). [RDAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0495) was originally identified in 2017 and targeted companies in the telecommunications sector.(Citation: Unit42 RDAT July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit42 RDAT July 2020),,(Citation: Unit42 RDAT July 2020)
description_zh: [RDAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0495) is a backdoor used by the suspected Iranian threat group [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049). [rdat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0495）最初在2017年确定，并在电信行业中有针对性的公司。（引用：Unit42 RDAT 2020年7月）

name: RDFSNIFFER
description: [RDFSNIFFER](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0416) is a module loaded by [BOOSTWRITE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0415) which allows an attacker to monitor and tamper with legitimate connections made via an application designed to provide visibility and system management capabilities to remote IT techs.(Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019),,(Citation: FireEye FIN7 Oct 2019)
description_zh: [rdfsniffer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0416）是由[boostwrite]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0415）加载的模块通过应用程序建立的合法连接旨在为远程IT技术提供可见性和系统管理功能。

name: REvil
description: [REvil](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0496) is a ransomware family that has been linked to the [GOLD SOUTHFIELD](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0115) group and operated as ransomware-as-a-service (RaaS) since at least April 2019. [REvil](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0496), which as been used against organizations in the manufacturing, transportation, and electric sectors, is highly configurable and shares code similarities with the GandCrab RaaS.(Citation: Secureworks REvil September 2019)(Citation: Intel 471 REvil March 2020)(Citation: Group IB Ransomware May 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks GandCrab and REvil September 2019),(Citation: Secureworks REvil September 2019),(Citation: IBM Ransomware Trends September 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Carbon Spider August 2021),(Citation: FBI Flash FIN7 USB),,(Citation: Intel 471 REvil March 2020),(Citation: Group IB Ransomware May 2020),(Citation: McAfee REvil October 2019),(Citation: Tetra Defense Sodinokibi March 2020),(Citation: Talos Sodinokibi April 2019),(Citation: Secureworks GandCrab and REvil September 2019),(Citation: Secureworks REvil September 2019),(Citation: G Data Sodinokibi June 2019),(Citation: Picus Sodinokibi January 2020),(Citation: BleepingComputer REvil 2021),(Citation: McAfee Sodinokibi October 2019),(Citation: Cylance Sodinokibi July 2019),(Citation: Kaspersky Sodin July 2019)
description_zh: [REVIL]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0496）是一个勒索软件，已链接到[Gold Southfield]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0115）至少自2019年4月以来，勒索软件-AS-A-Service（RAAS）。扇区高度可配置，并与Gandcrab Raas共享代码相似之处。

name: RGDoor
description: [RGDoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0258) is a malicious Internet Information Services (IIS) backdoor developed in the C++ language. [RGDoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0258) has been seen deployed on webservers belonging to the Middle East government organizations. [RGDoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0258) provides backdoor access to compromised IIS servers. (Citation: Unit 42 RGDoor Jan 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 RGDoor Jan 2018),,(Citation: ESET IIS Malware 2021),(Citation: Unit 42 RGDoor Jan 2018)
description_zh: [rgdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0258）是一种恶意的Internet信息服务（IIS），以C ++语言开发。 [rgdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0258）已被看到在属于中东政府组织的Web服务器上。 [rgdoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0258）提供了可折衷IIS服务器的后门访问。 （引用：2018年1月42日RGDOOR单元）

name: RIPTIDE
description: [RIPTIDE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0003) is a proxy-aware backdoor used by [APT12](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0005). (Citation: Moran 2014)
relationship citations: (Citation: Moran 2014),,(Citation: Moran 2014)
description_zh: [riptide]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0003）是[apt12]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/ggroups/g0005）使用的代理-Aware Backdoor。 （引文：Moran 2014）

name: ROADTools
description: [ROADTools](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0684) is a framework for enumerating Azure Active Directory environments. The tool is written in Python and publicly available on GitHub.(Citation: ROADtools Github)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Oct 2021),,(Citation: Roadtools)
description_zh: [ROADTOOLS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0684）是枚举Azure Active Directory环境的框架。该工具用Python编写，并在GitHub上公开可用。（引用：RoadTools Github）

name: ROCKBOOT
description: [ROCKBOOT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0112) is a [Bootkit](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1542/003) that has been used by an unidentified, suspected China-based group. (Citation: FireEye Bootkits)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),,(Citation: FireEye Bootkits)
description_zh: [rockboot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0112）是[bootkit]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/techniques/t1542/003） - 基于组。 （引文：FireEye Bootkits）

name: ROKRAT
description: [ROKRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0240) is a cloud-based remote access tool (RAT) used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067) to target victims in South Korea. [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067) has used ROKRAT during several campaigns from 2016 through 2021.(Citation: Talos ROKRAT)(Citation: Talos Group123)(Citation: Volexity InkySquid RokRAT August 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Talos Group123),(Citation: Securelist ScarCruft May 2019),,(Citation: Volexity InkySquid RokRAT August 2021),(Citation: Malwarebytes RokRAT VBA January 2021),(Citation: Securelist ScarCruft May 2019),(Citation: NCCGroup RokRat Nov 2018),(Citation: Talos ROKRAT),(Citation: Talos Group123),(Citation: Talos ROKRAT 2)
description_zh: [rokrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0240）是[APT37]使用的基于云的远程访问工具（Rat）（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0067）to韩国的目标受害者。 [APT37]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）在2016年至2021年的几项活动中使用了Rokrat。

name: RTM
description: [RTM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0148) is custom malware written in Delphi. It is used by the group of the same name ([RTM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0048)). Newer versions of the malware have been reported publicly as Redaman.(Citation: ESET RTM Feb 2017)(Citation: Unit42 Redaman January 2019)
contributors: Arie Olshtein, Check Point; Kobi Eisenkraft, Check Point
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET RTM Feb 2017),,(Citation: CheckPoint Redaman October 2019),(Citation: Unit42 Redaman January 2019),(Citation: ESET RTM Feb 2017)
description_zh: [RTM]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0148）是用Delphi编写的自定义恶意软件。它由同名组（[rtm]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0048））使用。较新的恶意软件版本已公开报道为Redaman。

name: Ragnar Locker
description: [Ragnar Locker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0481) is a ransomware that has been in use since at least December 2019.(Citation: Sophos Ragnar May 2020)(Citation: Cynet Ragnar Apr 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FBI Ragnar Locker 2020),(Citation: Cynet Ragnar Apr 2020),(Citation: Sophos Ragnar May 2020)
description_zh: [ragnar locker]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0481）是一种勒索软件，至少自2019年12月以来一直在使用。

name: Raindrop
description: [Raindrop](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0565) is a loader used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) that was discovered on some victim machines during investigations related to the 2020 SolarWinds cyber intrusion. It was discovered in January 2021 and was likely used since at least May 2020.(Citation: Symantec RAINDROP January 2021)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),(Citation: Symantec RAINDROP January 2021),,(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021),(Citation: Symantec RAINDROP January 2021)
description_zh: [raindrop]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0565）是[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的装载机，在调查中在某些受害者机器上发现与2020年的太阳能网络侵入有关。它是在2021年1月发现的，至少从2020年5月开始使用。

name: RainyDay
description: [RainyDay](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0629) is a backdoor tool that has been used by [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019) since at least 2020.(Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021),,(Citation: Bitdefender Naikon April 2021)
description_zh: [Rainyday]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0629）是[Naikon]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0019）以来至少至少2020年使用的后期工具。 （引文：Bitdefender Naikon 2021年4月）

name: Ramsay
description: [Ramsay](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0458) is an information stealing malware framework designed to collect and exfiltrate sensitive documents, including from air-gapped systems. Researchers have identified overlaps between [Ramsay](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0458) and the [Darkhotel](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0012)-associated Retro malware.(Citation: Eset Ramsay May 2020)(Citation: Antiy CERT Ramsay April 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Eset Ramsay May 2020),(Citation: Antiy CERT Ramsay April 2020)
description_zh: [ramsay]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0458）是一个信息，旨在窃取旨在收集和剥离敏感文档的恶意软件框架，包括来自空调系统。研究人员已经确定了[Ramsay]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0458）与[Darkhhotel]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0012） -  retro Malware。 ：Eset Ramsay 2020年5月）（引文：Antiy Cert Ramsay 2020年4月）

name: RawDisk
description: [RawDisk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0364) is a legitimate commercial driver from the EldoS Corporation that is used for interacting with files, disks, and partitions. The driver allows for direct modification of data on a local computer's hard drive. In some cases, the tool can enact these raw disk modifications from user-mode processes, circumventing Windows operating system security features.(Citation: EldoS RawDisk ITpro)(Citation: Novetta Blockbuster Destructive Malware)
relationship citations: (Citation: Novetta Blockbuster),(Citation: Novetta Blockbuster Destructive Malware),,(Citation: Unit 42 Shamoon3 2018),(Citation: Palo Alto Shamoon Nov 2016),(Citation: Novetta Blockbuster Destructive Malware)
description_zh: [RAWDISK]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0364）是Eldos Corporation的合法商业驱动程序，用于与文件，磁盘和分区进行交互。该驱动程序允许在本地计算机的硬盘驱动器上直接修改数据。在某些情况下，该工具可以从用户模式进程中进行这些原始磁盘修改，从而规避Windows操作系统安全功能。

name: RawPOS
description: [RawPOS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0169) is a point-of-sale (POS) malware family that searches for cardholder data on victims. It has been in use since at least 2008. (Citation: Kroll RawPOS Jan 2017) (Citation: TrendMicro RawPOS April 2015) (Citation: Visa RawPOS March 2015) FireEye divides RawPOS into three components: FIENDCRY, DUEBREW, and DRIFTWOOD. (Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016) (Citation: DarkReading FireEye FIN5 Oct 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: DarkReading FireEye FIN5 Oct 2015),(Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016),,(Citation: Visa RawPOS March 2015),(Citation: Kroll RawPOS Jan 2017),(Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016),(Citation: TrendMicro RawPOS April 2015)
description_zh: [RAWPOS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0169）是一个点销售（POS）恶意软件家族，可搜索受害者的持卡人数据。它至少从2008年开始就一直在使用。（引用：Kroll Rawpos 2017年1月）（引文：TrendMicro Rawpos 2015年4月）（引用：Visa Rawpos 2015年3月）FireEeye将RAWPOS分为三个组成部分：FiendCry，Dueendbrew，Duebrew和Driftwood。 （引用：Mandiant Fin5 GRRCON 2016年10月）（引文：Darkreading Fireeye Fin5 2015年10月）

name: Rclone
description: [Rclone](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1040) is a command line program for syncing files with cloud storage services such as Dropbox, Google Drive, Amazon S3, and MEGA. [Rclone](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1040) has been used in a number of ransomware campaigns, including those associated with the [Conti](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0575) and DarkSide Ransomware-as-a-Service operations.(Citation: Rclone)(Citation: Rclone Wars)(Citation: Detecting Rclone)(Citation: DarkSide Ransomware Gang)(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021),(Citation: DFIR Conti Bazar Nov 2021),(Citation: Rclone)
description_zh: [rclone]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1040）是一个命令行程序，用于将文件与云存储服务（例如Dropbox，Google Drive，Amazon S3和Mega）同步。 [rclone]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1040）已在许多勒索软件广告系列中使用，包括与[conti]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/software/s0575575） ）和Darkside Ransomware-AS-A-Service操作。（引用：RCLONE）（引用：RCLONE WARS）（引用：检测RCLONE）（引用：Darkside Ransomware Gang）（引用：DFIR Conti Bazar，2021年11月2021年）

name: Reaver
description: [Reaver](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0172) is a malware family that has been in the wild since at least late 2016. Reporting indicates victims have primarily been associated with the "Five Poisons," which are movements the Chinese government considers dangerous. The type of malware is rare due to its final payload being in the form of [Control Panel](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1218/002) items.(Citation: Palo Alto Reaver Nov 2017)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Palo Alto Reaver Nov 2017)
description_zh: [Reaver]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0172）是一个恶意软件家庭，至少从2016年下半年开始就一直在野外。报告表明受害者主要与“五个毒药”有关中国政府的行动认为危险。恶意软件的类型很少，因为其最终有效载荷的形式为[控制面板]（https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/t1218/002）项目。

name: RedLeaves
description: [RedLeaves](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0153) is a malware family used by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045). The code overlaps with [PlugX](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0013) and may be based upon the open source tool Trochilus. (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017) (Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: DOJ APT10 Dec 2018),,(Citation: PWC Cloud Hopper Technical Annex April 2017),(Citation: Accenture Hogfish April 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017)
description_zh: [redleaves]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0153）是[menupass]使用的恶意软件系列（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0045）。代码与[Punpurex]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0013）重叠，并且可能基于开源工具Trochilus。 （引文：PWC Cloud Hopper技术附件2017年4月）（引文：FireEye APT10 2017年4月10日）

name: Reg
description:
[Reg](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0075) is a Windows utility used to interact with the Windows Registry. It can be used at the command-line interface to query, add, modify, and remove information. (Citation: Microsoft Reg)

Utilities such as [Reg](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0075) are known to be used by persistent threats. (Citation: Windows Commands JPCERT)
relationship citations: (Citation: Rancor Unit42 June 2018),(Citation: US-CERT TA18-074A),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: Cybereason Soft Cell June 2019),(Citation: McAfee Honeybee),(Citation: Pentestlab Stored Credentials),(Citation: Microsoft Reg)
description_zh:
[reg]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0075）是Windows实用程序，用于与Windows注册表进行交互。它可以在命令行接口上使用，以查询，添加，修改和删除信息。 （引文：Microsoft Reg）

诸如[reg]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0075）之类的实用程序已被持续威胁使用。 （引用：Windows命令JPCERT）

name: RegDuke
description: [RegDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0511) is a first stage implant written in .NET and used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2017. [RegDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0511) has been used to control a compromised machine when control of other implants on the machine was lost.(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019),,(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
description_zh: [regduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0511）是第一个植入物，以.NET为.NET并使用[APT29]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0016），因为至少2017年。[regduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0511）已被用于控制机器的折衷机器。（引用：Eset Dukes 2019年10月）

name: Regin
description: [Regin](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0019) is a malware platform that has targeted victims in a range of industries, including telecom, government, and financial institutions. Some [Regin](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0019) timestamps date back to 2003. (Citation: Kaspersky Regin)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Kaspersky Regin)
description_zh: [Regin]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0019）是一个恶意软件平台，针对包括电信，政府和金融机构在内的一系列行业中的受害者。一些[Regin]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0019）时间戳可以追溯到2003年。（引用：Kaspersky Regin）

name: Remcos
description: [Remcos](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0332) is a closed-source tool that is marketed as a remote control and surveillance software by a company called Breaking Security. [Remcos](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0332) has been observed being used in malware campaigns.(Citation: Riskiq Remcos Jan 2018)(Citation: Talos Remcos Aug 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit 42 Gorgon Group Aug 2018),(Citation: MalwareBytes LazyScripter Feb 2021),(Citation: ESET Operation Spalax Jan 2021),(Citation: Fortinet Remcos Feb 2017),(Citation: Talos Remcos Aug 2018),(Citation: Riskiq Remcos Jan 2018)
description_zh: [remcos]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0332）是一种封闭的源工具，由一家名为Breaking Security的公司作为遥控器和监视软件销售。 [REMCOS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0332）已在恶意软件活动中使用。

name: Remexi
description: [Remexi](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0375) is a Windows-based Trojan that was developed in the C programming language.(Citation: Securelist Remexi Jan 2019)

description_zh: [remexi]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0375）是一种基于Windows的特洛伊木马，是在C编程语言中开发的。

name: RemoteCMD
description: [RemoteCMD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0166) is a custom tool used by [APT3](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0022) to execute commands on a remote system similar to SysInternal's PSEXEC functionality. (Citation: Symantec Buckeye)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Buckeye),,(Citation: Symantec Buckeye)

name: RemoteUtilities
description: [RemoteUtilities](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0592) is a legitimate remote administration tool that has been used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069) since at least 2021 for execution on target machines.(Citation: Trend Micro Muddy Water March 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Muddy Water March 2021),,(Citation: Trend Micro Muddy Water March 2021)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0592）是一种合法的远程管理工具，已由[muddywater]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0069）起来2021年在目标机器上执行。

name: Remsec
description: [Remsec](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0125) is a modular backdoor that has been used by [Strider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0041) and appears to have been designed primarily for espionage purposes. Many of its modules are written in Lua. (Citation: Symantec Strider Blog)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky ProjectSauron Blog),(Citation: Symantec Strider Blog),,(Citation: Kaspersky ProjectSauron Full Report),(Citation: Symantec Remsec IOCs),(Citation: Kaspersky ProjectSauron Technical Analysis)

name: Responder
description: Responder is an open source tool used for LLMNR, NBT-NS and MDNS poisoning, with built-in HTTP/SMB/MSSQL/FTP/LDAP rogue authentication server supporting NTLMv1/NTLMv2/LMv2, Extended Security NTLMSSP and Basic HTTP authentication. (Citation: GitHub Responder)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT28 Hospitality Aug 2017),(Citation: ClearSky Lazarus Aug 2020),(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018),,(Citation: GitHub Responder)
description_zh: RESTONDER是一种用于LLMNR，NBT-NS和MDNS中毒的开源工具，内置的HTTP/SMB/MSSQL/MSSQL/FTP/LDAP ROGUE AUTHENTICATION SERVER支持NTLMV1/NTLMV1/NTLMV2/LMV2，Extended Security NTLMSSP和基本的HTTP Autentication。 （引用：github响应者）

name: Revenge RAT
description: [Revenge RAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0379) is a freely available remote access tool written in .NET (C#).(Citation: Cylance Shaheen Nov 2018)(Citation: Cofense RevengeRAT Feb 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cylance Shaheen Nov 2018),,(Citation: Cofense RevengeRAT Feb 2019),(Citation: Cylance Shaheen Nov 2018)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0379）是一种免费的远程访问工具（c＃）。

name: Rifdoor
description: [Rifdoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0433) is a remote access trojan (RAT) that shares numerous code similarities with [HotCroissant](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0431).(Citation: Carbon Black HotCroissant April 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: AhnLab Andariel Subgroup of Lazarus June 2018),,(Citation: Carbon Black HotCroissant April 2020)

name: Rising Sun
description: [Rising Sun](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0448) is a modular backdoor that was used extensively in [Operation Sharpshooter](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0013) between 2017 and 2019. [Rising Sun](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0448) infected at least 87 organizations around the world, including nuclear, defense, energy, and financial service companies. Security researchers assessed [Rising Sun](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0448) included some source code from [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032)'s Trojan Duuzer.(Citation: McAfee Sharpshooter December 2018)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Bleeping Computer Op Sharpshooter March 2019),(Citation: McAfee Sharpshooter December 2018),(Citation: Bleeping Computer Op Sharpshooter March 2019),(Citation: McAfee Sharpshooter December 2018)
description_zh: [Rising Sun](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0448) is a modular backdoor that was used extensively in [Operation Sharpshooter](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0013) between 2017 and 2019年。[Rising Sun]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0448）感染了全球至少87个组织，包括核，国防，能源和金融服务公司。安全研究人员评估了[Rising Sun]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0448）包括[Lazarus Group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0032）的一些源代码。（引文：McAfee神枪手2018年12月）

name: RobbinHood
description: [RobbinHood](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0400) is ransomware that was first observed being used in an attack against the Baltimore city government's computer network.(Citation: CarbonBlack RobbinHood May 2019)(Citation: BaltimoreSun RobbinHood May 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: CarbonBlack RobbinHood May 2019)
description_zh: [Robbinood]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0400）是勒索软件，首先被观察到用于针对巴尔的摩市政府的计算机网络的攻击（引用：Carbonblack Robbinhood 2019年5月） 2019年5月）

name: RogueRobin
description: [RogueRobin](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0270) is a payload used by [DarkHydrus](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0079) that has been developed in PowerShell and C#. (Citation: Unit 42 DarkHydrus July 2018)(Citation: Unit42 DarkHydrus Jan 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Unit42 DarkHydrus Jan 2019),(Citation: Unit 42 DarkHydrus July 2018),,(Citation: Unit42 DarkHydrus Jan 2019),(Citation: GitHub Invoke-Obfuscation),(Citation: Unit 42 DarkHydrus July 2018)

name: Rover
description: [Rover](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0090) is malware suspected of being used for espionage purposes. It was used in 2015 in a targeted email sent to an Indian Ambassador to Afghanistan. (Citation: Palo Alto Rover)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Palo Alto Rover)
description_zh: [ROVER]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0090）是涉嫌用于间谍活动的恶意软件。它于2015年在发送给印度大使到阿富汗的有针对性电子邮件中使用。 （引文：帕洛阿尔托·罗弗）

name: Ruler
description: [Ruler](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0358) is a tool to abuse Microsoft Exchange services. It is publicly available on GitHub and the tool is executed via the command line. The creators of [Ruler](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0358) have also released a defensive tool, NotRuler, to detect its usage.(Citation: SensePost Ruler GitHub)(Citation: SensePost NotRuler)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT33 Guardrail),(Citation: Microsoft Holmium June 2020),,(Citation: SensePost Ruler GitHub)
description_zh: [标尺]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0358）是滥用Microsoft Exchange服务的工具。它在GitHub上公开可用，该工具通过命令行执行。 [标尺]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0358）的创建者还发布了一种防御工具，即Notruler，以检测其用法。

name: RunningRAT
description: [RunningRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0253) is a remote access tool that appeared in operations surrounding the 2018 Pyeongchang Winter Olympics along with [Gold Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0249) and [Brave Prince](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0252). (Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: McAfee Gold Dragon)
description_zh: [RunningRat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0253）是一种远程访问工具，出现在2018 Pyeongchang Winter Olympics周围的运营中，以及[Gold Dragon]（https://attack.mitre.orgg/）软件/S0249）和[Brave Prince]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0252）。 （引文：McAfee Gold Dragon）

name: Ryuk
description: [Ryuk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0446) is a ransomware designed to target enterprise environments that has been used in attacks since at least 2018. [Ryuk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0446) shares code similarities with Hermes ransomware.(Citation: CrowdStrike Ryuk January 2019)(Citation: FireEye Ryuk and Trickbot January 2019)(Citation: FireEye FIN6 Apr 2019)
contributors: Matt Brenton, Zurich Insurance Group; The DFIR Report, @TheDFIRReport
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike Ryuk January 2019),(Citation: FireEye FIN6 Apr 2019),(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: Sophos New Ryuk Attack October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk 2 Hour Speed Run November 2020),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk in 5 Hours October 2020),(Citation: FireEye KEGTAP SINGLEMALT October 2020),(Citation: DHS/CISA Ransomware Targeting Healthcare October 2020),(Citation: Red Canary Hospital Thwarted Ryuk October 2020),(Citation: DFIR Ryuk's Return October 2020),,(Citation: CrowdStrike Ryuk January 2019),(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: Bleeping Computer - Ryuk WoL),(Citation: ANSSI RYUK RANSOMWARE),(Citation: FireEye Ryuk and Trickbot January 2019)
description_zh: [ryuk]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0446）是一种勒索软件，旨在针对自2018年以来一直在攻击中使用的企业环境。 /software/s0446）与爱马仕勒索软件分享代码相似性。

name: S-Type
description: [S-Type](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0085) is a backdoor that was used in [Operation Dust Storm](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0016) since at least 2013.(Citation: Cylance Dust Storm)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Cylance Dust Storm),(Citation: Microsoft DTC),(Citation: Cylance Dust Storm)

name: SDBbot
description: [SDBbot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0461) is a backdoor with installer and loader components that has been used by [TA505](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0092) since at least 2019.(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019)(Citation: IBM TA505 April 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: IBM TA505 April 2020),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019),,(Citation: Korean FSI TA505 2020),(Citation: IBM TA505 April 2020),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 October 2019)
description_zh: [sdbbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0461）是一个备份器和安装程序和加载程序组件，自从[ta505]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/groups/g0092）已使用，此后已使用。至少2019年。（引文：2019年10月5日PRICKPOINT TA505）（引文：IBM TA505 2020年4月5日）

name: SDelete
description: [SDelete](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0195) is an application that securely deletes data in a way that makes it unrecoverable. It is part of the Microsoft Sysinternals suite of tools. (Citation: Microsoft SDelete July 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: PTSecurity Cobalt Dec 2016),(Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016),(Citation: Group IB Silence Sept 2018),(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach),,(Citation: Microsoft SDelete July 2016)
description_zh: [sdelete]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0195）是一个应用程序，以使其无法恢复的方式安全地删除数据。它是Microsoft Sysinternals工具套件的一部分。 （引文：Microsoft Sdelete 2016年7月）

name: SEASHARPEE
description: [SEASHARPEE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0185) is a Web shell that has been used by [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049). (Citation: FireEye APT34 Webinar Dec 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT34 Webinar Dec 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT34 Webinar Dec 2017)
description_zh: [seasharpee]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0185）是[oilrig]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0049）已使用的网络外壳。 （引文：FireEye APT34网络研讨会2017年12月）

name: SHARPSTATS
description: [SHARPSTATS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0450) is a .NET backdoor used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069) since at least 2019.(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019),,(Citation: TrendMicro POWERSTATS V3 June 2019)
description_zh: [SharpStats]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0450）是[muddywater]（https：//attack.mitre.org/groups/g0069）使用的.NET Backdoor，因为至少至少2019年。（引用：TrendMicro Powerstats v3 2019年6月）

name: SHIPSHAPE
description: [SHIPSHAPE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0028) is malware developed by [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) that allows propagation and exfiltration of data over removable devices. [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) may use this capability to exfiltrate data across air-gaps. (Citation: FireEye APT30)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT30),,(Citation: FireEye APT30)
description_zh: [shipshape]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0028）是[apt30]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0013）开发的恶意软件。 [apt30]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0013）可以使用此功能在气隙上驱除数据。 （引文：FireEye APT30）

name: SHOTPUT
description: [SHOTPUT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0063) is a custom backdoor used by [APT3](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0022). (Citation: FireEye Clandestine Wolf)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye Clandestine Wolf),,(Citation: Palo Alto CVE-2015-3113 July 2015),(Citation: FireEye Clandestine Wolf)
description_zh: [shotput]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0063）是[apt3]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0022）使用的自定义后门。 （引文：FireEye秘密狼）

name: SHUTTERSPEED
description: [SHUTTERSPEED](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0217) is a backdoor used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067). (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018),,(Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)

name: SILENTTRINITY
description: [SILENTTRINITY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0692) is an open source remote administration and post-exploitation framework primarily written in Python that includes stagers written in Powershell, C, and Boo. [SILENTTRINITY](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0692) was used in a 2019 campaign against Croatian government agencies by unidentified cyber actors.(Citation: GitHub SILENTTRINITY March 2022)(Citation: Security Affairs SILENTTRINITY July 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: GitHub SILENTTRINITY Modules July 2019),(Citation: Security Affairs SILENTTRINITY July 2019),(Citation: GitHub SILENTTRINITY March 2022)
description_zh: [silenttrinity]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0692）是一个开源远程管理和主要示例框架，主要用python编写，其中包括powershell，c和boo的stagers。 [silenttrinity]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0692）在2019年针对克罗地亚政府机构的运动中使用了身份不明的网络演员。

name: SLOTHFULMEDIA
description:
[SLOTHFULMEDIA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0533) is a remote access Trojan written in C++ that has been used by an unidentified "sophisticated cyber actor" since at least January 2017.(Citation: CISA MAR SLOTHFULMEDIA October 2020)(Citation: Costin Raiu IAmTheKing October 2020) It has been used to target government organizations, defense contractors, universities, and energy companies in Russia, India, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Malaysia, Ukraine, and Eastern Europe.(Citation: USCYBERCOM SLOTHFULMEDIA October 2020)(Citation: Kaspersky IAmTheKing October 2020)  

In October 2020, Kaspersky Labs assessed [SLOTHFULMEDIA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0533) is part of an activity cluster it refers to as "IAmTheKing".(Citation: Kaspersky IAmTheKing October 2020) ESET also noted code similarity between [SLOTHFULMEDIA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0533) and droppers used by a group it refers to as "PowerPool".(Citation: ESET PowerPool Code October 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: CISA MAR SLOTHFULMEDIA October 2020)
description_zh:
[SlothfulMedia]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0533）是一款远程访问，以C ++编写的Trojan，至少从2017年1月开始就被一个身份不明的“复杂的网络演员”使用。（引文：Cisa Mar Slothmedia Slothmedia 2020年10月）（引文：Costin raiu iamtheking 2020年10月）它已用于针对政府组织，国防承包商，大学和能源公司，印度，哈萨克斯坦，吉尔吉斯斯坦，马来西亚，乌克兰，乌克兰和东欧。 Slothfulmedia 2020年10月）（引文：Kaspersky Iamtheking 2020年10月）

2020年10月，Kaspersky Labs评估[SlothfulMedia]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0533）是活动群集的一部分，它称为“ iamtheking”。 [slothfulmedia]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0533）和一个小组使用的滴管之间的代码相似性。

name: SLOWDRIFT
description: [SLOWDRIFT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0218) is a backdoor used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067) against academic and strategic victims in South Korea. (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018),,(Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
description_zh: [slowdrift]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0218）是[apt37]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0067）使用的后门，以对付韩国的学术和战略受害者。 （引文：FireEye APT37 2018年2月）

name: SMOKEDHAM
description: [SMOKEDHAM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0649) is a Powershell-based .NET backdoor that was first reported in May 2021; it has been used by at least one ransomware-as-a-service affiliate.(Citation: FireEye Shining A Light on DARKSIDE May 2021)(Citation: FireEye SMOKEDHAM June 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FireEye SMOKEDHAM June 2021),(Citation: FireEye Shining A Light on DARKSIDE May 2021)
description_zh: [Smokedham]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0649）是一个基于PowerShell的.NET后门，于2021年5月首次报道；它已被至少一个勒索软件 - 服务分支机构使用。

name: SNUGRIDE
description: [SNUGRIDE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0159) is a backdoor that has been used by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045) as first stage malware. (Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT10 April 2017)
description_zh: [snugride]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0159）是[menupass]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0045）已使用的后门。 （引文：FireEye APT10 2017年4月10日）

name: SOUNDBITE
description: [SOUNDBITE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0157) is a signature backdoor used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050). (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
description_zh: [soundbite]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0157）是[APT32]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0050）使用的签名后门。 （引文：FireEye APT32 2017年5月）

name: SPACESHIP
description: [SPACESHIP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0035) is malware developed by [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) that allows propagation and exfiltration of data over removable devices. [APT30](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0013) may use this capability to exfiltrate data across air-gaps. (Citation: FireEye APT30)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT30),,(Citation: FireEye APT30)
description_zh: [SpaceHip]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0035）是[apt30]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.groups/g0013）的[） 。 [apt30]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0013）可以使用此功能在气隙上驱除数据。 （引文：FireEye APT30）

name: SQLRat
description: [SQLRat](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0390) is malware that executes SQL scripts to avoid leaving traditional host artifacts. [FIN7](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0046) has been observed using it.(Citation: Flashpoint FIN 7 March 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Flashpoint FIN 7 March 2019),,(Citation: Flashpoint FIN 7 March 2019)
description_zh: [sqlrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0390）是恶意软件，可以执行SQL脚本以避免留下传统的主机伪像。 [FIN7]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0046）已使用它。（引用：Flashpoint Fin 2019年3月7日）

name: STARWHALE
description: [STARWHALE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1037) is Windows Script File (WSF) backdoor that has been used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069), possibly since at least November 2021; there is also a [STARWHALE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1037) variant written in Golang with similar capabilities. Security researchers have also noted the use of [STARWHALE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1037) by UNC3313, which may be associated with [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069).(Citation: Mandiant UNC3313 Feb 2022)(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022),,(Citation: Mandiant UNC3313 Feb 2022),(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)
description_zh: [starwhale]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1037）是Windows脚本文件（WSF）backdoor，已由[muddywater]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.orgroups/g0069），，可能至少是2021年11月以来；还有一个[星际]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1037）具有类似功能的Golang。安全研究人员还指出，UNK3313的使用[Starwhale]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1037），可能与[muddywater]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/- G0069）。

name: SUGARDUMP
description: [SUGARDUMP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1042) is a proprietary browser credential harvesting tool that was used by UNC3890 during the [C0010](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0010) campaign. The first known [SUGARDUMP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1042) version was used since at least early 2021, a second SMTP C2 version was used from late 2021-early 2022, and a third HTTP C2 variant was used since at least April 2022.(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022),(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022)
description_zh: [sugardump]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1042）是一种专有的浏览器凭证收获工具，在[C0010]期间使用了UNC3890（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org.org.org/campaigns/c0010）使用，它使用活动。自从至少2021年初以来，使用了第一个已知的[Sugardump]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1042）版本至少从2022年4月开始使用（引用：Mandiant UNC3890 2022年8月）

name: SUGARUSH
description: [SUGARUSH](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1049) is a small custom backdoor that can establish a reverse shell over TCP to a hard coded C2 address. [SUGARUSH](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1049) was first identified during analysis of UNC3890's [C0010](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0010) campaign targeting Israeli companies, which began in late 2020.(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022),(Citation: Mandiant UNC3890 Aug 2022)
description_zh: [Sugarush]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1049）是一个小的自定义后门，可以通过TCP建立反向外壳，以将其换成硬编码的C2地址。 [sugarush]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1049）在分析UND3890的[C0010]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/campaigns/c0010）中首先确定2020年下半年。（引用：Mandiant UNC3890 2022年8月）

name: SUNBURST
description: [SUNBURST](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0559) is a trojanized DLL designed to fit within the SolarWinds Orion software update framework. It was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least February 2020.(Citation: SolarWinds Sunburst Sunspot Update January 2021)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
contributors: Daniyal Naeem, BT Security; Matt Brenton, Zurich Insurance Group
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020),(Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM May 2021),,(Citation: Symantec Sunburst Sending Data January 2021),(Citation: Microsoft Analyzing Solorigate Dec 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike SUNSPOT Implant January 2021),(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021),(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Additional Details Dec 2020),(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)
description_zh: [sunburst]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0559）是一款旨在适合Solarwinds Orion Orion软件更新框架中的Trojanized DLL。自2020年2月以来，[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用它。（引用：Solarwinds Sunburst Sunspot 2021年1月更新）

name: SUNSPOT
description: [SUNSPOT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0562) is an implant that injected the [SUNBURST](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0559) backdoor into the SolarWinds Orion software update framework. It was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least February 2020.(Citation: CrowdStrike SUNSPOT Implant January 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike SUNSPOT Implant January 2021),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),,(Citation: CrowdStrike SUNSPOT Implant January 2021)
description_zh: [sunspot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0562）是一种植入物，它注入[Sunburst]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/s0559）backdoor中。至少至少2020年2月以来，[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用了它。

name: SUPERNOVA
description: [SUPERNOVA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0578) is an in-memory web shell written in .NET C#. It was discovered in November 2020 during the investigation of [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016)'s SolarWinds cyber operation but determined to be unrelated. Subsequent analysis suggests [SUPERNOVA](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0578) may have been used by the China-based threat group SPIRAL.(Citation: Guidepoint SUPERNOVA Dec 2020)(Citation: Unit42 SUPERNOVA Dec 2020)(Citation: SolarWinds Advisory Dec 2020)(Citation: CISA Supernova Jan 2021)(Citation: Microsoft Analyzing Solorigate Dec 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit42 SUPERNOVA Dec 2020),(Citation: Splunk Supernova Jan 2021),(Citation: Guidepoint SUPERNOVA Dec 2020),(Citation: Carnegie Mellon University Supernova Dec 2020),(Citation: CISA Supernova Jan 2021)
description_zh: [supernova]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0578）是用.NET C＃编写的内存网络外壳。它是在2020年11月对[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）的调查中发现的。随后的分析表明[Supernova]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0578）可能已被总部位于中国的威胁集团螺旋式螺旋形所使用。 （引文：Solarwinds咨询2020年12月）（引文：CISA Supernova 2021年1月）（引用：Microsoft分析Solorigate 2020年12月）

name: SYNful Knock
description: [SYNful Knock](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0519) is a stealthy modification of the operating system of network devices that can be used to maintain persistence within a victim's network and provide new capabilities to the adversary.(Citation: Mandiant - Synful Knock)(Citation: Cisco Synful Knock Evolution)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Cisco Synful Knock Evolution),(Citation: Mandiant - Synful Knock)
description_zh: [Synful敲门]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0519）是对网络设备操作系统的隐身修改，可用于维持受害者网络中的持久性并为对手提供新的功能。引用：强度 - 同步敲击）（引文：思科同步敲门演变）

name: SYSCON
description: [SYSCON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0464) is a backdoor that has been in use since at least 2017 and has been associated with campaigns involving North Korean themes. [SYSCON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0464) has been delivered by the [CARROTBALL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0465) and [CARROTBAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0462) droppers.(Citation: Unit 42 CARROTBAT November 2018)(Citation: Unit 42 CARROTBAT January 2020)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: McAfee Honeybee),(Citation: Unit 42 CARROTBAT January 2020),(Citation: Unit 42 CARROTBAT November 2018)
description_zh: [SYSCON]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0464）是一款后门，至少从2017年开始就一直在使用，并且与涉及朝鲜主题的广告系列有关。 [SYSCON]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0464）已由[carrotball]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0465）和[carrotbat]（https：////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// Attack.mitre.org/software/S0462）滴管。

name: Saint Bot
description: [Saint Bot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1018) is a .NET downloader that has been used by [Ember Bear](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1003) since at least March 2021.(Citation: Malwarebytes Saint Bot April 2021)(Citation: Palo Alto Unit 42 OutSteel SaintBot February 2022 )
relationship citations: (Citation: Palo Alto Unit 42 OutSteel SaintBot February 2022 ),,(Citation: Palo Alto Unit 42 OutSteel SaintBot February 2022 ),(Citation: Malwarebytes Saint Bot April 2021)
description_zh: [SAINT BOT]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1018）是一个.NET下载器，自从[Ember Bear]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g1003）以来已使用至少2021年3月。

name: Sakula
description: [Sakula](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0074) is a remote access tool (RAT) that first surfaced in 2012 and was used in intrusions throughout 2015. (Citation: Dell Sakula)
relationship citations: (Citation: ThreatConnect Anthem),,(Citation: Dell Sakula)
description_zh: [sakula]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0074）是一种远程访问工具（RAT），该工具在2012年首次浮出水面，在整个2015年被用于入侵中。（引用：Dell Sakula）

name: SamSam
description: [SamSam](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0370) is ransomware that appeared in early 2016. Unlike some ransomware, its variants have required operators to manually interact with the malware to execute some of its core components.(Citation: US-CERT SamSam 2018)(Citation: Talos SamSam Jan 2018)(Citation: Sophos SamSam Apr 2018)(Citation: Symantec SamSam Oct 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Talos SamSam Jan 2018),(Citation: Sophos SamSam Apr 2018)
description_zh: [SAMSAM]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0370）是在2016年初出现的勒索软件。与某些勒索软件不同，其变体要求操作员手动与恶意软件进行交互以执行其核心组件（其一些核心组件）（（（引用：US-CERT SAMSAM 2018）（引文：Talos Samsam 2018年1月）（引文：Sophos Samsam 2018年4月）（引用：Symantec Samsam 2018年10月）

name: SeaDuke
description: [SeaDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0053) is malware that was used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) from 2014 to 2015. It was used primarily as a secondary backdoor for victims that were already compromised with [CozyCar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0046). (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),,(Citation: Unit 42 SeaDuke 2015),(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes),(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach),(Citation: Symantec Seaduke 2015),(Citation: FireEye WMI 2015)
description_zh: [Seaduke]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0053）是[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用的恶意软件。主要是已经被[cozycar]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0046）妥协的受害者的次要后门。 （引用：f-secure the dukes）

name: Seasalt
description: [Seasalt](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0345) is malware that has been linked to [APT1](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0006)'s 2010 operations. It shares some code similarities with [OceanSalt](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0346).(Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix)(Citation: McAfee Oceansalt Oct 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: McAfee Oceansalt Oct 2018),(Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix),,(Citation: McAfee Oceansalt Oct 2018),(Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix)
description_zh: [seasalt]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0345）是恶意软件，已链接到[apt1]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0006）2010年的操作。它与[OceanSalt]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0346）共享一些代码相似之处。

name: ServHelper
description: [ServHelper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0382) is a backdoor first observed in late 2018. The backdoor is written in Delphi and is typically delivered as a DLL file.(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro TA505 June 2019),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019),(Citation: Cybereason TA505 April 2019),(Citation: Deep Instinct TA505 Apr 2019),,(Citation: Trend Micro TA505 June 2019),(Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Jan 2019),(Citation: Deep Instinct TA505 Apr 2019)
description_zh: [SERVHELPER]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0382）是2018年底首次观察到的后门。后门是用Delphi编写的，通常以DLL文件交付。

name: Seth-Locker
description:
[Seth-Locker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0639) is a ransomware with some remote control capabilities that has been in use since at least 2021.
(Citation: Trend Micro Ransomware February 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Trend Micro Ransomware February 2021)
description_zh:
[Seth-Locker]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0639）是一种勒索软件，具有一些远程控制功能，至少自2021年以来就一直在使用。
（引文：趋势微勒索软件2021年2月）

name: ShadowPad
description: [ShadowPad](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0596) is a modular backdoor that was first identified in a supply chain compromise of the NetSarang software in mid-July 2017. The malware was originally thought to be exclusively used by [APT41](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0096), but has since been observed to be used by various Chinese threat activity groups. (Citation: Recorded Future RedEcho Feb 2021)(Citation: Securelist ShadowPad Aug 2017)(Citation: Kaspersky ShadowPad Aug 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro EarthLusca 2022),(Citation: Recorded Future RedEcho Feb 2021),(Citation: Kaspersky CactusPete Aug 2020),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019),,(Citation: TrendMicro EarthLusca 2022),(Citation: Securelist ShadowPad Aug 2017),(Citation: Kaspersky ShadowPad Aug 2017),(Citation: FireEye APT41 Aug 2019)
description_zh: [Shadowpad]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0596）是一个模块化后门，在2017年7月中旬在Netsarang软件的供应链中首次确定，最初被认为是专门使用的。作者：[apt41]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0096），但此后已观察到各种中国威胁活动组使用。 （引文：记录的未来Redecho 2021年2月）（引文：Securelist Shadowpad 2017年8月）（引文：Kaspersky Shadowpad 2017年8月）

name: Shamoon
description: [Shamoon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0140) is wiper malware that was first used by an Iranian group known as the "Cutting Sword of Justice" in 2012. Other versions known as Shamoon 2 and Shamoon 3 were observed in 2016 and 2018. [Shamoon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0140) has also been seen leveraging [RawDisk](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0364) and Filerase to carry out data wiping tasks. The term Shamoon is sometimes used to refer to the group using the malware as well as the malware itself.(Citation: Palo Alto Shamoon Nov 2016)(Citation: Unit 42 Shamoon3 2018)(Citation: Symantec Shamoon 2012)(Citation: FireEye Shamoon Nov 2016)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: McAfee Shamoon December19 2018),(Citation: McAfee Shamoon December 2018),(Citation: Unit 42 Shamoon3 2018),(Citation: FireEye Shamoon Nov 2016),(Citation: Symantec Shamoon 2012),(Citation: Palo Alto Shamoon Nov 2016)
description_zh: [Shamoon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0140）是刮水器恶意软件，该恶意软件首先被伊朗人集团使用，即2012年被称为“司法司法剑”。其他称为Shamoon 2和Shamoon 3的版本在2016年和2018年观察到。执行数据擦拭任务。 Shamoon一词有时用于使用恶意软件以及恶意软件本身来参考该小组。（引用：Palo Alto Shamoon 2016年11月）（引用：42 Shamoon 3 2018）（引用：Symantec Shamoon 2012）（引文：Fireeye Shamoon 2016年11月）

name: Shark
description: [Shark](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1019) is a backdoor malware written in C# and .NET that is an updated version of [Milan](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1015); it has been used by [HEXANE](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1001) since at least July 2021.(Citation: ClearSky Siamesekitten August 2021)(Citation: Accenture Lyceum Targets November 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Lyceum October 2021),(Citation: Accenture Lyceum Targets November 2021),,(Citation: ClearSky Siamesekitten August 2021),(Citation: Accenture Lyceum Targets November 2021)
description_zh: [shark]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1019）是用C＃和.NET编写的后门恶意软件，它是[米兰]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/software/ S1015）;至少自2021年7月以来，[hexane]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g1001）使用了它。（引用：Clearsky Siamesekitten 2021年8月）

name: SharpStage
description: [SharpStage](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0546) is a .NET malware with backdoor capabilities.(Citation: Cybereason Molerats Dec 2020)(Citation: BleepingComputer Molerats Dec 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Molerats Dec 2020),,(Citation: Cybereason Molerats Dec 2020),(Citation: BleepingComputer Molerats Dec 2020)
description_zh: [SharpStage]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0546）是带有后门功能的.NET恶意软件。

name: ShimRat
description: [ShimRat](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0444) has been used by the suspected China-based adversary [Mofang](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0103) in campaigns targeting multiple countries and sectors including government, military, critical infrastructure, automobile, and weapons development. The name "[ShimRat](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0444)" comes from the malware's extensive use of Windows Application Shimming to maintain persistence. (Citation: FOX-IT May 2016 Mofang)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FOX-IT May 2016 Mofang)
description_zh: [shimrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0444）已在靶向多个广告系列中使用，可疑的基于中国的对手[Mofang]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0103）国家和部门，包括政府，军事，关键基础设施，汽车和武器开发。名称“ [shimrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0444）”来自恶意软件的广泛使用Windows应用程序以保持持久性。 （引文：福克斯 -  2016年5月Mofang）

name: ShimRatReporter
description: [ShimRatReporter](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0445) is a tool used by suspected Chinese adversary [Mofang](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0103) to automatically conduct initial discovery. The details from this discovery are used to customize follow-on payloads (such as [ShimRat](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0444)) as well as set up faux infrastructure which mimics the adversary's targets. [ShimRatReporter](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0445) has been used in campaigns targeting multiple countries and sectors including government, military, critical infrastructure, automobile, and weapons development.(Citation: FOX-IT May 2016 Mofang)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: FOX-IT May 2016 Mofang)
description_zh: [ShimRatReporter](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0445) is a tool used by suspected Chinese adversary [Mofang](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0103) to automatically conduct initial discovery.该发现的详细信息用于自定义下载有效负载（例如[Shimrat]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s044444444444）），并设置了模拟对手目标的人造基础架构。 [shimratreporter]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0445）已用于针对多个国家和部门的运动，包括政府，军事，关键基础设施，汽车和武器开发。 mofang）

name: Sibot
description: [Sibot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0589) is dual-purpose malware written in VBScript designed to achieve persistence on a compromised system as well as download and execute additional payloads. Microsoft discovered three [Sibot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0589) variants in early 2021 during its investigation of [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) and the SolarWinds cyber intrusion campaign.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021),(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),(Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),,(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)
description_zh: [sibot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0589）是用VBScript编写的双释放恶意软件，旨在实现持久性系统上的持久性以及下载并执行其他有效负载。 Microsoft在2021年初研究[APT29]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/groups/g0016）和Solarwinds时，在2021年初发现了三个[sibot]（https://attps://attps.mitre.org/software/s0589）变体。网络入侵运动。（引文：Mstic Nobelium 2021年3月）

name: SideTwist
description: [SideTwist](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0610) is a C-based backdoor that has been used by [OilRig](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0049) since at least 2021.(Citation: Check Point APT34 April 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Check Point APT34 April 2021),,(Citation: Check Point APT34 April 2021)
description_zh: [SidetWist]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0610）是一种基于C 2021.（引用：Check Point APT34 2021年4月）

name: Siloscape
description: [Siloscape](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0623) is malware that targets Kubernetes clusters through Windows containers. [Siloscape](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0623) was first observed in March 2021.(Citation: Unit 42 Siloscape Jun 2021)
contributors: Daniel Prizmant, Palo Alto Networks; Yuval Avrahami, Palo Alto Networks
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit 42 Siloscape Jun 2021)
description_zh: [siloscape]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0623）是恶意软件，它通过Windows容器靶向Kubernetes簇。 [siloscape]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0623）于2021年3月首次观察。（引用：42单元Siloscape 2021年6月）

name: Skeleton Key
description: [Skeleton Key](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0007) is malware used to inject false credentials into domain controllers with the intent of creating a backdoor password. (Citation: Dell Skeleton) Functionality similar to [Skeleton Key](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0007) is included as a module in [Mimikatz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0002).
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Dell Skeleton)
description_zh: [骨架键]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0007）是恶意软件，用于将false凭据注入域控制器，以创建后门密码。 （引用：戴尔骨架）类似于[骨架键]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0007）的功能作为模块（mimikatz]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/） S0002）。

name: Skidmap
description: [Skidmap](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0468) is a kernel-mode rootkit used for cryptocurrency mining.(Citation: Trend Micro Skidmap)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Trend Micro Skidmap)
description_zh: [skidmap]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0468）是用于加密货币挖掘的内核 - 摩德rootkit。（引用：趋势微型SkidMap）

name: Sliver
description: [Sliver](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0633) is an open source, cross-platform, red team command and control framework written in Golang.(Citation: Bishop Fox Sliver Framework August 2019)
contributors: Achute Sharma, Keysight; Ayan Saha, Keysight
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: Secureworks IRON HEMLOCK Profile),,(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: GitHub Sliver HTTP),(Citation: GitHub Sliver File System August 2021),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Ifconfig),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Download),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Netstat),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Upload),(Citation: GitHub Sliver C2),(Citation: GitHub Sliver C2 DNS),(Citation: Bishop Fox Sliver Framework August 2019),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Screen),(Citation: GitHub Sliver Encryption)
description_zh: [sliver]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0633）是开源的，跨平台，红色团队命令和控制框架。

name: Small Sieve
description:
[Small Sieve](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1035) is a Telegram Bot API-based Python backdoor that has been distributed using a Nullsoft Scriptable Install System (NSIS) Installer; it has been used by [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069) since at least January 2022.(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)(Citation: NCSC GCHQ Small Sieve Jan 2022)

Security researchers have also noted [Small Sieve](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1035)'s use by UNC3313, which may be associated with [MuddyWater](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0069).(Citation: Mandiant UNC3313 Feb 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCSC GCHQ Small Sieve Jan 2022),(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022),,(Citation: NCSC GCHQ Small Sieve Jan 2022),(Citation: DHS CISA AA22-055A MuddyWater February 2022)
description_zh:
[小筛]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1035）是一种基于电报的基于机器人API的Python Backdoor，已使用Nullsoft Scriptable Spricalable Sentern Sentern System（NSIS）安装程序进行分发；至少自2022年1月起，[https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0069）已使用它。 ）

安全研究人员还指出了[Small Sieve]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1035）unc3313的用途可能与[muddywater]（https://attack.mitre.metrre.org/groups）相关/G0069)。（CITIT：MANDIANT UNC3313 2022年2月）

name: Smoke Loader
description:
[Smoke Loader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0226) is a malicious bot application that can be used to load other malware.
[Smoke Loader](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0226) has been seen in the wild since at least 2011 and has included a number of different payloads. It is notorious for its use of deception and self-protection. It also comes with several plug-ins. (Citation: Malwarebytes SmokeLoader 2016) (Citation: Microsoft Dofoil 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Talos Smoke Loader July 2018),(Citation: Microsoft Dofoil 2018),(Citation: Malwarebytes SmokeLoader 2016)
description_zh:
[Smoke Loader]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0226）是一个恶意BOT应用程序，可用于加载其他恶意软件。
[Smoke Loader]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0226）至少从2011年开始就在野外看到，其中包括许多不同的有效载荷。它因使用欺骗和自我保护而臭名昭著。它还带有几个插件。 （引文：Malwarebytes sumeloader 2016）（引文：Microsoft Dofoil 2018）

name: Socksbot
description: [Socksbot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0273) is a backdoor that  abuses Socket Secure (SOCKS) proxies. (Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: TrendMicro Patchwork Dec 2017)

name: SodaMaster
description: [SodaMaster](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0627) is a fileless malware used by [menuPass](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0045) to download and execute payloads since at least 2020.(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021),,(Citation: Securelist APT10 March 2021)

name: SombRAT
description: [SombRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0615) is a modular backdoor written in C++ that has been used since at least 2019 to download and execute malicious payloads, including [FIVEHANDS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0618) ransomware.(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020)(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)(Citation: CISA AR21-126A FIVEHANDS May 2021)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020),(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020),(Citation: CISA AR21-126A FIVEHANDS May 2021),(Citation: FireEye FiveHands April 2021)

description: [SoreFang](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0516) is first stage downloader used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) for exfiltration and to load other malware.(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020),(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016),,(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020),(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016)

name: SpeakUp
description: [SpeakUp](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0374) is a Trojan backdoor that targets both Linux and OSX devices. It was first observed in January 2019. (Citation: CheckPoint SpeakUp Feb 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: CheckPoint SpeakUp Feb 2019)

description: [Squirrelwaffle](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1030) is a loader that was first seen in September 2021. It has been used in spam email campaigns to deliver additional malware such as [Cobalt Strike](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0154) and the [QakBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0650) banking trojan.(Citation: ZScaler Squirrelwaffle Sep 2021)(Citation: Netskope Squirrelwaffle Oct 2021)
contributors: Catherine Williams, BT Security; Harry Hill, BT Security; Sebastian Showell-Westrip, BT Security
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Netskope Squirrelwaffle Oct 2021),(Citation: ZScaler Squirrelwaffle Sep 2021)

name: SslMM
description: [SslMM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0058) is a full-featured backdoor used by [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019) that has multiple variants. (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015)

name: StoneDrill
description: [StoneDrill](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0380) is wiper malware discovered in destructive campaigns against both Middle Eastern and European targets in association with [APT33](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0064).(Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017)(Citation: Kaspersky StoneDrill 2017)

name: StreamEx
description: [StreamEx](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0142) is a malware family that has been used by [Deep Panda](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0009) since at least 2015. In 2016, it was distributed via legitimate compromised Korean websites. (Citation: Cylance Shell Crew Feb 2017)

name: StrifeWater
description: [StrifeWater](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1034) is a remote-access tool that has been used by [Moses Staff](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G1009) in the initial stages of their attacks since at least November 2021.(Citation: Cybereason StrifeWater Feb 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason StrifeWater Feb 2022),,(Citation: Cybereason StrifeWater Feb 2022)

name: StrongPity
description: [StrongPity](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0491) is an information stealing malware used by [PROMETHIUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0056).(Citation: Bitdefender StrongPity June 2020)(Citation: Talos Promethium June 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Bitdefender StrongPity June 2020),(Citation: Talos Promethium June 2020),,(Citation: Talos Promethium June 2020),(Citation: Bitdefender StrongPity June 2020)

name: Stuxnet
description: [Stuxnet](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0603) was the first publicly reported piece of malware to specifically target industrial control systems devices. [Stuxnet](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0603) is a large and complex piece of malware that utilized multiple different behaviors including multiple zero-day vulnerabilities, a sophisticated Windows rootkit, and network infection routines.(Citation: Symantec W.32 Stuxnet Dossier)(Citation: CISA ICS Advisory ICSA-10-272-01)(Citation: ESET Stuxnet Under the Microscope)(Citation: Langer Stuxnet) [Stuxnet](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0603) was discovered in 2010, with some components being used as early as November 2008.(Citation: Symantec W.32 Stuxnet Dossier)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Symantec W.32 Stuxnet Dossier)
description_zh: [stuxnet]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0603）是第一个公开报告的恶意软件，专门针对工业控制系统设备。 [stuxnet]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0603）是一款大型且复杂的恶意软件，它利用了多种不同的行为，包括多个零日漏洞，复杂的Windows Windows rootkit，一个复杂的Windows rootkit和网络感染例程。 ：Symantec W.32 Stuxnet Dossier）（引用：CISA ICS Advisory ICSA-10-272-01）（引用：显微镜下的Eset Stuxnet）（引用：Langer Stuxnet）[stuxnet）[stuxnet] /Software/S0603）于2010年发现，最早在2008年11月使用了一些组件。（引用：Symantec W.32 Stuxnet Dossier）

name: Sykipot
description: [Sykipot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0018) is malware that has been used in spearphishing campaigns since approximately 2007 against victims primarily in the US. One variant of [Sykipot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0018) hijacks smart cards on victims. (Citation: Alienvault Sykipot DOD Smart Cards) The group using this malware has also been referred to as Sykipot. (Citation: Blasco 2013)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: AlienVault Sykipot 2011),(Citation: Blasco 2013),(Citation: Alienvault Sykipot DOD Smart Cards)
description_zh: [sykipot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0018）是恶意软件，自2007年以来，它主要用于美国主要在美国的受害者。 [sykipot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0018）的一种变体劫持了受害者的智能卡。 （引用：Alienvault Sykipot DOD智能卡）使用此恶意软件的组也称为Sykipot。 （引文：Blasco 2013）

description: [SynAck](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0242) is variant of Trojan ransomware targeting mainly English-speaking users since at least fall 2017. (Citation: SecureList SynAck Doppelgänging May 2018) (Citation: Kaspersky Lab SynAck May 2018)

relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021),,(Citation: Trend Micro Iron Tiger April 2021)

name: Systeminfo
description: [Systeminfo](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0096) is a Windows utility that can be used to gather detailed information about a computer. (Citation: TechNet Systeminfo)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016),(Citation: NCC Group APT15 Alive and Strong),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: FireEye admin@338),(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: Symantec Orangeworm April 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: Mandiant Operation Ke3chang November 2014),(Citation: Cybereason OperationCuckooBees May 2022),(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020),(Citation: McAfee Honeybee),(Citation: TechNet Systeminfo)

name: T9000
description: [T9000](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0098) is a backdoor that is a newer variant of the T5000 malware family, also known as Plat1. Its primary function is to gather information about the victim. It has been used in multiple targeted attacks against U.S.-based organizations. (Citation: FireEye admin@338 March 2014) (Citation: Palo Alto T9000 Feb 2016)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Palo Alto T9000 Feb 2016)
description_zh: [T9000]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0098）是一个后门，是T5000恶意软件家族的新变体，也称为plat1。它的主要功能是收集有关受害者的信息。它已用于针对美国组织的多次有针对性攻击。 （引文：FireEye Admin@2014年3月338日）（引文：Palo Alto T9000 2016年2月）

name: TAINTEDSCRIBE
description: [TAINTEDSCRIBE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0586) is a fully-featured beaconing implant integrated with command modules used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032). It was first reported in May 2020.(Citation: CISA MAR-10288834-2.v1  TAINTEDSCRIBE MAY 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CISA MAR-10288834-2.v1  TAINTEDSCRIBE MAY 2020),,(Citation: CISA MAR-10288834-2.v1  TAINTEDSCRIBE MAY 2020)

name: TDTESS
description: [TDTESS](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0164) is a 64-bit .NET binary backdoor used by [CopyKittens](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0052). (Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017),,(Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017)
