name: TEARDROP
description: [TEARDROP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0560) is a memory-only dropper that was discovered on some victim machines during investigations related to the 2020 SolarWinds cyber intrusion. It was likely used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least May 2020.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020),(Citation: Secureworks IRON RITUAL Profile),(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM May 2021),,(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020),(Citation: Check Point Sunburst Teardrop December 2020),(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
description_zh: [Teardrop]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0560）是一种内存的滴管，在与2020年Solarwinds网络侵入有关的调查期间，在某些受害者机器上发现了一个内存的滴管。它很可能自2020年5月以来[apt29]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0016）使用。（引用：2020年12月的FireEye Sunburst Backdoor）（引用：Microsoft Deep Dive Dive Dive Soloriate 2021年1月1月1日）

name: TEXTMATE
description: [TEXTMATE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0146) is a second-stage PowerShell backdoor that is memory-resident. It was observed being used along with [POWERSOURCE](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0145) in February 2017. (Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017),,(Citation: Cisco DNSMessenger March 2017),(Citation: FireEye FIN7 March 2017)
description_zh: [textmate]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0146）是第二阶段的PowerShell Backdoor，是内存居民。观察到与[PowerSource]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0145）一起使用。

name: TINYTYPHON
description: [TINYTYPHON](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0131) is a backdoor  that has been used by the actors responsible for the MONSOON campaign. The majority of its code was reportedly taken from the MyDoom worm. (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon)
relationship citations: (Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon),,(Citation: Forcepoint Monsoon)
description_zh: [tinytyphon]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0131）是一个后门，由负责季风活动的演员使用。据报道，其大部分代码都是从mydoom蠕虫中获取的。 （引文：力点季风）

name: TSCookie

[TSCookie](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0436) has been referred to as [PLEAD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0435) though more recent reporting indicates a separation between the two.(Citation: JPCert PLEAD Downloader June 2018)(Citation: JPCert BlackTech Malware September 2019)
contributors: Tatsuya Daitoku, Cyber Defense Institute, Inc.
relationship citations: (Citation: JPCert TSCookie March 2018),,(Citation: JPCert BlackTech Malware September 2019),(Citation: JPCert TSCookie March 2018)
description_zh: [tscookie]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0436）是一种远程访问工具（rat），在[blacktps：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0098 in针对日本目标的运动。（引用：JPCERT TSCOOKIE 2018年3月）（引文：JPCERT BLACKTECH恶意软件2019年9月）。 [tscookie]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0436）已被称为[[peale ead]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/software/s0435）两个。（引用：JPCERT求职者2018年6月）（引用：JPCERT BLACKTECH恶意软件2019年9月）

name: TURNEDUP

It has been dropped by [APT33](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0064)'s [StoneDrill](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0380) malware. (Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017) (Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017),(Citation: Symantec Elfin Mar 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Webinar Sept 2017),,(Citation: CyberBit Early Bird Apr 2018),(Citation: FireEye APT33 Sept 2017)

name: TYPEFRAME

relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT TYPEFRAME June 2018),,(Citation: US-CERT TYPEFRAME June 2018)

name: Taidoor
description: [Taidoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0011) is a remote access trojan (RAT) that has been used by Chinese government cyber actors to maintain access on victim networks.(Citation: CISA MAR-10292089-1.v2 TAIDOOR August 2021) [Taidoor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0011) has primarily been used against Taiwanese government organizations since at least 2010.(Citation: TrendMicro Taidoor)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: TrendMicro Taidoor),(Citation: CISA MAR-10292089-1.v2 TAIDOOR August 2021)
description_zh: [taidoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0011）是一款远程访问木马（老鼠），已被中国政府网络参与者使用来维持受害者网络的访问权限（引用：CISA MAR-10292089-- 1.V2 TAIDOOR 2021年8月）[taidoor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0011）主要在2010年以来对台湾政府组织进行了主要使用。

name: TajMahal
description: [TajMahal](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0467) is a multifunctional spying framework that has been in use since at least 2014. [TajMahal](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0467) is comprised of two separate packages, named Tokyo and Yokohama, and can deploy up to 80 plugins.(Citation: Kaspersky TajMahal April 2019)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Kaspersky TajMahal April 2019)

name: Tarrask
description: [Tarrask](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1011) is malware that has been used by [HAFNIUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0125) since at least August 2021. [Tarrask](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S1011) was designed to evade digital defenses and maintain persistence by generating concealed scheduled tasks.(Citation: Tarrask scheduled task)
relationship citations: (Citation: Tarrask scheduled task),,(Citation: Tarrask scheduled task)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1011）是[hafnium]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0125），至少从2021年8月202111年使用，它已被[hafnium]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0125）使用。 tarrask]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s1011）旨在通过生成隐藏的计划任务来逃避数字防御并保持持久性。（引用：Tarrask计划任务）

name: Tasklist
description: The [Tasklist](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0057) utility displays a list of applications and services with their Process IDs (PID) for all tasks running on either a local or a remote computer. It is packaged with Windows operating systems and can be executed from the command-line interface. (Citation: Microsoft Tasklist)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro DRBControl February 2020),(Citation: CISA SoreFang July 2016),(Citation: NCC Group APT15 Alive and Strong),(Citation: Alperovitch 2014),(Citation: Mandiant APT1),(Citation: Kaspersky Turla),(Citation: TrendMicro EarthLusca 2022),(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: Palo Alto OilRig May 2016),(Citation: FireEye APT34 Dec 2017),(Citation: Bitdefender FunnyDream Campaign November 2020),(Citation: McAfee Honeybee),(Citation: Microsoft Tasklist)
description_zh: [taskList]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0057）实用程序显示了在本地或远程计算机上运行的所有任务的应用程序和服务列表。它与Windows操作系统打包，可以从命令行接口执行。 （引用：Microsoft TaskList）

name: ThiefQuest
description: [ThiefQuest](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0595) is a virus, data stealer, and wiper that presents itself as ransomware targeting macOS systems. [ThiefQuest](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0595) was first seen in 2020 distributed via trojanized pirated versions of popular macOS software on Russian forums sharing torrent links.(Citation: Reed thiefquest fake ransom) Even though [ThiefQuest](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0595) presents itself as ransomware, since the dynamically generated encryption key is never sent to the attacker it may be more appropriately thought of as a form of wiper malware.(Citation: wardle evilquest partii)(Citation: reed thiefquest ransomware analysis)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: wardle evilquest partii),(Citation: wardle evilquest parti),(Citation: reed thiefquest ransomware analysis),(Citation: Trendmicro Evolving ThiefQuest 2020)
description_zh: [ThiefQuest]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0595）是一种病毒，数据窃取器和雨刮器，它以MacOS系统的勒索软件为目标。 [Thiefquest]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0595）在2020年首次通过Trojanized Pirated Pirated Pired版本在俄罗斯论坛上的流行MacOS软件分发，共享Torrent链接。 ThiefQuest]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0595）将自己作为勒索软件表示，因为动态生成的加密密钥永远不会发送给攻击者，因此可以更适当地将其视为雨水恶意软件的一种形式（引用。 ：Wardle EvilQuest Partii）（引用：Reed Thiefquest勒索软件分析）

name: ThreatNeedle
description: [ThreatNeedle](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0665) is a backdoor that has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032) since at least 2019 to target cryptocurrency, defense, and mobile gaming organizations.  It is considered to be an advanced cluster of [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032)'s Manuscrypt (a.k.a. NukeSped) malware family.(Citation: Kaspersky ThreatNeedle Feb 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky ThreatNeedle Feb 2021),,(Citation: Kaspersky ThreatNeedle Feb 2021)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0665）是[lazarus group]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0032）以来至少从2019年开始到2019目标加密货币，防御和移动游戏组织。它被认为是[lazarus group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0032）的高级群集。

description: [TinyTurla](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0668) is a backdoor that has been used by [Turla](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0010) against targets in the US, Germany, and Afghanistan since at least 2020.(Citation: Talos TinyTurla September 2021)
contributors: Kyaw Pyiyt Htet, @KyawPyiytHtet; Massimiliano Romano, BT Security

name: Tomiris
description: [Tomiris](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0671) is a backdoor written in Go that continuously queries its C2 server for executables to download and execute on a victim system. It was first reported in September 2021 during an investigation of a successful DNS hijacking campaign against a Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) member. Security researchers assess there are similarities between [Tomiris](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0671) and [GoldMax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0588).(Citation: Kaspersky Tomiris Sep 2021)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Kaspersky Tomiris Sep 2021)
description_zh: [tomiris]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0671）是在GO中写的后门，它不断查询其C2服务器，以便在受害者系统上下载和执行可执行文件。在2021年9月对一项针对独立国家（CIS）成员的联邦政府进行成功的DNS劫持运动的调查中，该活动于2021年9月首次报道。安全研究人员评估[tomiris]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0671）和[Goldmax]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/s0588）之间有相似之处。 2021年9月）

name: Tor
description: [Tor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0183) is a software suite and network that provides increased anonymity on the Internet. It creates a multi-hop proxy network and utilizes multilayer encryption to protect both the message and routing information. [Tor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0183) utilizes "Onion Routing," in which messages are encrypted with multiple layers of encryption; at each step in the proxy network, the topmost layer is decrypted and the contents forwarded on to the next node until it reaches its destination. (Citation: Dingledine Tor The Second-Generation Onion Router)
relationship citations: (Citation: CISA AA21-200A APT40 July 2021),(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach),(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory GRU Brute Force Campaign July 2021),(Citation: BlackBerry CostaRicto November 2020),(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019),(Citation: Dingledine Tor The Second-Generation Onion Router)
description_zh: [tor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0183）是一个软件套件和网络，可在Internet上提供更多的匿名性。它创建了一个多跳的代理网络，并利用多层加密来保护消息和路由信息。 [tor]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0183）使用“洋葱路由”，其中消息通过多个加密层进行加密；在代理网络的每个步骤中，最上层被解密，并且内容转发到下一个节点，直到它到达目的地为止。 （引文：二代洋葱路由器的丁丁丁）

name: Torisma
description: [Torisma](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0678) is a second stage implant designed for specialized monitoring that has been used by [Lazarus Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0032). [Torisma](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0678) was discovered during an investigation into the 2020 Operation North Star campaign that targeted the defense sector.(Citation: McAfee Lazarus Nov 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: McAfee Lazarus Nov 2020),,(Citation: McAfee Lazarus Nov 2020)
description_zh: [torisma]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0678）是第二阶段植入物，设计用于专门监控，该植入物已由[lazarus group]使用，（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org.org/groups/groups/g0032 ）。 [Torisma]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0678）在对针对国防部门的2020年北极星竞选活动的调查中被发现。

name: TrailBlazer
description: [TrailBlazer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0682) is a modular malware that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2019.(Citation: CrowdStrike StellarParticle January 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: CrowdStrike StellarParticle January 2022),,(Citation: CrowdStrike StellarParticle January 2022)

name: TrickBot
description: [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) is a Trojan spyware program written in C++ that first emerged in September 2016 as a possible successor to [Dyre](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0024). [TrickBot](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0266) was developed and initially used by [Wizard Spider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0102) for targeting banking sites in North America, Australia, and throughout Europe; it has since been used against all sectors worldwide as part of "big game hunting" ransomware campaigns.(Citation: S2 Grupo TrickBot June 2017)(Citation: Fidelis TrickBot Oct 2016)(Citation: IBM TrickBot Nov 2016)(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020)
contributors: Cybereason Nocturnus, @nocturnus; Daniyal Naeem, BT Security; FS-ISAC; Omkar Gudhate
relationship citations: (Citation: Proofpoint TA505 Sep 2017),(Citation: IBM TA505 April 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Wizard Spider October 2020),(Citation: Sophos New Ryuk Attack October 2020),(Citation: DHS/CISA Ransomware Targeting Healthcare October 2020),(Citation: CrowdStrike Grim Spider May 2019),,(Citation: Cyberreason Anchor December 2019),(Citation: IBM TrickBot Nov 2016),(Citation: Bitdefender Trickbot VNC module Whitepaper 2021),(Citation: TrendMicro Trickbot Feb 2019),(Citation: Bitdefender Trickbot March 2020),(Citation: Fidelis TrickBot Oct 2016),(Citation: ESET Trickbot Oct 2020),(Citation: Fortinet TrickBot),(Citation: Joe Sec Trickbot),(Citation: Microsoft Totbrick Oct 2017),(Citation: Bitdefender Trickbot C2 infra Nov 2020),(Citation: Trend Micro Totbrick Oct 2016),(Citation: Trickbot VNC module July 2021),(Citation: S2 Grupo TrickBot June 2017),(Citation: Eclypsium Trickboot December 2020),(Citation: Trend Micro Trickbot Nov 2018)
description_zh: [trickbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0266）是一款以C ++编写的Trojan Spyware程序，该程序于2016年9月首次出现，是[https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.mitre.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org.org ,， /软件/S0024）。 [trickbot]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0266）已开发并最初由[Wizard Spider]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0102）用于针对北美银行网站的目标，澳大利亚以及整个欧洲；此后，它已作为“大型游戏狩猎”勒索软件广告系列的一部分。蜘蛛2020年10月）

name: Trojan.Karagany
description: [Trojan.Karagany](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0094) is a modular remote access tool used for recon and linked to [Dragonfly](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0035). The source code for [Trojan.Karagany](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0094) originated from Dream Loader malware which was leaked in 2010 and sold on underground forums. (Citation: Symantec Dragonfly)(Citation: Secureworks Karagany July 2019)(Citation: Dragos DYMALLOY )
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks Karagany July 2019),(Citation: Symantec Dragonfly),(Citation: Gigamon Berserk Bear October 2021),,(Citation: Symantec Dragonfly),(Citation: Secureworks Karagany July 2019)

It is a collection of modules written in the Delphi programming language. (Citation: Microsoft Win Defender Truvasys Sep 2017) (Citation: Microsoft NEODYMIUM Dec 2016) (Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 21)

name: Turian
description: [Turian](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0647) is a backdoor that has been used by [BackdoorDiplomacy](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0135) to target Ministries of Foreign Affairs, telecommunication companies, and charities in Africa, Europe, the Middle East, and Asia. First reported in 2021, [Turian](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0647) is likely related to Quarian, an older backdoor that was last observed being used in 2013 against diplomatic targets in Syria and the United States.(Citation: ESET BackdoorDiplomacy Jun 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET BackdoorDiplomacy Jun 2021),,(Citation: ESET BackdoorDiplomacy Jun 2021)
description_zh: [Turian]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0647）是[BackdoorDiplomacy]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0135）已使用的后门，非洲，欧洲，中东和亚洲的电信公司和慈善机构。 [turian]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0647）首次报道，可能与Quarian有关，Quarian是一个较旧的后门，该后门在2013年被观察到，针对叙利亚和美国的外交目标。 （引文：ESET BacktoOdiorDomacy 2021年6月）

name: UACMe

name: USBStealer
description: [USBStealer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0136) is malware that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) since at least 2005 to extract information from air-gapped networks. It does not have the capability to communicate over the Internet and has been used in conjunction with [ADVSTORESHELL](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0045). (Citation: ESET Sednit USBStealer 2014) (Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy)
relationship citations: (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3),,(Citation: ESET Sednit USBStealer 2014),(Citation: Kaspersky Sofacy)
description_zh: [USBSTEALER]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0136）是[apt28]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0007）已使用的恶意软件，因为来自空气网络。它没有能力通过Internet进行通信，并且已与[Advstoreshell]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0045）一起使用。 （引文：Eset Sednit USBSTEALER 2014）（引文：Kaspersky Sofacy）

name: USBferry
description: [USBferry](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0452) is an information stealing malware and has been used by [Tropic Trooper](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0081) in targeted attacks against Taiwanese and Philippine air-gapped military environments. [USBferry](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0452) shares an overlapping codebase with [YAHOYAH](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0388), though it has several features which makes it a distinct piece of malware.(Citation: TrendMicro Tropic Trooper May 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro Tropic Trooper May 2020),,(Citation: TrendMicro Tropic Trooper May 2020)
description_zh: [USBferry](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0452) is an information stealing malware and has been used by [Tropic Trooper](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0081) in targeted attacks反对台湾和菲律宾空心的军事环境。 [USBFERRY]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0452）与[yahoyah]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0388）共享一个重叠的代码库，尽管它具有几个功能一件不同的恶意软件。

name: Ursnif
description: [Ursnif](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0386) is a banking trojan and variant of the Gozi malware observed being spread through various automated exploit kits, [Spearphishing Attachment](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1566/001)s, and malicious links.(Citation: NJCCIC Ursnif Sept 2016)(Citation: ProofPoint Ursnif Aug 2016) [Ursnif](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0386) is associated primarily with data theft, but variants also include components (backdoors, spyware, file injectors, etc.) capable of a wide variety of behaviors.(Citation: TrendMicro Ursnif Mar 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Valak May 2020),(Citation: Secureworks GOLD CABIN),(Citation: Unit 42 Valak July 2020),(Citation: Unit 42 TA551 Jan 2021),,(Citation: ProofPoint Ursnif Aug 2016),(Citation: TrendMicro BKDR_URSNIF.SM),(Citation: Bromium Ursnif Mar 2017),(Citation: TrendMicro PE_URSNIF.A2),(Citation: NJCCIC Ursnif Sept 2016),(Citation: FireEye Ursnif Nov 2017),(Citation: TrendMicro Ursnif File Dec 2014),(Citation: TrendMicro Ursnif Mar 2015)
description_zh: [ursnif]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0386）是一个银行木马，观察到的gozi恶意软件的变体通过各种自动化的exploit套件传播，[spearphensing enationment intactment intactment intactmentsmant interphanding entactment]（https：//attack.mitre。 org/Techniques/t1566/001）和恶意链接。（引用：NJCCIC URSNIF 2016年9月）（引用：Proofpoint Ursnif 2016年8月）[ursnif]（https://attack.mitarc.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/software/software/s0386）主要带有数据盗窃，但变体还包括能够采用多种行为的组件（后门，间谍软件，文件注射器等）。

[VBShower](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0442) has been used as a downloader for second stage payloads, including [PowerShower](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0441).(Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019),,(Citation: Kaspersky Cloud Atlas August 2019)

name: VERMIN

description: [Valak](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0476) is a multi-stage modular malware that can function as a standalone information stealer or downloader, first observed in 2019 targeting enterprises in the US and Germany.(Citation: Cybereason Valak May 2020)(Citation: Unit 42 Valak July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybereason Valak May 2020),(Citation: Secureworks GOLD CABIN),(Citation: Unit 42 Valak July 2020),(Citation: Unit 42 TA551 Jan 2021),,(Citation: Cybereason Valak May 2020),(Citation: SentinelOne Valak June 2020),(Citation: Unit 42 Valak July 2020)
description_zh: [valak]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0476）是一种多阶段的模块化恶意软件，可以用作独立信息窃取器或下载器，首次在2019年在美国和德国进行企业。 ：Cyber​​eason Valak 2020年5月）（引文：42 Unit 2020年7月）

name: VaporRage
description: [VaporRage](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0636) is a shellcode downloader that has been used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) since at least 2021.(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)
relationship citations: (Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021),,(Citation: MSTIC Nobelium Toolset May 2021)
description_zh: [https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0636）是一个ShellCode下载器，至少从2021年开始，它已被[APT29]（https：//attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mitre.mit--floade）。 （引文：Mstic Nobelium工具集2021年5月）

name: Vasport
description: [Vasport](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0207) is a trojan used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) to open a backdoor on compromised hosts. (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012) (Citation: Symantec Vasport May 2012)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Vasport May 2012)
description_zh: [vasport]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0207）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的特洛伊木马，可在受损的主机上打开后门。 （引文：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec Vasport 2012年5月）

name: Volgmer
description: [Volgmer](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0180) is a backdoor Trojan designed to provide covert access to a compromised system. It has been used since at least 2013 to target the government, financial, automotive, and media industries. Its primary delivery mechanism is suspected to be spearphishing. (Citation: US-CERT Volgmer Nov 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: US-CERT Volgmer Nov 2017),,(Citation: US-CERT Volgmer Nov 2017),(Citation: US-CERT Volgmer 2 Nov 2017),(Citation: Symantec Volgmer Aug 2014)
description_zh: [volgmer]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0180）是一款旨在提供妥协系统的秘密访问的后门特洛伊木马。它至少从2013年开始被用来针对政府，金融，汽车和媒体行业。怀疑其主要的输送机制是矛盾的。 （引文：美国库尔特沃尔格默2017年11月）

name: WEBC2
description: [WEBC2](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0109) is a family of backdoor malware used by [APT1](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0006) as early as July 2006. [WEBC2](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0109) backdoors are designed to retrieve a webpage, with commands hidden in HTML comments or special tags, from a predetermined C2 server. (Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix)(Citation: Mandiant APT1)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1),,(Citation: Mandiant APT1),(Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix)
description_zh: [webc2]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0109）是[APT1]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0006）使用的Backdoor恶意软件系列，于2006年7月。 [webc2]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0109）backdoors旨在检索网页，并在预定的C2服务器中隐藏了HTML注释或特殊标签中的命令。 （引用：Mandiant APT1附录）（引用：Mandiant APT1）

name: WINDSHIELD
description: [WINDSHIELD](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0155) is a signature backdoor used by [APT32](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0050). (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017),,(Citation: FireEye APT32 May 2017)
description_zh: [Windshield]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0155）是[apt32]（https://attack.mitre.org.org/groups/g0050）使用的签名后门。 （引文：FireEye APT32 2017年5月）

name: WINERACK
description: [WINERACK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0219) is a backdoor used by [APT37](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0067). (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018),,(Citation: FireEye APT37 Feb 2018)
description_zh: [winerack]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0219）是[apt37]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0067）使用的后门。 （引文：FireEye APT37 2018年2月）

name: WannaCry
description: [WannaCry](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0366) is ransomware that was first seen in a global attack during May 2017, which affected more than 150 countries. It contains worm-like features to spread itself across a computer network using the SMBv1 exploit EternalBlue.(Citation: LogRhythm WannaCry)(Citation: US-CERT WannaCry 2017)(Citation: Washington Post WannaCry 2017)(Citation: FireEye WannaCry 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: FireEye APT38 Oct 2018),(Citation: FireEye WannaCry 2017),(Citation: LogRhythm WannaCry),(Citation: SecureWorks WannaCry Analysis),,(Citation: US-CERT WannaCry 2017),(Citation: SecureWorks WannaCry Analysis),(Citation: FireEye WannaCry 2017),(Citation: LogRhythm WannaCry)
description_zh: [WannaCry]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0366）是勒索软件，在2017年5月的全球攻击中首次出现，影响了150多个国家。它包含类似蠕虫的功能，可以使用SMBV1利用EternalBlue在计算机网络中传播。

name: WarzoneRAT
description: [WarzoneRAT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0670) is a malware-as-a-service remote access tool (RAT) written in C++ that has been publicly available for purchase since at least late 2018.(Citation: Check Point Warzone Feb 2020)(Citation: Uptycs Warzone UAC Bypass November 2020)
contributors: Abhijit Mohanta, @abhijit_mohanta, Uptycs; Shilpesh Trivedi, Uptycs
relationship citations: (Citation: Check Point Warzone Feb 2020),(Citation: Uptycs Confucius APT Jan 2021),,(Citation: Check Point Warzone Feb 2020),(Citation: Uptycs Confucius APT Jan 2021),(Citation: Uptycs Warzone UAC Bypass November 2020)
description_zh: [WARZONERAT]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0670）是C ++编写的Malware-AS-A-Service Remote Access工具（Rat），至少从2018年底开始就可以公开购买。（（（引用：Check Point Warzone 2020年2月）（引文：UPTYCS WARZONE UAC绕行2020年11月）

name: WastedLocker
description: [WastedLocker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0612) is a ransomware family attributed to [Indrik Spider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0119) that has been used since at least May 2020. [WastedLocker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0612) has been used against a broad variety of sectors, including manufacturing, information technology, and media.(Citation: Symantec WastedLocker June 2020)(Citation: NCC Group WastedLocker June 2020)(Citation: Sentinel Labs WastedLocker July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: NCC Group WastedLocker June 2020),(Citation: Crowdstrike EvilCorp March 2021),,(Citation: NCC Group WastedLocker June 2020),(Citation: Sentinel Labs WastedLocker July 2020),(Citation: Symantec WastedLocker June 2020)
description_zh: [WastedLocker](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0612) is a ransomware family attributed to [Indrik Spider](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0119) that has been used since at least 2020年5月。[wastedlocker]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0612）已用于各种各样的部门，包括制造，信息技术和媒体。 ：NCC Group Wastedlocker 2020年6月）（引文：Sentinel Labs Wastedlocker 2020年7月）

name: Waterbear
description: [Waterbear](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0579) is modular malware attributed to [BlackTech](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0098) that has been used primarily for lateral movement, decrypting, and triggering payloads and is capable of hiding network behaviors.(Citation: Trend Micro Waterbear December 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Trend Micro Waterbear December 2019),,(Citation: Trend Micro Waterbear December 2019)
description_zh: [waterbear]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0579）是模块化的恶意软件，归因于[blackTech]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0098）解密和触发有效载荷，并能够隐藏网络行为。

name: WellMail
description: [WellMail](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0515) is a lightweight malware written in Golang used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016), similar in design and structure to [WellMess](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0514).(Citation: CISA WellMail July 2020)(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: CISA WellMail July 2020),(Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020),,(Citation: CISA WellMail July 2020),(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)
description_zh: [wellmail]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0515）是一种用[apt29]使用的Golang编写的轻量级恶意软件[wellmess]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0514）的结构。

name: WellMess
description: [WellMess](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0514) is lightweight malware family with variants written in .NET and Golang that has been in use since at least 2018 by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016).(Citation: CISA WellMess July 2020)(Citation: PWC WellMess July 2020)(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)
relationship citations: (Citation: Cybersecurity Advisory SVR TTP May 2021),(Citation: PWC WellMess C2 August 2020),(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020),(Citation: CISA WellMess July 2020),(Citation: PWC WellMess July 2020),,(Citation: PWC WellMess July 2020),(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020),(Citation: PWC WellMess C2 August 2020),(Citation: CISA WellMess July 2020)
description_zh: [WELLMESS]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0514）是轻量级恶意软件家族，其中包含.NET和Golang的变体，并且至少从[APT29]（https：// Attack）开始使用。 mitre.org/groups/g0016)。（CITATIT：CISA Wellmess 2020年7月）（引用：PWC Wellmess 2020年7月）（引用：NCSC APT29 2020年7月29日）

name: Wevtutil
description: [Wevtutil](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0645) is a Windows command-line utility that enables administrators to retrieve information about event logs and publishers.(Citation: Wevtutil Microsoft Documentation)
contributors: Harshal Tupsamudre, Qualys; Viren Chaudhari, Qualys
relationship citations: (Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016),(Citation: FoxIT Wocao December 2019),(Citation: F-Secure Lazarus Cryptocurrency Aug 2020),(Citation: Wevtutil Microsoft Documentation),(Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016)
description_zh: [wevtutil]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0645）是一个Windows命令 - 线实用程序，使管理员能够检索有关事件日志和发布者的信息。（引用：wevtutil microsoft文档）

name: WhisperGate
description: [WhisperGate](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0689) is a multi-stage wiper designed to look like ransomware that has been used in attacks against Ukraine since at least January 2022.(Citation: Cybereason WhisperGate February 2022)(Citation: Unit 42 WhisperGate January 2022)(Citation: Microsoft WhisperGate January 2022)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant UNC2589 March 2022),(Citation: CrowdStrike Ember Bear Profile March 2022),,(Citation: Cisco Ukraine Wipers January 2022),(Citation: Microsoft WhisperGate January 2022),(Citation: Cybereason WhisperGate February 2022),(Citation: Medium S2W WhisperGate January 2022),(Citation: Unit 42 WhisperGate January 2022),(Citation: Crowdstrike WhisperGate January 2022)
description_zh: [Whispergate]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0689）是一款多阶段雨刷，设计看起来像勒索软件，至少自2022年1月以来一直在针对乌克兰的攻击中使用。 （引文：42单元Whispergate 2022年1月）（引文：微软Whispergate 2022年1月）

name: Wiarp
description: [Wiarp](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0206) is a trojan used by [Elderwood](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0066) to open a backdoor on compromised hosts. (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012) (Citation: Symantec Wiarp May 2012)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec Elderwood Sept 2012),,(Citation: Symantec Wiarp May 2012)
description_zh: [WIARP]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0206）是[Elderwood]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0066）使用的特洛伊木马，以打开损害的主机后门。 （引文：Symantec Elderwood 2012年9月）（引文：Symantec Wiarp 2012年5月）

name: WinMM
description: [WinMM](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0059) is a full-featured, simple backdoor used by [Naikon](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0019). (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015),(Citation: CameraShy),,(Citation: Baumgartner Naikon 2015)
description_zh: [winmm]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0059）是[naikon]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0019）使用的完整，简单的后门。 （引文：Baumgartner Naikon 2015）

name: WindTail
description: [WindTail](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0466) is a macOS surveillance implant used by [Windshift](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0112). [WindTail](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0466) shares code similarities with Hack Back aka KitM OSX.(Citation: SANS Windshift August 2018)(Citation: objective-see windtail1 dec 2018)(Citation: objective-see windtail2 jan 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: SANS Windshift August 2018),(Citation: objective-see windtail2 jan 2019),(Citation: objective-see windtail1 dec 2018),,(Citation: objective-see windtail1 dec 2018),(Citation: objective-see windtail2 jan 2019)
description_zh: [Windtail]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0466）是[WindShift]使用的MACOS监视植入物（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/groups/g0112）。 [windtail]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0466）与hack back aka kitm osx共享代码相似性（引用：SANS WINDSHIFT 2018年8月） - 请参阅Windtail2 2019年1月）

name: Windows Credential Editor
description: [Windows Credential Editor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0005) is a password dumping tool. (Citation: Amplia WCE)
relationship citations: (Citation: Dell TG-3390),(Citation: FireEye FIN6 April 2016),(Citation: Microsoft GALLIUM December 2019),(Citation: FireEye APT40 March 2019),(Citation: Mandiant FIN5 GrrCON Oct 2016),(Citation: DarkReading FireEye FIN5 Oct 2015),(Citation: Secureworks BRONZE BUTLER Oct 2017),(Citation: Dark Reading APT39 JAN 2019),(Citation: Symantec Tick Apr 2016),(Citation: FireEye APT39 Jan 2019),,(Citation: Amplia WCE)
description_zh: [Windows凭证编辑器]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0005）是一个密码转储工具。 （引文：Amplia WCE）

name: Winexe
description: [Winexe](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0191) is a lightweight, open source tool similar to [PsExec](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0029) designed to allow system administrators to execute commands on remote servers. (Citation: Winexe Github Sept 2013) [Winexe](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0191) is unique in that it is a GNU/Linux based client. (Citation: Überwachung APT28 Forfiles June 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: Secureworks IRON TWILIGHT Active Measures March 2017),(Citation: SecureList Silence Nov 2017),(Citation: Überwachung APT28 Forfiles June 2015),(Citation: Securelist DarkVishnya Dec 2018),,(Citation: Secpod Winexe June 2017)
description_zh: [WINEXE]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0191）是一种轻巧的开源工具，类似于[PSEXEC]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org/software/s0029），旨在允许系统管理员在远程服务器上执行命令。 （引用：Winexe GitHub 2013年9月）[WINEXE]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0191）是唯一的，因为它是基于GNU/Linux的客户端。 （引文：überwachungapt28 Forfiles 2015年6月）

name: Wingbird
description: [Wingbird](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0176) is a backdoor that appears to be a version of commercial software [FinFisher](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0182). It is reportedly used to attack individual computers instead of networks. It was used by [NEODYMIUM](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0055) in a May 2016 campaign. (Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 21) (Citation: Microsoft NEODYMIUM Dec 2016)
relationship citations: (Citation: Microsoft NEODYMIUM Dec 2016),(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 21),,(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 21),(Citation: Microsoft Wingbird Nov 2017)
description_zh: [wingbird]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0176）是一个后门，似乎是商业软件的版本[Finfisher]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.mitre.org/software/software/s0182）。据报道，它用于攻击单个计算机而不是网络。它在2016年5月的活动中被[neododmium]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0055）使用。 （引文：Microsoft Sir Vol 21）（引文：Microsoft Neododymium 2016年12月）

name: Winnti for Linux
description: [Winnti for Linux](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0430) is a trojan, seen since at least 2015, designed specifically for targeting Linux systems. Reporting indicates the winnti malware family is shared across a number of actors including [Winnti Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0044). The Windows variant is tracked separately under [Winnti for Windows](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0141).(Citation: Chronicle Winnti for Linux May 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro EarthLusca 2022),(Citation: Crowdstrike GTR2020 Mar 2020),,(Citation: Chronicle Winnti for Linux May 2019)
description_zh: [Winnti for Linux]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0430）是一家特洛伊木马，至少从2015年开始，专门用于针对Linux系统。报告表明，Winnti恶意软件家族在[Winnti Group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0044）等许多演员中共享。 Windows变体在[Windows的Winnti]下单独跟踪（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0141）。

name: Winnti for Windows
description: [Winnti for Windows](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0141) is a modular remote access Trojan (RAT) that has been used likely by multiple groups to carry out intrusions in various regions since at least 2010, including by one group referred to as the same name, [Winnti Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0044).(Citation: Kaspersky Winnti April 2013)(Citation: Microsoft Winnti Jan 2017)(Citation: Novetta Winnti April 2015)(Citation: 401 TRG Winnti Umbrella May 2018). The Linux variant is tracked separately under [Winnti for Linux](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0430).(Citation: Chronicle Winnti for Linux May 2019)
relationship citations: (Citation: Kaspersky Winnti June 2015),(Citation: Kaspersky Winnti April 2013),,(Citation: Microsoft Winnti Jan 2017),(Citation: Novetta Winnti April 2015)
description_zh: [Windows的winnti]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0141）是一个模块化的远程访问木马（Rat），多个组可能使用多个组来在各个地区进行入侵，至少在2010年以来，包括由一个小组称为同名，[winnti group]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0044）。 Winnti 2015年4月）（引文：401 TRG Winnti雨伞2018年5月）。 Linux变体在[linux的Winnti]下分别跟踪（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0430）。

name: Wiper
description: [Wiper](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0041) is a family of destructive malware used in March 2013 during breaches of South Korean banks and media companies. (Citation: Dell Wiper)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Dell Wiper)
description_zh: [湿雨]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0041）是2013年3月违反韩国银行和媒体公司的破坏性恶意软件家族。 （引文：戴尔雨刮器）

name: XAgentOSX
description: [XAgentOSX](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0161) is a trojan that has been used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007)  on OS X and appears to be a port of their standard [CHOPSTICK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0023) or XAgent trojan. (Citation: XAgentOSX 2017)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec APT28 Oct 2018),(Citation: XAgentOSX 2017),(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018),,(Citation: XAgentOSX 2017)
description_zh: [xagentosx]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0161）是一个木马，在OS X上已被[APT28]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0007）使用成为其标准[筷子]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0023）或Xagent Trojan的端口。 （引文：Xagentosx 2017）

name: XCSSET
description: [XCSSET](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0658) is a macOS modular backdoor that targets Xcode application developers. [XCSSET](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0658) was first observed in August 2020 and has been used to install a backdoor component, modify browser applications, conduct collection, and provide ransomware-like encryption capabilities.(Citation: trendmicro xcsset xcode project 2020)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: trendmicro xcsset xcode project 2020),(Citation: 20 macOS Common Tools and Techniques),(Citation: Application Bundle Manipulation Brandon Dalton)
description_zh: [XCSSET]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0658）是一个针对Xcode应用程序开发人员的MacOS模块化后门。 [XCSSET]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0658）于2020年8月首次观察到，已用于安装后门组件，修改浏览器应用程序，进行操作收集，并提供类似lansomware的Encryptions功能（（（引文：TrendMicro XCSSET XCODE Project 2020）

name: XTunnel
description: [XTunnel](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0117) a VPN-like network proxy tool that can relay traffic between a C2 server and a victim. It was first seen in May 2013 and reportedly used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) during the compromise of the Democratic National Committee. (Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016) (Citation: Invincea XTunnel) (Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)
relationship citations: (Citation: Symantec APT28 Oct 2018),(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 3),(Citation: Secureworks IRON TWILIGHT Active Measures March 2017),(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018),,(Citation: Invincea XTunnel),(Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016),(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)
description_zh: [XTUNNEL]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0117）可以在C2服务器和受害者之间中继流量的VPN-Like网络代理工具。它于2013年5月首次出现，据报道，在民主党全国委员会妥协期间，[APT28]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0007）使用了它。 （引用：CrowdStrike DNC 2016年6月）（引文：Invincea Xtunnel）（引用：ESET SEDNIT第2部分）

name: Xbash
description: [Xbash](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0341) is a malware family that has targeted Linux and Microsoft Windows servers. The malware has been tied to the Iron Group, a threat actor group known for previous ransomware attacks. [Xbash](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0341) was developed in Python and then converted into a self-contained Linux ELF executable by using PyInstaller.(Citation: Unit42 Xbash Sept 2018)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Unit42 Xbash Sept 2018),(Citation: Trend Micro Xbash Sept 2018)
description_zh: [XBASH]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0341）是针对Linux和Microsoft Windows服务器的恶意软件家族。该恶意软件已与Iron Group绑定，Iron Group是一个以先前的勒索软件攻击而闻名的威胁性演员组。 [XBASH]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0341）在Python中开发，然后通过使用Pyinstaller转换为可执行的自式Linux Elf。

name: YAHOYAH
description: [YAHOYAH](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0388) is a Trojan used by [Tropic Trooper](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0081) as a second-stage backdoor.(Citation: TrendMicro TropicTrooper 2015)
relationship citations: (Citation: TrendMicro TropicTrooper 2015),,(Citation: TrendMicro TropicTrooper 2015)
description_zh: [yahoyah]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0388）是[Tropic Trooper]（https：//attack.mitre.org/groups/g0081）使用的特洛伊木马（https trooper]引文：TrendMicro Tropictrooper 2015）

name: ZLib
description: [ZLib](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0086) is a full-featured backdoor that was used as a second-stage implant during [Operation Dust Storm](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0016) since at least 2014. [ZLib](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0086) is malware and should not be confused with the legitimate compression library from which its name is derived.(Citation: Cylance Dust Storm)

name: Zeus Panda
description: [Zeus Panda](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0330) is a Trojan designed to steal banking information and other sensitive credentials for exfiltration. [Zeus Panda](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0330)’s original source code was leaked in 2011, allowing threat actors to use its source code as a basis for new malware variants. It is mainly used to target Windows operating systems ranging from Windows XP through Windows 10.(Citation: Talos Zeus Panda Nov 2017)(Citation: GDATA Zeus Panda June 2017)
relationship citations: ,,(Citation: Talos Zeus Panda Nov 2017),(Citation: GDATA Zeus Panda June 2017)

name: xCaon
description: [xCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0653) is an HTTP variant of the [BoxCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0651) malware family that has used by [IndigoZebra](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0136) since at least 2014. [xCaon](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0653) has been used to target political entities in Central Asia, including Kyrgyzstan and Uzbekistan.(Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021)(Citation: Securelist APT Trends Q2 2017)
contributors: Manikantan Srinivasan, NEC Corporation India; Pooja Natarajan, NEC Corporation India; Yoshihiro Kori, NEC Corporation
relationship citations: (Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021),,(Citation: Checkpoint IndigoZebra July 2021)
description_zh: [XCAON]（https://attack.mitre.org/software/s0653）是[boxcaon]（https://attack.mitre.mitre.org.org/software/s0651）的http变体，已使用[indigigozebra family fesl ]（https://attack.mitre.org/groups/g0136）至少从2014年开始。包括吉尔吉斯斯坦和乌兹别克斯坦。

name: xCmd
description: [xCmd](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0123) is an open source tool that is similar to [PsExec](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0029) and allows the user to execute applications on remote systems. (Citation: xCmd)
relationship citations: (Citation: Mandiant APT1 Appendix),,(Citation: xCmd)

name: yty

name: zwShell
description: [zwShell](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0350) is a remote access tool (RAT) written in Delphi that has been seen in the wild since the spring of 2010 and used by threat actors during [Night Dragon](https://attack.mitre.org/campaigns/C0002).(Citation: McAfee Night Dragon)
relationship citations: ,(Citation: McAfee Night Dragon),(Citation: McAfee Night Dragon)
